216class Statistics
217{
218 public:
219 Statistics() {}
220 void begin(const char *name)
221 {
222 msg("%s", name);
223 stats.emplace_back(name,0);
224 startTime = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
225 }
226 void end()
227 {
228 std::chrono::steady_clock::time_point endTime = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
229 stats.back().elapsed = static_cast<double>(std::chrono::duration_cast<
230 std::chrono::microseconds>(endTime - startTime).count())/1000000.0;
231 warn_flush();
232 }
233 void print()
234 {
235 bool restore=FALSE;
236 if (Debug::isFlagSet(Debug::Time))
237 {
238 Debug::clearFlag(Debug::Time);
239 restore=TRUE;
240 }
241 msg("----------------------\n");
242 for (const auto &s : stats)
243 {
244 msg("Spent %.6f seconds in %s",s.elapsed,s.name);
245 }
246 if (restore) Debug::setFlag(Debug::Time);
247 }
248 private:
249 struct stat
250 {
251 const char *name;
252 double elapsed;
253 //stat() : name(nullptr),elapsed(0) {}
254 stat(const char *n, double el) : name(n),elapsed(el) {}
255 };
256 std::vector<stat> stats;
257 std::chrono::steady_clock::time_point startTime;
258} g_s;

296static void addPageToContext(PageDef *pd,Entry *root)
297{
298 if (root->parent()) // add the page to it's scope
299 {
300 QCString scope = root->parent()->name;
301 if (root->parent()->section.isPackageDoc())
302 {
303 scope=substitute(scope,".","::");
304 }
305 scope = stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(scope);
306 scope+="::"+pd->name();
307 Definition *d = findScopeFromQualifiedName(Doxygen::globalScope,scope,nullptr,root->tagInfo());
308 if (d)
309 {
310 pd->setPageScope(d);
311 }
312 }
313}
314
315static void addRelatedPage(Entry *root)
316{
317 GroupDef *gd=nullptr;
318 for (const Grouping &g : root->groups)
319 {
320 if (!g.groupname.isEmpty() && (gd=Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(g.groupname))) break;
321 }
322 //printf("---> addRelatedPage() %s gd=%p\n",qPrint(root->name),gd);
323 QCString doc=root->doc+root->inbodyDocs;
324
325 PageDef *pd = addRelatedPage(root->name,root->args,doc,
326 root->docFile,
327 root->docLine,
328 root->startLine,
329 root->sli,
330 gd,root->tagInfo(),
331 FALSE,
332 root->lang
333 );
334 if (pd)
335 {
336 pd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
337 pd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
338 pd->setLocalToc(root->localToc);
339 addPageToContext(pd,root);
340 }
341}
342
343static void buildGroupListFiltered(const Entry *root,bool additional, bool includeExternal)
344{
345 if (root->section.isGroupDoc() && !root->name.isEmpty() &&
346 ((!includeExternal && root->tagInfo()==nullptr) ||
347 ( includeExternal && root->tagInfo()!=nullptr))
348 )
349 {
350 AUTO_TRACE("additional={} includeExternal={}",additional,includeExternal);
351 if ((root->groupDocType==Entry::GROUPDOC_NORMAL && !additional) ||
352 (root->groupDocType!=Entry::GROUPDOC_NORMAL && additional))
353 {
354 GroupDef *gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(root->name);
355 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Processing group '{}':'{}' gd={}", root->type,root->name,(void*)gd);
356
357 if (gd)
358 {
359 if ( !gd->hasGroupTitle() )
360 {
361 gd->setGroupTitle( root->type );
362 }
363 else if ( root->type.length() > 0 && root->name != root->type && gd->groupTitle() != root->type )
364 {
365 warn( root->fileName,root->startLine,
366 "group %s: ignoring title \"%s\" that does not match old title \"%s\"",
367 qPrint(root->name), qPrint(root->type), qPrint(gd->groupTitle()) );
368 }
369 gd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
370 gd->setDocumentation( root->doc, root->docFile, root->docLine );
371 gd->setInbodyDocumentation( root->inbodyDocs, root->inbodyFile, root->inbodyLine );
372 gd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
373 gd->setRefItems(root->sli);
374 gd->setLanguage(root->lang);
375 if (root->groupDocType==Entry::GROUPDOC_NORMAL)
376 {
377 root->commandOverrides.apply_groupGraph([&](bool b) { gd->overrideGroupGraph(b); });
378 }
379 }
380 else
381 {
382 if (root->tagInfo())
383 {
384 gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->add(root->name,
385 std::unique_ptr<GroupDef>(
386 createGroupDef(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->name,root->type,root->tagInfo()->fileName)));
387 gd->setReference(root->tagInfo()->tagName);
388 }
389 else
390 {
391 gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->add(root->name,
392 std::unique_ptr<GroupDef>(
393 createGroupDef(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->name,root->type)));
394 }
395 gd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
396 // allow empty docs for group
397 gd->setDocumentation(!root->doc.isEmpty() ? root->doc : QCString(" "),root->docFile,root->docLine,FALSE);
398 gd->setInbodyDocumentation( root->inbodyDocs, root->inbodyFile, root->inbodyLine );
399 gd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
400 gd->setRefItems(root->sli);
401 gd->setLanguage(root->lang);
402 if (root->groupDocType==Entry::GROUPDOC_NORMAL)
403 {
404 root->commandOverrides.apply_groupGraph([&](bool b) { gd->overrideGroupGraph(b); });
405 }
406 }
407 }
408 }
409 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildGroupListFiltered(e.get(),additional,includeExternal);
410}
411
412static void buildGroupList(const Entry *root)
413{
414 // --- first process only local groups
415 // first process the @defgroups blocks
416 buildGroupListFiltered(root,FALSE,FALSE);
417 // then process the @addtogroup, @weakgroup blocks
418 buildGroupListFiltered(root,TRUE,FALSE);
419
420 // --- then also process external groups
421 // first process the @defgroups blocks
422 buildGroupListFiltered(root,FALSE,TRUE);
423 // then process the @addtogroup, @weakgroup blocks
424 buildGroupListFiltered(root,TRUE,TRUE);
425}
426
427static void findGroupScope(const Entry *root)
428{
429 if (root->section.isGroupDoc() && !root->name.isEmpty() &&
430 root->parent() && !root->parent()->name.isEmpty())
431 {
432 GroupDef *gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(root->name);
433 if (gd)
434 {
435 QCString scope = root->parent()->name;
436 if (root->parent()->section.isPackageDoc())
437 {
438 scope=substitute(scope,".","::");
439 }
440 scope = stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(scope);
441 scope+="::"+gd->name();
442 Definition *d = findScopeFromQualifiedName(Doxygen::globalScope,scope,nullptr,root->tagInfo());
443 if (d)
444 {
445 gd->setGroupScope(d);
446 }
447 }
448 }
449 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findGroupScope(e.get());
450}
451
452static void organizeSubGroupsFiltered(const Entry *root,bool additional)
453{
454 if (root->section.isGroupDoc() && !root->name.isEmpty())
455 {
456 AUTO_TRACE("additional={}",additional);
457 if ((root->groupDocType==Entry::GROUPDOC_NORMAL && !additional) ||
458 (root->groupDocType!=Entry::GROUPDOC_NORMAL && additional))
459 {
460 GroupDef *gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(root->name);
461 if (gd)
462 {
463 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("adding {} to group {}",root->name,gd->name());
464 addGroupToGroups(root,gd);
465 }
466 }
467 }
468 for (const auto &e : root->children()) organizeSubGroupsFiltered(e.get(),additional);
469}
470
471static void organizeSubGroups(const Entry *root)
472{
473 //printf("Defining groups\n");
474 // first process the @defgroups blocks
475 organizeSubGroupsFiltered(root,FALSE);
476 //printf("Additional groups\n");
477 // then process the @addtogroup, @weakgroup blocks
478 organizeSubGroupsFiltered(root,TRUE);
479}

482
483static void buildFileList(const Entry *root)
484{
485 if ((root->section.isFileDoc() || (root->section.isFile() && Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL))) &&
486 !root->name.isEmpty() && !root->tagInfo() // skip any file coming from tag files
487 )
488 {
489 bool ambig = false;
490 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,root->name,ambig);
491 if (!fd || ambig)
492 {
493 bool save_ambig = ambig;
494 // use the directory of the file to see if the described file is in the same
495 // directory as the describing file.
496 QCString fn = root->fileName;
497 int newIndex=fn.findRev('/');
498 if (newIndex<0)
499 {
500 fn = root->name;
501 }
502 else
503 {
504 fn = fn.left(newIndex)+"/"+root->name;
505 }
506 fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,fn,ambig);
507 if (!fd) ambig = save_ambig;
508 }
509 //printf("**************** root->name=%s fd=%p\n",qPrint(root->name),(void*)fd);
510 if (fd && !ambig)
511 {
512 //printf("Adding documentation!\n");
513 // using FALSE in setDocumentation is small hack to make sure a file
514 // is documented even if a \file command is used without further
515 // documentation
516 fd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine,FALSE);
517 fd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
518 fd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
519 fd->setRefItems(root->sli);
520 root->commandOverrides.apply_includeGraph ([&](bool b) { fd->overrideIncludeGraph(b); });
521 root->commandOverrides.apply_includedByGraph([&](bool b) { fd->overrideIncludedByGraph(b); });
522 for (const Grouping &g : root->groups)
523 {
524 GroupDef *gd=nullptr;
525 if (!g.groupname.isEmpty() && (gd=Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(g.groupname)))
526 {
527 if (!gd->containsFile(fd))
528 {
529 gd->addFile(fd);
530 fd->makePartOfGroup(gd);
531 //printf("File %s: in group %s\n",qPrint(fd->name()),qPrint(gd->name()));
532 }
533 }
534 else if (!gd && g.pri == Grouping::GROUPING_INGROUP)
535 {
536 warn(root->fileName, root->startLine,
537 "Found non-existing group '%s' for the command '%s', ignoring command",
538 qPrint(g.groupname), Grouping::getGroupPriName( g.pri )
539 );
540 }
541 }
542 }
543 else
544 {
545 QCString text(4096, QCString::ExplicitSize);
546 text.sprintf("the name '%s' supplied as "
547 "the argument in the \\file statement ",
548 qPrint(root->name));
549 if (ambig) // name is ambiguous
550 {
551 text+="matches the following input files:\n";
552 text+=showFileDefMatches(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,root->name);
553 text+="\n";
554 text+="Please use a more specific name by "
555 "including a (larger) part of the path!";
556 }
557 else // name is not an input file
558 {
559 text+="is not an input file";
560 }
561 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,"%s", qPrint(text));
562 }
563 }
564 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildFileList(e.get());
565}
566
567template<class DefMutable>
568static void addIncludeFile(DefMutable *cd,FileDef *ifd,const Entry *root)
569{
570 if (
571 (!root->doc.stripWhiteSpace().isEmpty() ||
572 !root->brief.stripWhiteSpace().isEmpty() ||
573 Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL)
574 ) && root->protection!=Protection::Private
575 )
576 {
577 //printf(">>>>>> includeFile=%s\n",qPrint(root->includeFile));
578
579 bool local=Config_getBool(FORCE_LOCAL_INCLUDES);
580 QCString includeFile = root->includeFile;
581 if (!includeFile.isEmpty() && includeFile.at(0)=='"')
582 {
583 local = TRUE;
584 includeFile=includeFile.mid(1,includeFile.length()-2);
585 }
586 else if (!includeFile.isEmpty() && includeFile.at(0)=='<')
587 {
588 local = FALSE;
589 includeFile=includeFile.mid(1,includeFile.length()-2);
590 }
591
592 bool ambig = false;
593 FileDef *fd=nullptr;
594 // see if we need to include a verbatim copy of the header file
595 //printf("root->includeFile=%s\n",qPrint(root->includeFile));
596 if (!includeFile.isEmpty() &&
597 (fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,includeFile,ambig))==nullptr
598 )
599 { // explicit request
600 QCString text;
601 text.sprintf("the name '%s' supplied as "
602 "the argument of the \\class, \\struct, \\union, or \\include command ",
603 qPrint(includeFile)
604 );
605 if (ambig) // name is ambiguous
606 {
607 text+="matches the following input files:\n";
608 text+=showFileDefMatches(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,root->includeFile);
609 text+="\n";
610 text+="Please use a more specific name by "
611 "including a (larger) part of the path!";
612 }
613 else // name is not an input file
614 {
615 text+="is not an input file";
616 }
617 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine, "%s", qPrint(text));
618 }
619 else if (includeFile.isEmpty() && ifd &&
620 // see if the file extension makes sense
621 guessSection(ifd->name()).isHeader())
622 { // implicit assumption
623 fd=ifd;
624 }
625
626 // if a file is found, we mark it as a source file.
627 if (fd)
628 {
629 QCString iName = !root->includeName.isEmpty() ?
630 root->includeName : includeFile;
631 if (!iName.isEmpty()) // user specified include file
632 {
633 if (iName.at(0)=='<') local=FALSE; // explicit override
634 else if (iName.at(0)=='"') local=TRUE;
635 if (iName.at(0)=='"' || iName.at(0)=='<')
636 {
637 iName=iName.mid(1,iName.length()-2); // strip quotes or brackets
638 }
639 if (iName.isEmpty())
640 {
641 iName=fd->name();
642 }
643 }
644 else if (!Config_getList(STRIP_FROM_INC_PATH).empty())
645 {
646 iName=stripFromIncludePath(fd->absFilePath());
647 }
648 else // use name of the file containing the class definition
649 {
650 iName=fd->name();
651 }
652 if (fd->generateSourceFile()) // generate code for header
653 {
654 cd->setIncludeFile(fd,iName,local,!root->includeName.isEmpty());
655 }
656 else // put #include in the class documentation without link
657 {
658 cd->setIncludeFile(nullptr,iName,local,TRUE);
659 }
660 }
661 }
662}
663
664
665QCString stripTemplateSpecifiers(const QCString &s)
666{
667 size_t l = s.length();
668 int count=0;
669 int round=0;
670 QCString result;
671 for (size_t i=0;i<l;i++)
672 {
673 char c=s.at(i);
674 if (c=='(') round++;
675 else if (c==')' && round>0) round--;
676 else if (c=='<' && round==0) count++;
677 if (count==0)
678 {
679 result+=c;
680 }
681 if (c=='>' && round==0 && count>0) count--;
682 }
683 //printf("stripTemplateSpecifiers(%s)=%s\n",qPrint(s),qPrint(result));
684 return result;
685}
686
687/*! returns the Definition object belonging to the first \a level levels of
688 * full qualified name \a name. Creates an artificial scope if the scope is
689 * not found and set the parent/child scope relation if the scope is found.
690 */
691[[maybe_unused]]
692static Definition *buildScopeFromQualifiedName(const QCString &name_,SrcLangExt lang,const TagInfo *tagInfo)
693{
694 QCString name = stripTemplateSpecifiers(name_);
695 name.stripPrefix("::");
696 int level = name.contains("::");
697 //printf("buildScopeFromQualifiedName(%s) level=%d\n",qPrint(name),level);
698 int i=0, p=0, l=0;
699 Definition *prevScope=Doxygen::globalScope;
700 QCString fullScope;
701 while (i<level)
702 {
703 int idx=getScopeFragment(name,p,&l);
704 if (idx==-1) return prevScope;
705 QCString nsName = name.mid(idx,l);
706 if (nsName.isEmpty()) return prevScope;
707 if (!fullScope.isEmpty()) fullScope+="::";
708 fullScope+=nsName;
709 NamespaceDef *nd=Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(fullScope);
710 DefinitionMutable *innerScope = toDefinitionMutable(nd);
711 ClassDef *cd=nullptr;
712 if (nd==nullptr) cd = getClass(fullScope);
713 if (nd==nullptr && cd) // scope is a class
714 {
715 innerScope = toDefinitionMutable(cd);
716 }
717 else if (nd==nullptr && cd==nullptr && fullScope.find('<')==-1) // scope is not known and could be a namespace!
718 {
719 // introduce bogus namespace
720 //printf("++ adding dummy namespace %s to %s tagInfo=%p\n",qPrint(nsName),qPrint(prevScope->name()),(void*)tagInfo);
721 NamespaceDefMutable *newNd=
722 toNamespaceDefMutable(
723 Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->add(fullScope,
724 createNamespaceDef(
725 "[generated]",1,1,fullScope,
726 tagInfo?tagInfo->tagName:QCString(),
727 tagInfo?tagInfo->fileName:QCString())));
728 if (newNd)
729 {
730 newNd->setLanguage(lang);
731 newNd->setArtificial(TRUE);
732 // add namespace to the list
733 innerScope = newNd;
734 }
735 }
736 else // scope is a namespace
737 {
738 }
739 if (innerScope)
740 {
741 // make the parent/child scope relation
742 DefinitionMutable *prevScopeMutable = toDefinitionMutable(prevScope);
743 if (prevScopeMutable)
744 {
745 prevScopeMutable->addInnerCompound(toDefinition(innerScope));
746 }
747 innerScope->setOuterScope(prevScope);
748 }
749 else // current scope is a class, so return only the namespace part...
750 {
751 return prevScope;
752 }
753 // proceed to the next scope fragment
754 p=idx+l+2;
755 prevScope=toDefinition(innerScope);
756 i++;
757 }
758 return prevScope;
759}
760
761static Definition *findScopeFromQualifiedName(NamespaceDefMutable *startScope,const QCString &n,
762 FileDef *fileScope,const TagInfo *tagInfo)
763{
764 //printf("<findScopeFromQualifiedName(%s,%s)\n",startScope ? qPrint(startScope->name()) : 0, qPrint(n));
765 Definition *resultScope=toDefinition(startScope);
766 if (resultScope==nullptr) resultScope=Doxygen::globalScope;
767 QCString scope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(n,FALSE);
768 int l1 = 0;
769 int i1 = getScopeFragment(scope,0,&l1);
770 if (i1==-1)
771 {
772 //printf(">no fragments!\n");
773 return resultScope;
774 }
775 int p=i1+l1,l2=0,i2=0;
776 while ((i2=getScopeFragment(scope,p,&l2))!=-1)
777 {
778 QCString nestedNameSpecifier = scope.mid(i1,l1);
779 Definition *orgScope = resultScope;
780 //printf(" nestedNameSpecifier=%s\n",qPrint(nestedNameSpecifier));
781 resultScope = const_cast<Definition*>(resultScope->findInnerCompound(nestedNameSpecifier));
782 //printf(" resultScope=%p\n",resultScope);
783 if (resultScope==nullptr)
784 {
785 if (orgScope==Doxygen::globalScope && fileScope && !fileScope->getUsedNamespaces().empty())
786 // also search for used namespaces
787 {
788 for (const auto &nd : fileScope->getUsedNamespaces())
789 {
790 NamespaceDef *mnd = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd);
791 if (mnd)
792 {
793 resultScope = findScopeFromQualifiedName(toNamespaceDefMutable(nd),n,fileScope,tagInfo);
794 if (resultScope!=nullptr) break;
795 }
796 }
797 if (resultScope)
798 {
799 // for a nested class A::I in used namespace N, we get
800 // N::A::I while looking for A, so we should compare
801 // resultScope->name() against scope.left(i2+l2)
802 //printf(" -> result=%s scope=%s\n",qPrint(resultScope->name()),qPrint(scope));
803 if (rightScopeMatch(resultScope->name(),scope.left(i2+l2)))
804 {
805 break;
806 }
807 goto nextFragment;
808 }
809 }
810
811 // also search for used classes. Complication: we haven't been able
812 // to put them in the right scope yet, because we are still resolving
813 // the scope relations!
814 // Therefore loop through all used classes and see if there is a right
815 // scope match between the used class and nestedNameSpecifier.
816 for (const auto &usedName : g_usingDeclarations)
817 {
818 //printf("Checking using class %s\n",usedName.c_str());
819 if (rightScopeMatch(usedName.c_str(),nestedNameSpecifier))
820 {
821 // ui.currentKey() is the fully qualified name of nestedNameSpecifier
822 // so use this instead.
823 QCString fqn = QCString(usedName) + scope.right(scope.length()-p);
824 resultScope = buildScopeFromQualifiedName(fqn,startScope->getLanguage(),nullptr);
825 //printf("Creating scope from fqn=%s result %p\n",qPrint(fqn),resultScope);
826 if (resultScope)
827 {
828 //printf("> Match! resultScope=%s\n",qPrint(resultScope->name()));
829 return resultScope;
830 }
831 }
832 }
833
834 //printf("> name %s not found in scope %s\n",qPrint(nestedNameSpecifier),qPrint(orgScope->name()));
835 return nullptr;
836 }
837 nextFragment:
838 i1=i2;
839 l1=l2;
840 p=i2+l2;
841 }
842 //printf(">findScopeFromQualifiedName scope %s\n",qPrint(resultScope->name()));
843 return resultScope;
844}
845
846std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> getTemplateArgumentsFromName(
847 const QCString &name,
848 const ArgumentLists &tArgLists)
849{
850 // for each scope fragment, check if it is a template and advance through
851 // the list if so.
852 int i=0, p=0;
853 auto alIt = tArgLists.begin();
854 while ((i=name.find("::",p))!=-1 && alIt!=tArgLists.end())
855 {
856 NamespaceDef *nd = Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(name.left(i));
857 if (nd==nullptr)
858 {
859 ClassDef *cd = getClass(name.left(i));
860 if (cd)
861 {
862 if (!cd->templateArguments().empty())
863 {
864 ++alIt;
865 }
866 }
867 }
868 p=i+2;
869 }
870 return alIt!=tArgLists.end() ?
871 std::make_unique<ArgumentList>(*alIt) :
872 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList>();
873}
874
875static
876ClassDef::CompoundType convertToCompoundType(EntryType section,TypeSpecifier specifier)
877{
878 ClassDef::CompoundType sec=ClassDef::Class;
879
880 if (specifier.isStruct())
881 sec=ClassDef::Struct;
882 else if (specifier.isUnion())
883 sec=ClassDef::Union;
884 else if (specifier.isCategory())
885 sec=ClassDef::Category;
886 else if (specifier.isInterface())
887 sec=ClassDef::Interface;
888 else if (specifier.isProtocol())
889 sec=ClassDef::Protocol;
890 else if (specifier.isException())
891 sec=ClassDef::Exception;
892 else if (specifier.isService())
893 sec=ClassDef::Service;
894 else if (specifier.isSingleton())
895 sec=ClassDef::Singleton;
896
897 if (section.isUnionDoc())
898 sec=ClassDef::Union;
899 else if (section.isStructDoc())
900 sec=ClassDef::Struct;
901 else if (section.isInterfaceDoc())
902 sec=ClassDef::Interface;
903 else if (section.isProtocolDoc())
904 sec=ClassDef::Protocol;
905 else if (section.isCategoryDoc())
906 sec=ClassDef::Category;
907 else if (section.isExceptionDoc())
908 sec=ClassDef::Exception;
909 else if (section.isServiceDoc())
910 sec=ClassDef::Service;
911 else if (section.isSingletonDoc())
912 sec=ClassDef::Singleton;
913
914 return sec;
915}
916
917
918static void addClassToContext(const Entry *root)
919{
920 AUTO_TRACE("name={}",root->name);
921 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
922
923 QCString scName;
924 if (root->parent()->section.isScope())
925 {
926 scName=root->parent()->name;
927 }
928 // name without parent's scope
929 QCString fullName = root->name;
930
931 // strip off any template parameters (but not those for specializations)
932 fullName=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(fullName);
933
934 // name with scope (if not present already)
935 QCString qualifiedName = fullName;
936 if (!scName.isEmpty() && !leftScopeMatch(fullName,scName))
937 {
938 qualifiedName.prepend(scName+"::");
939 }
940
941 // see if we already found the class before
942 ClassDefMutable *cd = getClassMutable(qualifiedName);
943
944 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Found class with name '{}', qualifiedName '{}'", cd ? cd->name() : root->name, qualifiedName);
945
946 if (cd)
947 {
948 fullName=cd->name();
949 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Existing class '{}'",cd->name());
950 //if (cd->templateArguments()==0)
951 //{
952 // //printf("existing ClassDef tempArgList=%p specScope=%s\n",root->tArgList,qPrint(root->scopeSpec));
953 // cd->setTemplateArguments(tArgList);
954 //}
955
956 cd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
957 cd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
958 root->commandOverrides.apply_collaborationGraph([&](bool b ) { cd->overrideCollaborationGraph(b); });
959 root->commandOverrides.apply_inheritanceGraph ([&](CLASS_GRAPH_t gt) { cd->overrideInheritanceGraph(gt); });
960
961 if (!root->spec.isForwardDecl() && cd->isForwardDeclared())
962 {
963 cd->setDefFile(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
964 if (root->bodyLine!=-1)
965 {
966 cd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
967 cd->setBodyDef(fd);
968 }
969 }
970
971 if (cd->templateArguments().empty() || (cd->isForwardDeclared() && !root->spec.isForwardDecl()))
972 {
973 // this happens if a template class declared with @class is found
974 // before the actual definition or if a forward declaration has different template
975 // parameter names.
976 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> tArgList = getTemplateArgumentsFromName(cd->name(),root->tArgLists);
977 if (tArgList)
978 {
979 cd->setTemplateArguments(*tArgList);
980 }
981 }
982 if (cd->requiresClause().isEmpty() && !root->req.isEmpty())
983 {
984 cd->setRequiresClause(root->req);
985 }
986
987 cd->setCompoundType(convertToCompoundType(root->section,root->spec));
988
989 cd->setMetaData(root->metaData);
990 }
991 else // new class
992 {
993 ClassDef::CompoundType sec = convertToCompoundType(root->section,root->spec);
994
995 QCString className;
996 QCString namespaceName;
997 extractNamespaceName(fullName,className,namespaceName);
998
999 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New class: fullname '{}' namespace '{}' name='{}' brief='{}' docs='{}'",
1000 fullName, namespaceName, className, Trace::trunc(root->brief), Trace::trunc(root->doc));
1001
1002 QCString tagName;
1003 QCString refFileName;
1004 const TagInfo *tagInfo = root->tagInfo();
1005 if (tagInfo)
1006 {
1007 tagName = tagInfo->tagName;
1008 refFileName = tagInfo->fileName;
1009 if (fullName.find("::")!=-1)
1010 // symbols imported via tag files may come without the parent scope,
1011 // so we artificially create it here
1012 {
1013 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(fullName,root->lang,tagInfo);
1014 }
1015 }
1016 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> tArgList;
1017 int i=0;
1018 if ((root->lang==SrcLangExt::CSharp || root->lang==SrcLangExt::Java) && (i=fullName.findRev('<'))!=-1)
1019 {
1020 // a Java/C# generic class looks like a C++ specialization, so we need to split the
1021 // name and template arguments here
1022 tArgList = stringToArgumentList(root->lang,fullName.mid(i));
1023 fullName=fullName.left(i);
1024 }
1025 else
1026 {
1027 tArgList = getTemplateArgumentsFromName(fullName,root->tArgLists);
1028 }
1029 // add class to the list
1030 cd = toClassDefMutable(
1031 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(fullName,
1032 createClassDef(tagInfo?tagName:root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
1033 fullName,sec,tagName,refFileName,TRUE,root->spec.isEnum()) ));
1034 if (cd)
1035 {
1036 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New class '{}' type={} #tArgLists={} tagInfo={} hidden={} artificial={}",
1037 fullName,cd->compoundTypeString(),root->tArgLists.size(),
1038 fmt::ptr(tagInfo),root->hidden,root->artificial);
1039 cd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine); // copy docs to definition
1040 cd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1041 cd->setLanguage(root->lang);
1042 cd->setId(root->id);
1043 cd->setHidden(root->hidden);
1044 cd->setArtificial(root->artificial);
1045 cd->setClassSpecifier(root->spec);
1046 cd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
1047 cd->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
1048 root->commandOverrides.apply_collaborationGraph([&](bool b ) { cd->overrideCollaborationGraph(b); });
1049 root->commandOverrides.apply_inheritanceGraph ([&](CLASS_GRAPH_t gt) { cd->overrideInheritanceGraph(gt); });
1050
1051 if (tArgList)
1052 {
1053 cd->setTemplateArguments(*tArgList);
1054 }
1055 cd->setRequiresClause(root->req);
1056 cd->setProtection(root->protection);
1057 cd->setIsStatic(root->isStatic);
1058
1059 // file definition containing the class cd
1060 cd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
1061 cd->setBodyDef(fd);
1062
1063 cd->setMetaData(root->metaData);
1064
1065 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
1066 }
1067 else
1068 {
1069 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Class {} not added, already exists as alias", fullName);
1070 }
1071 }
1072
1073 if (cd)
1074 {
1075 cd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
1076 if (!root->subGrouping) cd->setSubGrouping(FALSE);
1077 if (!root->spec.isForwardDecl())
1078 {
1079 if (cd->hasDocumentation())
1080 {
1081 addIncludeFile(cd,fd,root);
1082 }
1083 if (fd && root->section.isCompound())
1084 {
1085 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Inserting class {} in file {} (root->fileName='{}')", cd->name(), fd->name(), root->fileName);
1086 cd->setFileDef(fd);
1087 fd->insertClass(cd);
1088 }
1089 }
1090 addClassToGroups(root,cd);
1091 ModuleManager::instance().addClassToModule(root,cd);
1092 cd->setRefItems(root->sli);
1093 }
1094}
1095
1096//----------------------------------------------------------------------
1097// build a list of all classes mentioned in the documentation
1098// and all classes that have a documentation block before their definition.
1099static void buildClassList(const Entry *root)
1100{
1101 if ((root->section.isCompound() || root->section.isObjcImpl()) && !root->name.isEmpty())
1102 {
1103 AUTO_TRACE();
1104 addClassToContext(root);
1105 }
1106 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildClassList(e.get());
1107}
1108
1109static void buildClassDocList(const Entry *root)
1110{
1111 if ((root->section.isCompoundDoc()) && !root->name.isEmpty())
1112 {
1113 AUTO_TRACE();
1114 addClassToContext(root);
1115 }
1116 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildClassDocList(e.get());
1117}
1118
1119//----------------------------------------------------------------------
1120// build a list of all classes mentioned in the documentation
1121// and all classes that have a documentation block before their definition.
1122
1123static void addConceptToContext(const Entry *root)
1124{
1125 AUTO_TRACE();
1126 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
1127
1128 QCString scName;
1129 if (root->parent()->section.isScope())
1130 {
1131 scName=root->parent()->name;
1132 }
1133
1134 // name with scope (if not present already)
1135 QCString qualifiedName = root->name;
1136 if (!scName.isEmpty() && !leftScopeMatch(qualifiedName,scName))
1137 {
1138 qualifiedName.prepend(scName+"::");
1139 }
1140
1141 // see if we already found the concept before
1142 ConceptDefMutable *cd = getConceptMutable(qualifiedName);
1143
1144 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Found concept with name '{}' (qualifiedName='{}')", cd ? cd->name() : root->name, qualifiedName);
1145
1146 if (cd)
1147 {
1148 qualifiedName=cd->name();
1149 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Existing concept '{}'",cd->name());
1150
1151 cd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
1152 cd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1153
1154 addIncludeFile(cd,fd,root);
1155 }
1156 else // new concept
1157 {
1158 QCString className;
1159 QCString namespaceName;
1160 extractNamespaceName(qualifiedName,className,namespaceName);
1161
1162 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New concept: fullname '{}' namespace '{}' name='{}' brief='{}' docs='{}'",
1163 qualifiedName,namespaceName,className,root->brief,root->doc);
1164
1165 QCString tagName;
1166 QCString refFileName;
1167 const TagInfo *tagInfo = root->tagInfo();
1168 if (tagInfo)
1169 {
1170 tagName = tagInfo->tagName;
1171 refFileName = tagInfo->fileName;
1172 if (qualifiedName.find("::")!=-1)
1173 // symbols imported via tag files may come without the parent scope,
1174 // so we artificially create it here
1175 {
1176 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(qualifiedName,root->lang,tagInfo);
1177 }
1178 }
1179 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> tArgList = getTemplateArgumentsFromName(qualifiedName,root->tArgLists);
1180 // add concept to the list
1181 cd = toConceptDefMutable(
1182 Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap->add(qualifiedName,
1183 createConceptDef(tagInfo?tagName:root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
1184 qualifiedName,tagName,refFileName)));
1185 if (cd)
1186 {
1187 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New concept '{}' #tArgLists={} tagInfo={}",
1188 qualifiedName,root->tArgLists.size(),fmt::ptr(tagInfo));
1189 cd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine); // copy docs to definition
1190 cd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1191 cd->setLanguage(root->lang);
1192 cd->setId(root->id);
1193 cd->setHidden(root->hidden);
1194 cd->setGroupId(root->mGrpId);
1195 if (tArgList)
1196 {
1197 cd->setTemplateArguments(*tArgList);
1198 }
1199 cd->setInitializer(root->initializer.str().c_str());
1200 // file definition containing the class cd
1201 cd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
1202 cd->setBodyDef(fd);
1203 addIncludeFile(cd,fd,root);
1204
1205 // also add namespace to the correct structural context
1206 Definition *d = findScopeFromQualifiedName(Doxygen::globalScope,qualifiedName,nullptr,tagInfo);
1207 if (d && d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1208 {
1209 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1210 if (dm)
1211 {
1212 dm->addInnerCompound(cd);
1213 }
1214 cd->setOuterScope(d);
1215 }
1216 }
1217 else
1218 {
1219 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Concept '{}' not added, already exists (as alias)", qualifiedName);
1220 }
1221 }
1222
1223 if (cd)
1224 {
1225 cd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
1226 if (fd)
1227 {
1228 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Inserting concept '{}' in file '{}' (root->fileName='{}')", cd->name(), fd->name(), root->fileName);
1229 cd->setFileDef(fd);
1230 fd->insertConcept(cd);
1231 }
1232 addConceptToGroups(root,cd);
1233 ModuleManager::instance().addConceptToModule(root,cd);
1234 cd->setRefItems(root->sli);
1235 }
1236}

1238static void findModuleDocumentation(const Entry *root)
1239{
1240 if (root->section.isModuleDoc())
1241 {
1242 AUTO_TRACE();
1243 ModuleManager::instance().addDocs(root);
1244 }
1245 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findModuleDocumentation(e.get());
1246}
1247
1248static void buildConceptList(const Entry *root)
1249{
1250 if (root->section.isConcept())
1251 {
1252 AUTO_TRACE();
1253 addConceptToContext(root);
1254 }
1255 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildConceptList(e.get());
1256}
1257
1258static void buildConceptDocList(const Entry *root)
1259{
1260 if (root->section.isConceptDoc())
1261 {
1262 AUTO_TRACE();
1263 addConceptToContext(root);
1264 }
1265 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildConceptDocList(e.get());
1266}
1267
1268// This routine is to allow @ingroup X @{ concept A; concept B; @} to work
1269// (same also works for variable and functions because of logic in MemberGroup::insertMember)
1270static void distributeConceptGroups()
1271{
1272 AUTO_TRACE();
1273 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap)
1274 {
1275 if (cd->groupId()!=DOX_NOGROUP)
1276 {
1277 for (const auto &ocd : *Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap)
1278 {
1279 if (cd!=ocd && cd->groupId()==ocd->groupId() &&
1280 !cd->partOfGroups().empty() && ocd->partOfGroups().empty())
1281 {
1282 ConceptDefMutable *ocdm = toConceptDefMutable(ocd.get());
1283 if (ocdm)
1284 {
1285 for (const auto &gd : cd->partOfGroups())
1286 {
1287 if (gd)
1288 {
1289 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("making concept '{}' part of group '{}'",ocdm->name(),gd->name());
1290 ocdm->makePartOfGroup(gd);
1291 gd->addConcept(ocd.get());
1292 }
1293 }
1294 }
1295 }
1296 }
1297 }
1298 }
1299}
1300
1301//----------------------------------------------------------------------
1302
1303static void resolveClassNestingRelations()
1304{
1305 ClassDefSet visitedClasses;
1306
1307 bool done=FALSE;
1308 //int iteration=0;
1309 while (!done)
1310 {
1311 done=TRUE;
1312 //++iteration;
1313 struct ClassAlias
1314 {
1315 ClassAlias(const QCString &name,std::unique_ptr<ClassDef> cd,DefinitionMutable *ctx) :
1316 aliasFullName(name),aliasCd(std::move(cd)), aliasContext(ctx) {}
1317 QCString aliasFullName;
1318 std::unique_ptr<ClassDef> aliasCd;
1319 DefinitionMutable *aliasContext;
1320 };
1321 std::vector<ClassAlias> aliases;
1322 for (const auto &icd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
1323 {
1324 ClassDefMutable *cd = toClassDefMutable(icd.get());
1325 if (cd && visitedClasses.find(icd.get())==visitedClasses.end())
1326 {
1327 QCString name = stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(icd->name());
1328 //printf("processing=%s, iteration=%d\n",qPrint(cd->name()),iteration);
1329 // also add class to the correct structural context
1330 Definition *d = findScopeFromQualifiedName(Doxygen::globalScope,
1331 name,icd->getFileDef(),nullptr);
1332 if (d)
1333 {
1334 //printf("****** adding %s to scope %s in iteration %d\n",qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(d->name()),iteration);
1335 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1336 if (dm)
1337 {
1338 dm->addInnerCompound(cd);
1339 }
1340 cd->setOuterScope(d);
1341
1342 // for inline namespace add an alias of the class to the outer scope
1343 while (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1344 {
1345 NamespaceDef *nd = toNamespaceDef(d);
1346 //printf("nd->isInline()=%d\n",nd->isInline());
1347 if (nd && nd->isInline())
1348 {
1349 d = d->getOuterScope();
1350 if (d)
1351 {
1352 dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1353 if (dm)
1354 {
1355 auto aliasCd = createClassDefAlias(d,cd);
1356 QCString aliasFullName = d->qualifiedName()+"::"+aliasCd->localName();
1357 aliases.emplace_back(aliasFullName,std::move(aliasCd),dm);
1358 //printf("adding %s to %s as %s\n",qPrint(aliasCd->name()),qPrint(d->name()),qPrint(aliasFullName));
1359 }
1360 }
1361 }
1362 else
1363 {
1364 break;
1365 }
1366 }
1367
1368 visitedClasses.insert(icd.get());
1369 done=FALSE;
1370 }
1371 //else
1372 //{
1373 // printf("****** ignoring %s: scope not (yet) found in iteration %d\n",qPrint(cd->name()),iteration);
1374 //}
1375 }
1376 }
1377 // add aliases
1378 for (auto &alias : aliases)
1379 {
1380 ClassDef *aliasCd = Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(alias.aliasFullName,std::move(alias.aliasCd));
1381 if (aliasCd)
1382 {
1383 alias.aliasContext->addInnerCompound(aliasCd);
1384 }
1385 }
1386 }
1387
1388 //give warnings for unresolved compounds
1389 for (const auto &icd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
1390 {
1391 ClassDefMutable *cd = toClassDefMutable(icd.get());
1392 if (cd && visitedClasses.find(icd.get())==visitedClasses.end())
1393 {
1394 QCString name = stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(cd->name());
1395 //printf("processing unresolved=%s, iteration=%d\n",qPrint(cd->name()),iteration);
1396 /// create the scope artificially
1397 // anyway, so we can at least relate scopes properly.
1398 Definition *d = buildScopeFromQualifiedName(name,cd->getLanguage(),nullptr);
1399 if (d && d!=cd && !cd->getDefFileName().isEmpty())
1400 // avoid recursion in case of redundant scopes, i.e: namespace N { class N::C {}; }
1401 // for this case doxygen assumes the existence of a namespace N::N in which C is to be found!
1402 // also avoid warning for stuff imported via a tagfile.
1403 {
1404 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1405 if (dm)
1406 {
1407 dm->addInnerCompound(cd);
1408 }
1409 cd->setOuterScope(d);
1410 warn(cd->getDefFileName(),cd->getDefLine(),
1411 "Internal inconsistency: scope for class %s not "
1412 "found!",qPrint(name)
1413 );
1414 }
1415 }
1416 }
1417}
1418
1419void distributeClassGroupRelations()
1420{
1421 //bool inlineGroupedClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_GROUPED_CLASSES);
1422 //if (!inlineGroupedClasses) return;
1423 //printf("** distributeClassGroupRelations()\n");
1424
1425 ClassDefSet visitedClasses;
1426 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
1427 {
1428 //printf("Checking %s\n",qPrint(cd->name()));
1429 // distribute the group to nested classes as well
1430 if (visitedClasses.find(cd.get())==visitedClasses.end() && !cd->partOfGroups().empty())
1431 {
1432 //printf(" Candidate for merging\n");
1433 GroupDef *gd = cd->partOfGroups().front();
1434 for (auto &ncd : cd->getClasses())
1435 {
1436 ClassDefMutable *ncdm = toClassDefMutable(ncd);
1437 if (ncdm && ncdm->partOfGroups().empty())
1438 {
1439 //printf(" Adding %s to group '%s'\n",qPrint(ncd->name()),
1440 // gd->groupTitle());
1441 ncdm->makePartOfGroup(gd);
1442 gd->addClass(ncdm);
1443 }
1444 }
1445 visitedClasses.insert(cd.get()); // only visit every class once
1446 }
1447 }
1448}
1449
1450//----------------------------
1451
1452static ClassDefMutable *createTagLessInstance(const ClassDef *rootCd,const ClassDef *templ,const QCString &fieldName)
1453{
1454 QCString fullName = removeAnonymousScopes(templ->name());
1455 if (fullName.endsWith("::")) fullName=fullName.left(fullName.length()-2);
1456 fullName+="."+fieldName;
1457
1458 //printf("** adding class %s based on %s\n",qPrint(fullName),qPrint(templ->name()));
1459 ClassDefMutable *cd = toClassDefMutable(
1460 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(fullName,
1461 createClassDef(templ->getDefFileName(),
1462 templ->getDefLine(),
1463 templ->getDefColumn(),
1464 fullName,
1465 templ->compoundType())));
1466 if (cd)
1467 {
1468 cd->setDocumentation(templ->documentation(),templ->docFile(),templ->docLine()); // copy docs to definition
1469 cd->setBriefDescription(templ->briefDescription(),templ->briefFile(),templ->briefLine());
1470 cd->setLanguage(templ->getLanguage());
1471 cd->setBodySegment(templ->getDefLine(),templ->getStartBodyLine(),templ->getEndBodyLine());
1472 cd->setBodyDef(templ->getBodyDef());
1473
1474 cd->setOuterScope(rootCd->getOuterScope());
1475 if (rootCd->getOuterScope()!=Doxygen::globalScope)
1476 {
1477 DefinitionMutable *outerScope = toDefinitionMutable(rootCd->getOuterScope());
1478 if (outerScope)
1479 {
1480 outerScope->addInnerCompound(cd);
1481 }
1482 }
1483
1484 FileDef *fd = templ->getFileDef();
1485 if (fd)
1486 {
1487 cd->setFileDef(fd);
1488 fd->insertClass(cd);
1489 }
1490 for (auto &gd : rootCd->partOfGroups())
1491 {
1492 cd->makePartOfGroup(gd);
1493 gd->addClass(cd);
1494 }
1495
1496 MemberList *ml = templ->getMemberList(MemberListType::PubAttribs());
1497 if (ml)
1498 {
1499 for (const auto &md : *ml)
1500 {
1501 //printf(" Member %s type=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()),md->typeString());
1502 auto newMd = createMemberDef(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine(),md->getDefColumn(),
1503 md->typeString(),md->name(),md->argsString(),md->excpString(),
1504 md->protection(),md->virtualness(),md->isStatic(),Relationship::Member,
1505 md->memberType(),
1506 ArgumentList(),ArgumentList(),"");
1507 MemberDefMutable *imd = toMemberDefMutable(newMd.get());
1508 imd->setMemberClass(cd);
1509 imd->setDocumentation(md->documentation(),md->docFile(),md->docLine());
1510 imd->setBriefDescription(md->briefDescription(),md->briefFile(),md->briefLine());
1511 imd->setInbodyDocumentation(md->inbodyDocumentation(),md->inbodyFile(),md->inbodyLine());
1512 imd->setMemberSpecifiers(md->getMemberSpecifiers());
1513 imd->setVhdlSpecifiers(md->getVhdlSpecifiers());
1514 imd->setMemberGroupId(md->getMemberGroupId());
1515 imd->setInitializer(md->initializer());
1516 imd->setRequiresClause(md->requiresClause());
1517 imd->setMaxInitLines(md->initializerLines());
1518 imd->setBitfields(md->bitfieldString());
1519 imd->setLanguage(md->getLanguage());
1520 cd->insertMember(imd);
1521 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(md->name());
1522 mn->push_back(std::move(newMd));
1523 }
1524 }
1525 }
1526 return cd;
1527}
1528
1529/** Look through the members of class \a cd and its public members.
1530 * If there is a member m of a tag less struct/union,
1531 * then we create a duplicate of the struct/union with the name of the
1532 * member to identify it.
1533 * So if cd has name S, then the tag less struct/union will get name S.m
1534 * Since tag less structs can be nested we need to call this function
1535 * recursively. Later on we need to patch the member types so we keep
1536 * track of the hierarchy of classes we create.
1537 */
1538static void processTagLessClasses(const ClassDef *rootCd,
1539 const ClassDef *cd,
1540 ClassDefMutable *tagParentCd,
1541 const QCString &prefix,int count)
1542{
1543 //printf("%d: processTagLessClasses %s\n",count,qPrint(cd->name()));
1544 //printf("checking members for %s\n",qPrint(cd->name()));
1545 if (tagParentCd && !cd->getClasses().empty())
1546 {
1547 MemberList *ml = cd->getMemberList(MemberListType::PubAttribs());
1548 if (ml)
1549 {
1550 int pos=0;
1551 for (const auto &md : *ml)
1552 {
1553 QCString type = md->typeString();
1554 if (type.find("::@")!=-1) // member of tag less struct/union
1555 {
1556 for (const auto &icd : cd->getClasses())
1557 {
1558 //printf(" member %s: type='%s'\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(type));
1559 //printf(" comparing '%s'<->'%s'\n",qPrint(type),qPrint(icd->name()));
1560 if (type.find(icd->name())!=-1) // matching tag less struct/union
1561 {
1562 QCString name = md->name();
1563 if (md->isAnonymous()) name = "__unnamed" + QCString().setNum(pos++)+"__";
1564 if (!prefix.isEmpty()) name.prepend(prefix+".");
1565 //printf(" found %s for class %s\n",qPrint(name),qPrint(cd->name()));
1566 ClassDefMutable *ncd = createTagLessInstance(rootCd,icd,name);
1567 if (ncd)
1568 {
1569 processTagLessClasses(rootCd,icd,ncd,name,count+1);
1570 //printf(" addTagged %s to %s\n",qPrint(ncd->name()),qPrint(tagParentCd->name()));
1571 ncd->setTagLessReference(icd);
1572
1573 // replace tag-less type for generated/original member
1574 // by newly created class name.
1575 // note the difference between changing cd and tagParentCd.
1576 // for the initial call this is the same pointer, but for
1577 // recursive calls cd is the original tag-less struct (of which
1578 // there is only one instance) and tagParentCd is the newly
1579 // generated tagged struct of which there can be multiple instances!
1580 MemberList *pml = tagParentCd->getMemberList(MemberListType::PubAttribs());
1581 if (pml)
1582 {
1583 for (const auto &pmd : *pml)
1584 {
1585 MemberDefMutable *pmdm = toMemberDefMutable(pmd);
1586 if (pmdm && pmd->name()==md->name())
1587 {
1588 pmdm->setAccessorType(ncd,substitute(pmd->typeString(),icd->name(),ncd->name()));
1589 //pmd->setType(substitute(pmd->typeString(),icd->name(),ncd->name()));
1590 }
1591 }
1592 }
1593 }
1594 }
1595 }
1596 }
1597 }
1598 }
1599 }
1600}
1601
1602static void findTagLessClasses(std::vector<ClassDefMutable*> &candidates,ClassDef *cd)
1603{
1604 for (const auto &icd : cd->getClasses())
1605 {
1606 if (icd->name().find("@")==-1) // process all non-anonymous inner classes
1607 {
1608 findTagLessClasses(candidates,icd);
1609 }
1610 }
1611
1612 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd);
1613 if (cdm)
1614 {
1615 candidates.push_back(cdm);
1616 }
1617}
1618
1619static void findTagLessClasses()
1620{
1621 std::vector<ClassDefMutable *> candidates;
1622 for (auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
1623 {
1624 Definition *scope = cd->getOuterScope();
1625 if (scope && scope->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeClass) // that is not nested
1626 {
1627 findTagLessClasses(candidates,cd.get());
1628 }
1629 }
1630
1631 // since processTagLessClasses is potentially adding classes to Doxygen::classLinkedMap
1632 // we need to call it outside of the loop above, otherwise the iterator gets invalidated!
1633 for (auto &cd : candidates)
1634 {
1635 processTagLessClasses(cd,cd,cd,"",0); // process tag less inner struct/classes
1636 }
1637}
1638
1639
1640//----------------------------------------------------------------------
1641// build a list of all namespaces mentioned in the documentation
1642// and all namespaces that have a documentation block before their definition.
1643static void buildNamespaceList(const Entry *root)
1644{
1645 if (
1646 (root->section.isNamespace() ||
1647 root->section.isNamespaceDoc() ||
1648 root->section.isPackageDoc()
1649 ) &&
1650 !root->name.isEmpty()
1651 )
1652 {
1653 AUTO_TRACE("name={}",root->name);
1654
1655 QCString fName = root->name;
1656 if (root->section.isPackageDoc())
1657 {
1658 fName=substitute(fName,".","::");
1659 }
1660
1661 QCString fullName = stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(fName);
1662 if (!fullName.isEmpty())
1663 {
1664 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Found namespace {} in {} at line {}",root->name,root->fileName,root->startLine);
1665 NamespaceDef *ndi = Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(fullName);
1666 if (ndi) // existing namespace
1667 {
1668 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = toNamespaceDefMutable(ndi);
1669 if (nd) // non-inline namespace
1670 {
1671 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Existing namespace");
1672 nd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
1673 nd->setName(fullName); // change name to match docs
1674 nd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
1675 nd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1676 if (nd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Unknown)
1677 {
1678 nd->setLanguage(root->lang);
1679 }
1680 if (root->tagInfo()==nullptr && nd->isReference() && !(root->doc.isEmpty() && root->brief.isEmpty()))
1681 // if we previously found namespace nd in a tag file and now we find a
1682 // documented namespace with the same name in the project, then remove
1683 // the tag file reference
1684 {
1685 nd->setReference("");
1686 nd->setFileName(fullName);
1687 }
1688 nd->setMetaData(root->metaData);
1689
1690 // file definition containing the namespace nd
1691 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
1692 if (nd->isArtificial())
1693 {
1694 nd->setArtificial(FALSE); // found namespace explicitly, so cannot be artificial
1695 nd->setDefFile(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
1696 }
1697 // insert the namespace in the file definition
1698 if (fd) fd->insertNamespace(nd);
1699 addNamespaceToGroups(root,nd);
1700 nd->setRefItems(root->sli);
1701 }
1702 }
1703 else // fresh namespace
1704 {
1705 QCString tagName;
1706 QCString tagFileName;
1707 const TagInfo *tagInfo = root->tagInfo();
1708 if (tagInfo)
1709 {
1710 tagName = tagInfo->tagName;
1711 tagFileName = tagInfo->fileName;
1712 }
1713 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("new namespace {} lang={} tagName={}",fullName,langToString(root->lang),tagName);
1714 // add namespace to the list
1715 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = toNamespaceDefMutable(
1716 Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->add(fullName,
1717 createNamespaceDef(tagInfo?tagName:root->fileName,root->startLine,
1718 root->startColumn,fullName,tagName,tagFileName,
1719 root->type,root->spec.isPublished())));
1720 if (nd)
1721 {
1722 nd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine); // copy docs to definition
1723 nd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1724 nd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
1725 nd->setHidden(root->hidden);
1726 nd->setArtificial(root->artificial);
1727 nd->setLanguage(root->lang);
1728 nd->setId(root->id);
1729 nd->setMetaData(root->metaData);
1730 nd->setInline(root->spec.isInline());
1731 nd->setExported(root->exported);
1732
1733 addNamespaceToGroups(root,nd);
1734 nd->setRefItems(root->sli);
1735
1736 // file definition containing the namespace nd
1737 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
1738 // insert the namespace in the file definition
1739 if (fd) fd->insertNamespace(nd);
1740
1741 // the empty string test is needed for extract all case
1742 nd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1743 nd->insertUsedFile(fd);
1744 nd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
1745 nd->setBodyDef(fd);
1746
1747 // also add namespace to the correct structural context
1748 Definition *d = findScopeFromQualifiedName(Doxygen::globalScope,fullName,nullptr,tagInfo);
1749 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("adding namespace {} to context {}",nd->name(),d ? d->name() : QCString("<none>"));
1750 if (d==nullptr) // we didn't find anything, create the scope artificially
1751 // anyway, so we can at least relate scopes properly.
1752 {
1753 d = buildScopeFromQualifiedName(fullName,nd->getLanguage(),tagInfo);
1754 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1755 if (dm)
1756 {
1757 dm->addInnerCompound(nd);
1758 }
1759 nd->setOuterScope(d);
1760 // TODO: Due to the order in which the tag file is written
1761 // a nested class can be found before its parent!
1762 }
1763 else
1764 {
1765 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1766 if (dm)
1767 {
1768 dm->addInnerCompound(nd);
1769 }
1770 nd->setOuterScope(d);
1771 // in case of d is an inline namespace, alias insert nd in the part scope of d.
1772 while (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1773 {
1774 NamespaceDef *pnd = toNamespaceDef(d);
1775 if (pnd && pnd->isInline())
1776 {
1777 d = d->getOuterScope();
1778 if (d)
1779 {
1780 dm = toDefinitionMutable(d);
1781 if (dm)
1782 {
1783 auto aliasNd = createNamespaceDefAlias(d,nd);
1784 dm->addInnerCompound(aliasNd.get());
1785 QCString aliasName = aliasNd->name();
1786 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("adding alias {} to {}",aliasName,d->name());
1787 Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->add(aliasName,std::move(aliasNd));
1788 }
1789 }
1790 else
1791 {
1792 break;
1793 }
1794 }
1795 else
1796 {
1797 break;
1798 }
1799 }
1800 }
1801 }
1802 }
1803 }
1804 }
1805 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildNamespaceList(e.get());
1806}
1807
1808//----------------------------------------------------------------------
1809
1810static NamespaceDef *findUsedNamespace(const LinkedRefMap<NamespaceDef> &unl,
1811 const QCString &name)
1812{
1813 NamespaceDef *usingNd =nullptr;
1814 for (auto &und : unl)
1815 {
1816 QCString uScope=und->name()+"::";
1817 usingNd = getResolvedNamespace(uScope+name);
1818 if (usingNd!=nullptr) break;
1819 }
1820 return usingNd;
1821}
1822
1823static void findUsingDirectives(const Entry *root)
1824{
1825 if (root->section.isUsingDir())
1826 {
1827 AUTO_TRACE("Found using directive {} at line {} of {}",root->name,root->startLine,root->fileName);
1828 QCString name=substitute(root->name,".","::");
1829 if (name.endsWith("::"))
1830 {
1831 name=name.left(name.length()-2);
1832 }
1833 if (!name.isEmpty())
1834 {
1835 NamespaceDef *usingNd = nullptr;
1836 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = nullptr;
1837 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
1838 QCString nsName;
1839
1840 // see if the using statement was found inside a namespace or inside
1841 // the global file scope.
1842 if (root->parent() && root->parent()->section.isNamespace() &&
1843 (fd==nullptr || fd->getLanguage()!=SrcLangExt::Java) // not a .java file
1844 )
1845 {
1846 nsName=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->parent()->name);
1847 if (!nsName.isEmpty())
1848 {
1849 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(nsName);
1850 }
1851 }
1852
1853 // find the scope in which the 'using' namespace is defined by prepending
1854 // the possible scopes in which the using statement was found, starting
1855 // with the most inner scope and going to the most outer scope (i.e.
1856 // file scope).
1857 int scopeOffset = static_cast<int>(nsName.length());
1858 do
1859 {
1860 QCString scope=scopeOffset>0 ?
1861 nsName.left(scopeOffset)+"::" : QCString();
1862 usingNd = getResolvedNamespace(scope+name);
1863 //printf("Trying with scope='%s' usingNd=%p\n",(scope+qPrint(name)),usingNd);
1864 if (scopeOffset==0)
1865 {
1866 scopeOffset=-1;
1867 }
1868 else if ((scopeOffset=nsName.findRev("::",scopeOffset-1))==-1)
1869 {
1870 scopeOffset=0;
1871 }
1872 } while (scopeOffset>=0 && usingNd==nullptr);
1873
1874 if (usingNd==nullptr && nd) // not found, try used namespaces in this scope
1875 // or in one of the parent namespace scopes
1876 {
1877 const NamespaceDefMutable *pnd = nd;
1878 while (pnd && usingNd==nullptr)
1879 {
1880 // also try with one of the used namespaces found earlier
1881 usingNd = toNamespaceDefMutable(findUsedNamespace(pnd->getUsedNamespaces(),name));
1882
1883 // goto the parent
1884 Definition *s = pnd->getOuterScope();
1885 if (s && s->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1886 {
1887 pnd = toNamespaceDefMutable(toNamespaceDef(s));
1888 }
1889 else
1890 {
1891 pnd = nullptr;
1892 }
1893 }
1894 }
1895 if (usingNd==nullptr && fd) // still nothing, also try used namespace in the
1896 // global scope
1897 {
1898 usingNd = findUsedNamespace(fd->getUsedNamespaces(),name);
1899 }
1900
1901 //printf("%s -> %s\n",qPrint(name),usingNd?qPrint(usingNd->name()):"<none>");
1902
1903 // add the namespace the correct scope
1904 if (usingNd)
1905 {
1906 //printf("using fd=%p nd=%p\n",fd,nd);
1907 if (nd)
1908 {
1909 //printf("Inside namespace %s\n",qPrint(nd->name()));
1910 nd->addUsingDirective(usingNd);
1911 }
1912 else if (fd)
1913 {
1914 //printf("Inside file %s\n",qPrint(fd->name()));
1915 fd->addUsingDirective(usingNd);
1916 }
1917 }
1918 else // unknown namespace, but add it anyway.
1919 {
1920 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("new unknown namespace {} lang={} hidden={}",name,langToString(root->lang),root->hidden);
1921 // add namespace to the list
1922 nd = toNamespaceDefMutable(
1923 Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->add(name,
1924 createNamespaceDef(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,name)));
1925 if (nd)
1926 {
1927 nd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine); // copy docs to definition
1928 nd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1929 nd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
1930 nd->setHidden(root->hidden);
1931 nd->setArtificial(TRUE);
1932 nd->setLanguage(root->lang);
1933 nd->setId(root->id);
1934 nd->setMetaData(root->metaData);
1935 nd->setInline(root->spec.isInline());
1936 nd->setExported(root->exported);
1937
1938 for (const Grouping &g : root->groups)
1939 {
1940 GroupDef *gd=nullptr;
1941 if (!g.groupname.isEmpty() && (gd=Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(g.groupname)))
1942 gd->addNamespace(nd);
1943 }
1944
1945 // insert the namespace in the file definition
1946 if (fd)
1947 {
1948 fd->insertNamespace(nd);
1949 fd->addUsingDirective(nd);
1950 }
1951
1952 // the empty string test is needed for extract all case
1953 nd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
1954 nd->insertUsedFile(fd);
1955 nd->setRefItems(root->sli);
1956 }
1957 }
1958 }
1959 }
1960 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findUsingDirectives(e.get());
1961}
1962
1963//----------------------------------------------------------------------
1964
1965static void buildListOfUsingDecls(const Entry *root)
1966{
1967 if (root->section.isUsingDecl() &&
1968 !root->parent()->section.isCompound() // not a class/struct member
1969 )
1970 {
1971 QCString name = substitute(root->name,".","::");
1972 g_usingDeclarations.insert(name.str());
1973 }
1974 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildListOfUsingDecls(e.get());
1975}
1976
1977
1978static void findUsingDeclarations(const Entry *root,bool filterPythonPackages)
1979{
1980 if (root->section.isUsingDecl() &&
1981 !root->parent()->section.isCompound() && // not a class/struct member
1982 (!filterPythonPackages || (root->lang==SrcLangExt::Python && root->fileName.endsWith("__init__.py")))
1983 )
1984 {
1985 AUTO_TRACE("Found using declaration '{}' at line {} of {} inside section {}",
1986 root->name,root->startLine,root->fileName,root->parent()->section);
1987 if (!root->name.isEmpty())
1988 {
1989 const Definition *usingDef = nullptr;
1990 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = nullptr;
1991 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
1992 QCString scName;
1993
1994 // see if the using statement was found inside a namespace or inside
1995 // the global file scope.
1996 if (root->parent()->section.isNamespace())
1997 {
1998 scName=root->parent()->name;
1999 if (!scName.isEmpty())
2000 {
2001 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scName);
2002 }
2003 }
2004
2005 // Assume the using statement was used to import a class.
2006 // Find the scope in which the 'using' namespace is defined by prepending
2007 // the possible scopes in which the using statement was found, starting
2008 // with the most inner scope and going to the most outer scope (i.e.
2009 // file scope).
2010
2011 QCString name = substitute(root->name,".","::"); //Java/C# scope->internal
2012
2013 SymbolResolver resolver;
2014 const Definition *scope = nd;
2015 if (nd==nullptr) scope = fd;
2016 usingDef = resolver.resolveSymbol(scope,name);
2017
2018 //printf("usingDef(scope=%s,name=%s)=%s\n",qPrint(nd?nd->qualifiedName():""),qPrint(name),usingDef?qPrint(usingDef->qualifiedName()):"nullptr");
2019
2020 if (!usingDef)
2021 {
2022 usingDef = getClass(name); // try direct lookup, this is needed to get
2023 // builtin STL classes to properly resolve, e.g.
2024 // vector -> std::vector
2025 }
2026 if (!usingDef)
2027 {
2028 usingDef = Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->find(name); // check if it is already hidden
2029 }
2030#if 0
2031 if (!usingDef)
2032 {
2033 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New using class '{}' (sec={})! #tArgLists={}",
2034 name,root->section,root->tArgLists.size());
2035 ClassDefMutable *usingCd = toClassDefMutable(
2036 Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->add(name,
2037 createClassDef( "<using>",1,1, name, ClassDef::Class)));
2038 if (usingCd)
2039 {
2040 usingCd->setArtificial(TRUE);
2041 usingCd->setLanguage(root->lang);
2042 usingDef = usingCd;
2043 }
2044 }
2045#endif
2046 else
2047 {
2048 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Found used type '{}' in scope='{}'",
2049 usingDef->name(), nd ? nd->name(): fd ? fd->name() : QCString("<unknown>"));
2050 }
2051
2052 if (usingDef)
2053 {
2054 if (nd)
2055 {
2056 nd->addUsingDeclaration(usingDef);
2057 }
2058 else if (fd)
2059 {
2060 fd->addUsingDeclaration(usingDef);
2061 }
2062 }
2063 }
2064 }
2065 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findUsingDeclarations(e.get(),filterPythonPackages);
2066}
2067
2068//----------------------------------------------------------------------
2069
2070static void applyMemberOverrideOptions(const Entry *root,MemberDefMutable *md)
2071{
2072 root->commandOverrides.apply_callGraph ([&](bool b) { md->overrideCallGraph(b); });
2073 root->commandOverrides.apply_callerGraph ([&](bool b) { md->overrideCallerGraph(b); });
2074 root->commandOverrides.apply_referencedByRelation([&](bool b) { md->overrideReferencedByRelation(b); });
2075 root->commandOverrides.apply_referencesRelation ([&](bool b) { md->overrideReferencesRelation(b); });
2076 root->commandOverrides.apply_inlineSource ([&](bool b) { md->overrideInlineSource(b); });
2077 root->commandOverrides.apply_enumValues ([&](bool b) { md->overrideEnumValues(b); });
2078}
2079
2080//----------------------------------------------------------------------
2081
2082static void findUsingDeclImports(const Entry *root)
2083{
2084 if (root->section.isUsingDecl() &&
2085 root->parent()->section.isCompound() // in a class/struct member
2086 )
2087 {
2088 AUTO_TRACE("Found using declaration '{}' inside section {}", root->name, root->parent()->section);
2089 QCString fullName=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->parent()->name);
2090 fullName=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(fullName);
2091 fullName=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(fullName);
2092 ClassDefMutable *cd = getClassMutable(fullName);
2093 if (cd)
2094 {
2095 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found class '{}'",cd->name());
2096 int i=root->name.findRev("::");
2097 if (i!=-1)
2098 {
2099 QCString scope=root->name.left(i);
2100 QCString memName=root->name.right(root->name.length()-i-2);
2101 SymbolResolver resolver;
2102 const ClassDef *bcd = resolver.resolveClass(cd,scope); // todo: file in fileScope parameter
2103 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("name={} scope={} bcd={}",scope,cd?cd->name():"<none>",bcd?bcd->name():"<none>");
2104 if (bcd && bcd!=cd)
2105 {
2106 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found class '{}' memName='{}'",bcd->name(),memName);
2107 const MemberNameInfoLinkedMap &mnlm=bcd->memberNameInfoLinkedMap();
2108 const MemberNameInfo *mni = mnlm.find(memName);
2109 if (mni)
2110 {
2111 for (auto &mi : *mni)
2112 {
2113 const MemberDef *md = mi->memberDef();
2114 if (md && md->protection()!=Protection::Private)
2115 {
2116 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found member '{}'",mni->memberName());
2117 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
2118 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
2119 {
2120 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
2121 }
2122 const ArgumentList &templAl = md->templateArguments();
2123 const ArgumentList &al = md->argumentList();
2124
2125 if (!cd->containsOverload(md))
2126 {
2127 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("creating new member {} for class {}",memName,cd->name());
2128 auto newMd = createMemberDef(
2129 fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
2130 md->typeString(),memName,md->argsString(),
2131 md->excpString(),root->protection,root->virt,
2132 md->isStatic(),Relationship::Member,md->memberType(),
2133 templAl,al,root->metaData
2134 );
2135 auto newMmd = toMemberDefMutable(newMd.get());
2136 newMmd->setMemberClass(cd);
2137 cd->insertMember(newMd.get());
2138 if (!root->doc.isEmpty() || !root->brief.isEmpty())
2139 {
2140 newMmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
2141 newMmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
2142 newMmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
2143 }
2144 else
2145 {
2146 newMmd->setDocumentation(md->documentation(),md->docFile(),md->docLine());
2147 newMmd->setBriefDescription(md->briefDescription(),md->briefFile(),md->briefLine());
2148 newMmd->setInbodyDocumentation(md->inbodyDocumentation(),md->inbodyFile(),md->inbodyLine());
2149 }
2150 newMmd->setDefinition(md->definition());
2151 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,newMmd);
2152 newMmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
2153 newMmd->setBitfields(md->bitfieldString());
2154 newMmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
2155 newMmd->setBodySegment(md->getDefLine(),md->getStartBodyLine(),md->getEndBodyLine());
2156 newMmd->setBodyDef(md->getBodyDef());
2157 newMmd->setInitializer(md->initializer());
2158 newMmd->setRequiresClause(md->requiresClause());
2159 newMmd->setMaxInitLines(md->initializerLines());
2160 newMmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
2161 newMmd->setMemberSpecifiers(md->getMemberSpecifiers());
2162 newMmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(md->getVhdlSpecifiers());
2163 newMmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
2164 newMmd->setId(root->id);
2165 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(memName);
2166 mn->push_back(std::move(newMd));
2167 }
2168 }
2169 }
2170 }
2171 }
2172 }
2173 }
2174 }
2175 else if (root->section.isUsingDecl() &&
2176 (root->parent()->section.isNamespace() || root->parent()->section.isEmpty()) && // namespace or global member
2177 root->lang==SrcLangExt::Cpp // do we also want this for e.g. Fortran? (see test case 095)
2178 )
2179 {
2180 AUTO_TRACE("Found using declaration '{}' inside section {}", root->name, root->parent()->section);
2181 Definition *scope = nullptr;
2182 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = nullptr;
2183 FileDef *fd = root->parent()->fileDef();
2184 if (!root->parent()->name.isEmpty())
2185 {
2186 QCString fullName=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->parent()->name);
2187 fullName=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(fullName);
2188 nd = toNamespaceDefMutable(getResolvedNamespace(fullName));
2189 scope = nd;
2190 }
2191 else
2192 {
2193 scope = fd;
2194 }
2195 if (scope)
2196 {
2197 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found scope '{}'",scope->name());
2198 SymbolResolver resolver;
2199 const Definition *def = resolver.resolveSymbol(root->name.startsWith("::") ? nullptr : scope,root->name);
2200 if (def && def->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
2201 {
2202 int i=root->name.find("::");
2203 QCString memName;
2204 if (i!=-1)
2205 {
2206 memName = root->name.right(root->name.length()-i-2);
2207 }
2208 else
2209 {
2210 memName = root->name;
2211 }
2212 const MemberDef *md = toMemberDef(def);
2213 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found member '{}' for name '{}'",md->qualifiedName(),root->name);
2214 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
2215 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
2216 {
2217 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
2218 }
2219 const ArgumentList &templAl = md->templateArguments();
2220 const ArgumentList &al = md->argumentList();
2221
2222 auto newMd = createMemberDef(
2223 fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
2224 md->typeString(),memName,md->argsString(),
2225 md->excpString(),root->protection,root->virt,
2226 md->isStatic(),Relationship::Member,md->memberType(),
2227 templAl,al,root->metaData
2228 );
2229 auto newMmd = toMemberDefMutable(newMd.get());
2230 if (nd)
2231 {
2232 newMmd->setNamespace(nd);
2233 nd->insertMember(newMd.get());
2234 }
2235 if (fd)
2236 {
2237 newMmd->setFileDef(fd);
2238 fd->insertMember(newMd.get());
2239 }
2240 if (!root->doc.isEmpty() || !root->brief.isEmpty())
2241 {
2242 newMmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
2243 newMmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
2244 newMmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
2245 }
2246 else
2247 {
2248 newMmd->setDocumentation(md->documentation(),md->docFile(),md->docLine());
2249 newMmd->setBriefDescription(md->briefDescription(),md->briefFile(),md->briefLine());
2250 newMmd->setInbodyDocumentation(md->inbodyDocumentation(),md->inbodyFile(),md->inbodyLine());
2251 }
2252 newMmd->setDefinition(md->definition());
2253 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,newMmd);
2254 newMmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
2255 newMmd->setBitfields(md->bitfieldString());
2256 newMmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
2257 newMmd->setBodySegment(md->getDefLine(),md->getStartBodyLine(),md->getEndBodyLine());
2258 newMmd->setBodyDef(md->getBodyDef());
2259 newMmd->setInitializer(md->initializer());
2260 newMmd->setRequiresClause(md->requiresClause());
2261 newMmd->setMaxInitLines(md->initializerLines());
2262 newMmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
2263 newMmd->setMemberSpecifiers(md->getMemberSpecifiers());
2264 newMmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(md->getVhdlSpecifiers());
2265 newMmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
2266 newMmd->setId(root->id);
2267 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(memName);
2268 mn->push_back(std::move(newMd));
2269#if 0 // insert an alias instead of a copy
2270 const MemberDef *md = toMemberDef(def);
2271 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found member '{}' for name '{}'",md->qualifiedName(),root->name);
2272 auto aliasMd = createMemberDefAlias(nd,md);
2273 QCString aliasFullName = nd->qualifiedName()+"::"+aliasMd->localName();
2274 if (nd && aliasMd.get())
2275 {
2276 nd->insertMember(aliasMd.get());
2277 }
2278 if (fd && aliasMd.get())
2279 {
2280 fd->insertMember(aliasMd.get());
2281 }
2282 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(aliasFullName);
2283 mn->push_back(std::move(aliasMd));
2284#endif
2285 }
2286 else if (def && def->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
2287 {
2288 const ClassDef *cd = toClassDef(def);
2289 QCString copyFullName;
2290 if (nd==nullptr)
2291 {
2292 copyFullName = cd->localName();
2293 }
2294 else
2295 {
2296 copyFullName = nd->qualifiedName()+"::"+cd->localName();
2297 }
2298 if (Doxygen::classLinkedMap->find(copyFullName)==nullptr)
2299 {
2300 ClassDefMutable *ncdm = toClassDefMutable(
2301 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(copyFullName,
2302 cd->deepCopy(copyFullName)));
2303 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found class '{}' for name '{}' copy '{}' obj={}",cd->qualifiedName(),root->name,copyFullName,(void*)ncdm);
2304 if (ncdm)
2305 {
2306 if (nd) ncdm->moveTo(nd);
2307 if ((!root->doc.isEmpty() || !root->brief.isEmpty())) // use docs at using statement
2308 {
2309 ncdm->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
2310 ncdm->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
2311 }
2312 else // use docs from used class
2313 {
2314 ncdm->setDocumentation(cd->documentation(),cd->docFile(),cd->docLine());
2315 ncdm->setBriefDescription(cd->briefDescription(),cd->briefFile(),cd->briefLine());
2316 }
2317 if (nd)
2318 {
2319 nd->addInnerCompound(ncdm);
2320 nd->addUsingDeclaration(ncdm);
2321 }
2322 if (fd)
2323 {
2324 if (ncdm) ncdm->setFileDef(fd);
2325 fd->insertClass(ncdm);
2326 fd->addUsingDeclaration(ncdm);
2327 }
2328 }
2329 }
2330#if 0 // insert an alias instead of a copy
2331 auto aliasCd = createClassDefAlias(nd,cd);
2332 QCString aliasFullName;
2333 if (nd==nullptr)
2334 {
2335 aliasFullName = aliasCd->localName();
2336 }
2337 else
2338 {
2339 aliasFullName = nd->qualifiedName()+"::"+aliasCd->localName();
2340 }
2341 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found class '{}' for name '{}' aliasFullName='{}'",cd->qualifiedName(),root->name,aliasFullName);
2342 auto acd = Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(aliasFullName,std::move(aliasCd));
2343 if (nd && acd)
2344 {
2345 nd->addInnerCompound(acd);
2346 }
2347 if (fd && acd)
2348 {
2349 fd->insertClass(acd);
2350 }
2351#endif
2352 }
2353 else if (scope)
2354 {
2355 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("no symbol with name '{}' in scope {}",root->name,scope->name());
2356 }
2357 }
2358 }
2359 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findUsingDeclImports(e.get());
2360}
