4274//----------------------------------------------------------------------
4275
4276/*! make a dictionary of all template arguments of class cd
4277 * that are part of the base class name.
4278 * Example: A template class A with template arguments <R,S,T>
4279 * that inherits from B<T,T,S> will have T and S in the dictionary.
4280 */
4281static TemplateNameMap getTemplateArgumentsInName(const ArgumentList &templateArguments,const std::string &name)
4282{
4283 std::map<std::string,int> templateNames;
4284 int count=0;
4285 for (const Argument &arg : templateArguments)
4286 {
4287 static const reg::Ex re(R"(\a[\w:]*)");
4288 reg::Iterator it(name,re);
4289 reg::Iterator end;
4290 for (; it!=end ; ++it)
4291 {
4292 const auto &match = *it;
4293 std::string n = match.str();
4294 if (n==arg.name.str())
4295 {
4296 if (templateNames.find(n)==templateNames.end())
4297 {
4298 templateNames.emplace(n,count);
4299 }
4300 }
4301 }
4302 }
4303 return templateNames;
4304}
4305
4306/*! Searches a class from within \a context and \a cd and returns its
4307 * definition if found (otherwise nullptr is returned).
4308 */
4309static ClassDef *findClassWithinClassContext(Definition *context,ClassDef *cd,const QCString &name)
4310{
4311 ClassDef *result=nullptr;
4312 if (cd==nullptr)
4313 {
4314 return result;
4315 }
4316 FileDef *fd=cd->getFileDef();
4317 SymbolResolver resolver(fd);
4318 if (context && cd!=context)
4319 {
4320 result = const_cast<ClassDef*>(resolver.resolveClass(context,name,true,true));
4321 }
4322 //printf("1. result=%p\n",result);
4323 if (result==nullptr)
4324 {
4325 result = const_cast<ClassDef*>(resolver.resolveClass(cd,name,true,true));
4326 }
4327 //printf("2. result=%p\n",result);
4328 if (result==nullptr) // try direct class, needed for namespaced classes imported via tag files (see bug624095)
4329 {
4330 result = getClass(name);
4331 }
4332 //printf("3. result=%p\n",result);
4333 //printf("** Trying to find %s within context %s class %s result=%s lookup=%p\n",
4334 // qPrint(name),
4335 // context ? qPrint(context->name()) : "<none>",
4336 // cd ? qPrint(cd->name()) : "<none>",
4337 // result ? qPrint(result->name()) : "<none>",
4338 // Doxygen::classLinkedMap->find(name)
4339 // );
4340 return result;
4341}
4342
4343
4344static void findUsedClassesForClass(const Entry *root,
4345 Definition *context,
4346 ClassDefMutable *masterCd,
4347 ClassDefMutable *instanceCd,
4348 bool isArtificial,
4349 const ArgumentList *actualArgs = nullptr,
4350 const TemplateNameMap &templateNames = TemplateNameMap()
4351 )
4352{
4353 AUTO_TRACE();
4354 const ArgumentList &formalArgs = masterCd->templateArguments();
4355 for (auto &mni : masterCd->memberNameInfoLinkedMap())
4356 {
4357 for (auto &mi : *mni)
4358 {
4359 const MemberDef *md=mi->memberDef();
4360 if (md->isVariable() || md->isObjCProperty()) // for each member variable in this class
4361 {
4362 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Found variable '{}' in class '{}'",md->name(),masterCd->name());
4363 QCString type = normalizeNonTemplateArgumentsInString(md->typeString(),masterCd,formalArgs);
4364 QCString typedefValue = md->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Java ? type : resolveTypeDef(masterCd,type);
4365 if (!typedefValue.isEmpty())
4366 {
4367 type = typedefValue;
4368 }
4369 int pos=0;
4370 QCString usedClassName;
4371 QCString templSpec;
4372 bool found=FALSE;
4373 // the type can contain template variables, replace them if present
4374 type = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(type,formalArgs,actualArgs);
4375
4376 //printf(" template substitution gives=%s\n",qPrint(type));
4377 while (!found && extractClassNameFromType(type,pos,usedClassName,templSpec,root->lang)!=-1)
4378 {
4379 // find the type (if any) that matches usedClassName
4380 SymbolResolver resolver(masterCd->getFileDef());
4381 const ClassDefMutable *typeCd = resolver.resolveClassMutable(masterCd,usedClassName,false,true);
4382 //printf("====> usedClassName=%s -> typeCd=%s\n",
4383 // qPrint(usedClassName),typeCd?qPrint(typeCd->name()):"<none>");
4384 if (typeCd)
4385 {
4386 usedClassName = typeCd->name();
4387 }
4388
4389 int sp=usedClassName.find('<');
4390 if (sp==-1) sp=0;
4391 // replace any namespace aliases
4392 replaceNamespaceAliases(usedClassName);
4393 // add any template arguments to the class
4394 QCString usedName = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(usedClassName+templSpec);
4395 //printf(" usedName=%s usedClassName=%s templSpec=%s\n",qPrint(usedName),qPrint(usedClassName),qPrint(templSpec));
4396
4397 TemplateNameMap formTemplateNames;
4398 if (templateNames.empty())
4399 {
4400 formTemplateNames = getTemplateArgumentsInName(formalArgs,usedName.str());
4401 }
4402 BaseInfo bi(usedName,Protection::Public,Specifier::Normal);
4403 findClassRelation(root,context,instanceCd,&bi,formTemplateNames,TemplateInstances,isArtificial);
4404
4405 for (const Argument &arg : masterCd->templateArguments())
4406 {
4407 if (arg.name==usedName) // type is a template argument
4408 {
4409 ClassDef *usedCd = Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->find(usedName);
4410 ClassDefMutable *usedCdm = toClassDefMutable(usedCd);
4411 if (usedCd==nullptr)
4412 {
4413 usedCdm = toClassDefMutable(
4414 Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->add(usedName,
4415 createClassDef(
4416 masterCd->getDefFileName(),masterCd->getDefLine(),
4417 masterCd->getDefColumn(),
4418 usedName,
4419 ClassDef::Class)));
4420 if (usedCdm)
4421 {
4422 //printf("making %s a template argument!!!\n",qPrint(usedCd->name()));
4423 usedCdm->makeTemplateArgument();
4424 usedCdm->setUsedOnly(TRUE);
4425 usedCdm->setLanguage(masterCd->getLanguage());
4426 usedCd = usedCdm;
4427 }
4428 }
4429 if (usedCd)
4430 {
4431 found=TRUE;
4432 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("case 1: adding used class '{}'", usedCd->name());
4433 instanceCd->addUsedClass(usedCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4434 if (usedCdm)
4435 {
4436 if (isArtificial) usedCdm->setArtificial(TRUE);
4437 usedCdm->addUsedByClass(instanceCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4438 }
4439 }
4440 }
4441 }
4442
4443 if (!found)
4444 {
4445 ClassDef *usedCd=findClassWithinClassContext(context,masterCd,usedName);
4446 //printf("Looking for used class %s: result=%s master=%s\n",
4447 // qPrint(usedName),usedCd?qPrint(usedCd->name()):"<none>",masterCd?qPrint(masterCd->name()):"<none>");
4448
4449 if (usedCd)
4450 {
4451 found=TRUE;
4452 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("case 2: adding used class '{}'", usedCd->name());
4453 instanceCd->addUsedClass(usedCd,md->name(),md->protection()); // class exists
4454 ClassDefMutable *usedCdm = toClassDefMutable(usedCd);
4455 if (usedCdm)
4456 {
4457 usedCdm->addUsedByClass(instanceCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4458 }
4459 }
4460 }
4461 }
4462 if (!found && !type.isEmpty()) // used class is not documented in any scope
4463 {
4464 ClassDef *usedCd = Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->find(type);
4465 ClassDefMutable *usedCdm = toClassDefMutable(usedCd);
4466 if (usedCd==nullptr && !Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_RELATIONS))
4467 {
4468 if (type.endsWith("(*") || type.endsWith("(^")) // type is a function pointer
4469 {
4470 type+=md->argsString();
4471 }
4472 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New undocumented used class '{}'", type);
4473 usedCdm = toClassDefMutable(
4474 Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->add(type,
4475 createClassDef(
4476 masterCd->getDefFileName(),masterCd->getDefLine(),
4477 masterCd->getDefColumn(),
4478 type,ClassDef::Class)));
4479 if (usedCdm)
4480 {
4481 usedCdm->setUsedOnly(TRUE);
4482 usedCdm->setLanguage(masterCd->getLanguage());
4483 usedCd = usedCdm;
4484 }
4485 }
4486 if (usedCd)
4487 {
4488 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("case 3: adding used class '{}'", usedCd->name());
4489 instanceCd->addUsedClass(usedCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4490 if (usedCdm)
4491 {
4492 if (isArtificial) usedCdm->setArtificial(TRUE);
4493 usedCdm->addUsedByClass(instanceCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4494 }
4495 }
4496 }
4497 }
4498 }
4499 }
4500}
4501
4502static void findBaseClassesForClass(
4503 const Entry *root,
4504 Definition *context,
4505 ClassDefMutable *masterCd,
4506 ClassDefMutable *instanceCd,
4507 FindBaseClassRelation_Mode mode,
4508 bool isArtificial,
4509 const ArgumentList *actualArgs = nullptr,
4510 const TemplateNameMap &templateNames=TemplateNameMap()
4511 )
4512{
4513 AUTO_TRACE("name={}",root->name);
4514 // The base class could ofcouse also be a non-nested class
4515 const ArgumentList &formalArgs = masterCd->templateArguments();
4516 for (const BaseInfo &bi : root->extends)
4517 {
4518 //printf("masterCd=%s bi.name='%s' #actualArgs=%d\n",
4519 // qPrint(masterCd->localName()),qPrint(bi.name),actualArgs ? (int)actualArgs->size() : -1);
4520 TemplateNameMap formTemplateNames;
4521 if (templateNames.empty())
4522 {
4523 formTemplateNames = getTemplateArgumentsInName(formalArgs,bi.name.str());
4524 }
4525 BaseInfo tbi = bi;
4526 tbi.name = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(bi.name,formalArgs,actualArgs);
4527 //printf("masterCd=%p instanceCd=%p bi->name=%s tbi.name=%s\n",(void*)masterCd,(void*)instanceCd,qPrint(bi.name),qPrint(tbi.name));
4528
4529 if (mode==DocumentedOnly)
4530 {
4531 // find a documented base class in the correct scope
4532 if (!findClassRelation(root,context,instanceCd,&tbi,formTemplateNames,DocumentedOnly,isArtificial))
4533 {
4534 // 1.8.2: decided to show inheritance relations even if not documented,
4535 // we do make them artificial, so they do not appear in the index
4536 //if (!Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_RELATIONS))
4537 bool b = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_RELATIONS) ? TRUE : isArtificial;
4538 //{
4539 // no documented base class -> try to find an undocumented one
4540 findClassRelation(root,context,instanceCd,&tbi,formTemplateNames,Undocumented,b);
4541 //}
4542 }
4543 }
4544 else if (mode==TemplateInstances)
4545 {
4546 findClassRelation(root,context,instanceCd,&tbi,formTemplateNames,TemplateInstances,isArtificial);
4547 }
4548 }
4549}
4550
4551//----------------------------------------------------------------------
4552
4553static void findTemplateInstanceRelation(const Entry *root,
4554 Definition *context,
4555 ClassDefMutable *templateClass,const QCString &templSpec,
4556 const TemplateNameMap &templateNames,
4557 bool isArtificial)
4558{
4559 AUTO_TRACE("Derived from template '{}' with parameters '{}' isArtificial={}",
4560 templateClass->name(),templSpec,isArtificial);
4561
4562 QCString tempArgsStr = tempArgListToString(templateClass->templateArguments(),root->lang,false);
4563 bool existingClass = templSpec==tempArgsStr;
4564 if (existingClass) return; // avoid recursion
4565
4566 bool freshInstance=FALSE;
4567 ClassDefMutable *instanceClass = toClassDefMutable(
4568 templateClass->insertTemplateInstance(
4569 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,templSpec,freshInstance));
4570 if (instanceClass)
4571 {
4572 instanceClass->setArtificial(TRUE);
4573 instanceClass->setLanguage(root->lang);
4574
4575 if (freshInstance)
4576 {
4577 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("found fresh instance '{}'",instanceClass->name());
4578 instanceClass->setTemplateBaseClassNames(templateNames);
4579
4580 // search for new template instances caused by base classes of
4581 // instanceClass
4582 auto it_pair = g_classEntries.equal_range(templateClass->name().str());
4583 for (auto it=it_pair.first ; it!=it_pair.second ; ++it)
4584 {
4585 const Entry *templateRoot = it->second;
4586 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("template root found '{}' templSpec='{}'",templateRoot->name,templSpec);
4587 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> templArgs = stringToArgumentList(root->lang,templSpec);
4588 findBaseClassesForClass(templateRoot,context,templateClass,instanceClass,
4589 TemplateInstances,isArtificial,templArgs.get(),templateNames);
4590
4591 findUsedClassesForClass(templateRoot,context,templateClass,instanceClass,
4592 isArtificial,templArgs.get(),templateNames);
4593 }
4594 }
4595 else
4596 {
4597 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("instance already exists");
4598 }
4599 }
4600}
4601
4602static bool isRecursiveBaseClass(const QCString &scope,const QCString &name)
4603{
4604 QCString n=name;
4605 int index=n.find('<');
4606 if (index!=-1)
4607 {
4608 n=n.left(index);
4609 }
4610 bool result = rightScopeMatch(scope,n);
4611 return result;
4612}
4613
4614/*! Searches for the end of a template in prototype \a s starting from
4615 * character position \a startPos. If the end was found the position
4616 * of the closing > is returned, otherwise -1 is returned.
4617 *
4618 * Handles exotic cases such as
4619 * \code
4620 * Class<(id<0)>
4621 * Class<bits<<2>
4622 * Class<"<">
4623 * Class<'<'>
4624 * Class<(")<")>
4625 * \endcode
4626 */
4627static int findEndOfTemplate(const QCString &s,size_t startPos)
4628{
4629 // locate end of template
4630 size_t e=startPos;
4631 int brCount=1;
4632 int roundCount=0;
4633 size_t len = s.length();
4634 bool insideString=FALSE;
4635 bool insideChar=FALSE;
4636 char pc = 0;
4637 while (e<len && brCount!=0)
4638 {
4639 char c=s.at(e);
4640 switch(c)
4641 {
4642 case '<':
4643 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4644 {
4645 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='<')
4646 e++;
4647 else if (roundCount==0)
4648 brCount++;
4649 }
4650 break;
4651 case '>':
4652 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4653 {
4654 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='>')
4655 e++;
4656 else if (roundCount==0)
4657 brCount--;
4658 }
4659 break;
4660 case '(':
4661 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4662 roundCount++;
4663 break;
4664 case ')':
4665 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4666 roundCount--;
4667 break;
4668 case '"':
4669 if (!insideChar)
4670 {
4671 if (insideString && pc!='\\')
4672 insideString=FALSE;
4673 else
4674 insideString=TRUE;
4675 }
4676 break;
4677 case '\'':
4678 if (!insideString)
4679 {
4680 if (insideChar && pc!='\\')
4681 insideChar=FALSE;
4682 else
4683 insideChar=TRUE;
4684 }
4685 break;
4686 }
4687 pc = c;
4688 e++;
4689 }
4690 return brCount==0 ? static_cast<int>(e) : -1;
4691}
4692
4693static int findTemplateSpecializationPosition(const QCString &name)
4694{
4695 if (name.isEmpty()) return 0;
4696 int l = static_cast<int>(name.length());
4697 if (name[l-1]=='>') // search backward to find the matching <, allowing nested <...> and strings.
4698 {
4699 int count=1;
4700 int i=l-2;
4701 char insideQuote=0;
4702 while (count>0 && i>=0)
4703 {
4704 char c = name[i--];
4705 switch (c)
4706 {
4707 case '>': if (!insideQuote) count++; break;
4708 case '<': if (!insideQuote) count--; break;
4709 case '\'': if (!insideQuote) insideQuote=c;
4710 else if (insideQuote==c && (i<0 || name[i]!='\\')) insideQuote=0;
4711 break;
4712 case '"': if (!insideQuote) insideQuote=c;
4713 else if (insideQuote==c && (i<0 || name[i]!='\\')) insideQuote=0;
4714 break;
4715 default: break;
4716 }
4717 }
4718 if (i>=0) l=i+1;
4719 }
4720 return l;
4721}
4722
4723static bool findClassRelation(
4724 const Entry *root,
4725 Definition *context,
4726 ClassDefMutable *cd,
4727 const BaseInfo *bi,
4728 const TemplateNameMap &templateNames,
4729 FindBaseClassRelation_Mode mode,
4730 bool isArtificial
4731 )
4732{
4733 AUTO_TRACE("name={} base={} isArtificial={}",cd->name(),bi->name,isArtificial);
4734
4735 QCString biName=bi->name;
4736 bool explicitGlobalScope=FALSE;
4737 if (biName.startsWith("::")) // explicit global scope
4738 {
4739 biName=biName.right(biName.length()-2);
4740 explicitGlobalScope=TRUE;
4741 }
4742
4743 Entry *parentNode=root->parent();
4744 bool lastParent=FALSE;
4745 do // for each parent scope, starting with the largest scope
4746 // (in case of nested classes)
4747 {
4748 QCString scopeName= parentNode ? parentNode->name : QCString();
4749 int scopeOffset=explicitGlobalScope ? 0 : static_cast<int>(scopeName.length());
4750 do // try all parent scope prefixes, starting with the largest scope
4751 {
4752 //printf("scopePrefix='%s' biName='%s'\n",
4753 // qPrint(scopeName.left(scopeOffset)),qPrint(biName));
4754
4755 QCString baseClassName=biName;
4756 if (scopeOffset>0)
4757 {
4758 baseClassName.prepend(scopeName.left(scopeOffset)+"::");
4759 }
4760 //QCString stripped;
4761 //baseClassName=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope
4762 // (removeRedundantWhiteSpace(baseClassName),TRUE,
4763 // &stripped);
4764 SymbolResolver resolver(cd->getFileDef());
4765 ClassDefMutable *baseClass = resolver.resolveClassMutable(explicitGlobalScope ? Doxygen::globalScope : context,
4766 baseClassName,
4767 mode==Undocumented,
4768 true
4769 );
4770 const MemberDef *baseClassTypeDef = resolver.getTypedef();
4771 QCString templSpec = resolver.getTemplateSpec();
4772 //printf("baseClassName=%s baseClass=%p cd=%p explicitGlobalScope=%d\n",
4773 // qPrint(baseClassName),baseClass,cd,explicitGlobalScope);
4774 //printf(" scope='%s' baseClassName='%s' baseClass=%s templSpec=%s\n",
4775 // cd ? qPrint(cd->name()):"<none>",
4776 // qPrint(baseClassName),
4777 // baseClass?qPrint(baseClass->name()):"<none>",
4778 // qPrint(templSpec)
4779 // );
4780 //if (baseClassName.left(root->name.length())!=root->name ||
4781 // baseClassName.at(root->name.length())!='<'
4782 // ) // Check for base class with the same name.
4783 // // If found then look in the outer scope for a match
4784 // // and prevent recursion.
4785 if (!isRecursiveBaseClass(root->name,baseClassName)
4786 || explicitGlobalScope
4787 // sadly isRecursiveBaseClass always true for UNO IDL ifc/svc members
4788 // (i.e. this is needed for addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton)
4789 || (root->lang==SrcLangExt::IDL &&
4790 (root->section.isExportedInterface() ||
4791 root->section.isIncludedService()))
4792 )
4793 {
4794 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("class relation '{}' inherited/used by '{}' found prot={} virt={} templSpec='{}'",
4795 baseClassName, root->name, bi->prot, bi->virt, templSpec);
4796
4797 int i=findTemplateSpecializationPosition(baseClassName);
4798 int si=baseClassName.findRev("::",i);
4799 if (si==-1) si=0;
4800 if (baseClass==nullptr && static_cast<size_t>(i)!=baseClassName.length())
4801 // base class has template specifiers
4802 {
4803 // TODO: here we should try to find the correct template specialization
4804 // but for now, we only look for the unspecialized base class.
4805 int e=findEndOfTemplate(baseClassName,i+1);
4806 //printf("baseClass==0 i=%d e=%d\n",i,e);
4807 if (e!=-1) // end of template was found at e
4808 {
4809 templSpec = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(baseClassName.mid(i,e-i));
4810 baseClassName = baseClassName.left(i)+baseClassName.right(baseClassName.length()-e);
4811 baseClass = resolver.resolveClassMutable(explicitGlobalScope ? Doxygen::globalScope : context,
4812 baseClassName,
4813 mode==Undocumented,
4814 true
4815 );
4816 baseClassTypeDef = resolver.getTypedef();
4817 //printf("baseClass=%p -> baseClass=%s templSpec=%s\n",
4818 // baseClass,qPrint(baseClassName),qPrint(templSpec));
4819 }
4820 }
4821 else if (baseClass && !templSpec.isEmpty()) // we have a known class, but also
4822 // know it is a template, so see if
4823 // we can also link to the explicit
4824 // instance (for instance if a class
4825 // derived from a template argument)
4826 {
4827 //printf("baseClass=%s templSpec=%s\n",qPrint(baseClass->name()),qPrint(templSpec));
4828 ClassDefMutable *templClass=getClassMutable(baseClass->name()+templSpec);
4829 if (templClass)
4830 {
4831 // use the template instance instead of the template base.
4832 baseClass = templClass;
4833 templSpec.clear();
4834 }
4835 }
4836
4837 //printf("cd=%p baseClass=%p\n",cd,baseClass);
4838 bool found=baseClass!=nullptr && (baseClass!=cd || mode==TemplateInstances);
4839 //printf("1. found=%d\n",found);
4840 if (!found && si!=-1)
4841 {
4842 // replace any namespace aliases
4843 replaceNamespaceAliases(baseClassName);
4844 baseClass = resolver.resolveClassMutable(explicitGlobalScope ? Doxygen::globalScope : context,
4845 baseClassName,
4846 mode==Undocumented,
4847 true
4848 );
4849 baseClassTypeDef = resolver.getTypedef();
4850 found=baseClass!=nullptr && baseClass!=cd;
4851 if (found) templSpec = resolver.getTemplateSpec();
4852 }
4853 //printf("2. found=%d\n",found);
4854
4855 if (!found)
4856 {
4857 baseClass=toClassDefMutable(findClassWithinClassContext(context,cd,baseClassName));
4858 //printf("findClassWithinClassContext(%s,%s)=%p\n",
4859 // qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(baseClassName),baseClass);
4860 found = baseClass!=nullptr && baseClass!=cd;
4861
4862 }
4863 //printf("3. found=%d\n",found);
4864 if (!found)
4865 {
4866 // for PHP the "use A\B as C" construct map class C to A::B, so we lookup
4867 // the class name also in the alias mapping.
4868 auto it = Doxygen::namespaceAliasMap.find(baseClassName.str());
4869 if (it!=Doxygen::namespaceAliasMap.end()) // see if it is indeed a class.
4870 {
4871 baseClass=getClassMutable(QCString(it->second.alias));
4872 found = baseClass!=nullptr && baseClass!=cd;
4873 }
4874 }
4875 bool isATemplateArgument = templateNames.find(biName.str())!=templateNames.end();
4876
4877 //printf("4. found=%d\n",found);
4878 if (found)
4879 {
4880 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Documented base class '{}' templSpec='{}'",biName,templSpec);
4881 // add base class to this class
4882
4883 // if templSpec is not empty then we should "instantiate"
4884 // the template baseClass. A new ClassDef should be created
4885 // to represent the instance. To be able to add the (instantiated)
4886 // members and documentation of a template class
4887 // (inserted in that template class at a later stage),
4888 // the template should know about its instances.
4889 // the instantiation process, should be done in a recursive way,
4890 // since instantiating a template may introduce new inheritance
4891 // relations.
4892 if (!templSpec.isEmpty() && mode==TemplateInstances)
4893 {
4894 // if baseClass is actually a typedef then we should not
4895 // instantiate it, since typedefs are in a different namespace
4896 // see bug531637 for an example where this would otherwise hang
4897 // Doxygen
4898 if (baseClassTypeDef==nullptr)
4899 {
4900 //printf(" => findTemplateInstanceRelation: %s\n",qPrint(baseClass->name()));
4901 findTemplateInstanceRelation(root,context,baseClass,templSpec,templateNames,baseClass->isArtificial());
4902 }
4903 }
4904 else if (mode==DocumentedOnly || mode==Undocumented)
4905 {
4906 //printf(" => insert base class\n");
4907 QCString usedName;
4908 if (baseClassTypeDef || cd->isCSharp())
4909 {
4910 usedName=biName;
4911 //printf("***** usedName=%s templSpec=%s\n",qPrint(usedName),qPrint(templSpec));
4912 }
4913 Protection prot = bi->prot;
4914 if (Config_getBool(SIP_SUPPORT)) prot=Protection::Public;
4915 if (cd!=baseClass && !cd->isSubClass(baseClass) && baseClass->isBaseClass(cd,true,templSpec)==0) // check for recursion, see bug690787
4916 {
4917 cd->insertBaseClass(baseClass,usedName,prot,bi->virt,templSpec);
4918 // add this class as super class to the base class
4919 baseClass->insertSubClass(cd,prot,bi->virt,templSpec);
4920 }
4921 else
4922 {
4923 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
4924 "Detected potential recursive class relation "
4925 "between class %s and base class %s!",
4926 qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(baseClass->name())
4927 );
4928 }
4929 }
4930 return TRUE;
4931 }
4932 else if (mode==Undocumented && (scopeOffset==0 || isATemplateArgument))
4933 {
4934 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("New undocumented base class '{}' baseClassName='{}' templSpec='{}' isArtificial={}",
4935 biName,baseClassName,templSpec,isArtificial);
4936 baseClass=nullptr;
4937 if (isATemplateArgument)
4938 {
4939 baseClass = toClassDefMutable(Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->find(baseClassName));
4940 if (baseClass==nullptr) // not found (or alias)
4941 {
4942 baseClass= toClassDefMutable(
4943 Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->add(baseClassName,
4944 createClassDef(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
4945 baseClassName,
4946 ClassDef::Class)));
4947 if (baseClass) // really added (not alias)
4948 {
4949 if (isArtificial) baseClass->setArtificial(TRUE);
4950 baseClass->setLanguage(root->lang);
4951 }
4952 }
4953 }
4954 else
4955 {
4956 baseClass = toClassDefMutable(Doxygen::classLinkedMap->find(baseClassName));
4957 //printf("*** classDDict->find(%s)=%p biName=%s templSpec=%s\n",
4958 // qPrint(baseClassName),baseClass,qPrint(biName),qPrint(templSpec));
4959 if (baseClass==nullptr) // not found (or alias)
4960 {
4961 baseClass = toClassDefMutable(
4962 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->add(baseClassName,
4963 createClassDef(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
4964 baseClassName,
4965 ClassDef::Class)));
4966 if (baseClass) // really added (not alias)
4967 {
4968 if (isArtificial) baseClass->setArtificial(TRUE);
4969 baseClass->setLanguage(root->lang);
4970 si = baseClassName.findRev("::");
4971 if (si!=-1) // class is nested
4972 {
4973 Definition *sd = findScopeFromQualifiedName(Doxygen::globalScope,baseClassName.left(si),nullptr,root->tagInfo());
4974 if (sd==nullptr || sd==Doxygen::globalScope) // outer scope not found
4975 {
4976 baseClass->setArtificial(TRUE); // see bug678139
4977 }
4978 }
4979 }
4980 }
4981 }
4982 if (baseClass)
4983 {
4984 if (biName.endsWith("-p"))
4985 {
4986 biName="<"+biName.left(biName.length()-2)+">";
4987 }
4988 if (!cd->isSubClass(baseClass) && cd!=baseClass && cd->isBaseClass(baseClass,true,templSpec)==0) // check for recursion
4989 {
4990 // add base class to this class
4991 cd->insertBaseClass(baseClass,biName,bi->prot,bi->virt,templSpec);
4992 // add this class as super class to the base class
4993 baseClass->insertSubClass(cd,bi->prot,bi->virt,templSpec);
4994 }
4995 // the undocumented base was found in this file
4996 baseClass->insertUsedFile(root->fileDef());
4997
4998 Definition *scope = buildScopeFromQualifiedName(baseClass->name(),root->lang,nullptr);
4999 if (scope!=baseClass)
5000 {
5001 baseClass->setOuterScope(scope);
5002 }
5003
5004 if (baseClassName.endsWith("-p"))
5005 {
5006 baseClass->setCompoundType(ClassDef::Protocol);
5007 }
5008 return TRUE;
5009 }
5010 else
5011 {
5012 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Base class '{}' not created (alias?)",biName);
5013 }
5014 }
5015 else
5016 {
5017 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Base class '{}' not found",biName);
5018 }
5019 }
5020 else
5021 {
5022 if (mode!=TemplateInstances)
5023 {
5024 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
5025 "Detected potential recursive class relation "
5026 "between class %s and base class %s!",
5027 qPrint(root->name),qPrint(baseClassName)
5028 );
5029 }
5030 // for mode==TemplateInstance this case is quite common and
5031 // indicates a relation between a template class and a template
5032 // instance with the same name.
5033 }
5034 if (scopeOffset==0)
5035 {
5036 scopeOffset=-1;
5037 }
5038 else if ((scopeOffset=scopeName.findRev("::",scopeOffset-1))==-1)
5039 {
5040 scopeOffset=0;
5041 }
5042 //printf("new scopeOffset='%d'",scopeOffset);
5043 } while (scopeOffset>=0);
5044
5045 if (parentNode==nullptr)
5046 {
5047 lastParent=TRUE;
5048 }
5049 else
5050 {
5051 parentNode=parentNode->parent();
5052 }
5053 } while (lastParent);
5054
5055 return FALSE;
5056}
5057
5058//----------------------------------------------------------------------
5059// Computes the base and super classes for each class in the tree
5060
5061static bool isClassSection(const Entry *root)
5062{
5063 if ( !root->name.isEmpty() )
5064 {
5065 if (root->section.isCompound())
5066 // is it a compound (class, struct, union, interface ...)
5067 {
5068 return TRUE;
5069 }
5070 else if (root->section.isCompoundDoc())
5071 // is it a documentation block with inheritance info.
5072 {
5073 bool hasExtends = !root->extends.empty();
5074 if (hasExtends) return TRUE;
5075 }
5076 }
5077 return FALSE;
5078}
5079
5080
5081/*! Builds a dictionary of all entry nodes in the tree starting with \a root
5082 */
5083static void findClassEntries(const Entry *root)
5084{
5085 if (isClassSection(root))
5086 {
5087 g_classEntries.emplace(root->name.str(),root);
5088 }
5089 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findClassEntries(e.get());
5090}
5091
5092static QCString extractClassName(const Entry *root)
5093{
5094 // strip any anonymous scopes first
5095 QCString bName=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->name);
5096 bName=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(bName);
5097 int i=0;
5098 if ((root->lang==SrcLangExt::CSharp || root->lang==SrcLangExt::Java) &&
5099 (i=bName.find('<'))!=-1)
5100 {
5101 // a Java/C# generic class looks like a C++ specialization, so we need to strip the
5102 // template part before looking for matches
5103 bName=bName.left(i);
5104 }
5105 return bName;
5106}
5107
5108/*! Using the dictionary build by findClassEntries(), this
5109 * function will look for additional template specialization that
5110 * exists as inheritance relations only. These instances will be
5111 * added to the template they are derived from.
5112 */
5113static void findInheritedTemplateInstances()
5114{
5115 AUTO_TRACE();
5116 ClassDefSet visitedClasses;
5117 for (const auto &[name,root] : g_classEntries)
5118 {
5119 QCString bName = extractClassName(root);
5120 ClassDefMutable *cdm = getClassMutable(bName);
5121 if (cdm)
5122 {
5123 findBaseClassesForClass(root,cdm,cdm,cdm,TemplateInstances,FALSE);
5124 }
5125 }
5126}
5127
5128static void makeTemplateInstanceRelation(const Entry *root,ClassDefMutable *cd)
5129{
5130 AUTO_TRACE("root->name={} cd={}",root->name,cd->name());
5131 int i = root->name.find('<');
5132 if (i!=-1)
5133 {
5134 ClassDefMutable *master = getClassMutable(root->name.left(i));
5135 if (master && master!=cd && !cd->templateMaster())
5136 {
5137 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("class={} master={}",cd->name(),cd->templateMaster()?cd->templateMaster()->name():"<none>",master->name());
5138 cd->setTemplateMaster(master);
5139 master->insertExplicitTemplateInstance(cd,root->name.mid(i));
5140 }
5141 }
5142}
5143
5144static void findUsedTemplateInstances()
5145{
5146 AUTO_TRACE();
5147 for (const auto &[name,root] : g_classEntries)
5148 {
5149 QCString bName = extractClassName(root);
5150 ClassDefMutable *cdm = getClassMutable(bName);
5151 if (cdm)
5152 {
5153 findUsedClassesForClass(root,cdm,cdm,cdm,TRUE);
5154 makeTemplateInstanceRelation(root,cdm);
5155 cdm->addTypeConstraints();
5156 }
5157 }
5158}
5159
5160static void warnUndocumentedNamespaces()
5161{
5162 AUTO_TRACE();
5163 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
5164 {
5165 if (!nd->hasDocumentation())
5166 {
5167 if ((guessSection(nd->getDefFileName()).isHeader() ||
5168 nd->getLanguage() == SrcLangExt::Fortran) && // Fortran doesn't have header files.
5169 !Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_NAMESPACES) // undocumented namespaces are visible
5170 )
5171 {
5172 warn_undoc(nd->getDefFileName(),nd->getDefLine(), "%s %s is not documented.",
5173 nd->getLanguage() == SrcLangExt::Fortran ? "Module" : "Namespace",
5174 qPrint(nd->name()));
5175 }
5176 }
5177 }
5178}
5179
5180static void computeClassRelations()
5181{
5182 AUTO_TRACE();
5183 for (const auto &[name,root] : g_classEntries)
5184 {
5185 QCString bName = extractClassName(root);
5186 ClassDefMutable *cd = getClassMutable(bName);
5187 if (cd)
5188 {
5189 findBaseClassesForClass(root,cd,cd,cd,DocumentedOnly,FALSE);
5190 }
5191 size_t numMembers = cd ? cd->memberNameInfoLinkedMap().size() : 0;
5192 if ((cd==nullptr || (!cd->hasDocumentation() && !cd->isReference())) && numMembers>0 && !bName.endsWith("::"))
5193 {
5194 if (!root->name.isEmpty() && root->name.find('@')==-1 && // normal name
5195 (guessSection(root->fileName).isHeader() ||
5196 Config_getBool(EXTRACT_LOCAL_CLASSES)) && // not defined in source file
5197 protectionLevelVisible(root->protection) && // hidden by protection
5198 !Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_CLASSES) // undocumented class are visible
5199 )
5200 warn_undoc(
5201 root->fileName,root->startLine,
5202 "Compound %s is not documented.",
5203 qPrint(root->name)
5204 );
5205 }
5206 }
5207}
5208
5209static void computeTemplateClassRelations()
5210{
5211 AUTO_TRACE();
5212 for (const auto &[name,root] : g_classEntries)
5213 {
5214 QCString bName=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->name);
5215 bName=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(bName);
5216 ClassDefMutable *cd=getClassMutable(bName);
5217 // strip any anonymous scopes first
5218 if (cd && !cd->getTemplateInstances().empty())
5219 {
5220 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Template class '{}'",cd->name());
5221 for (const auto &ti : cd->getTemplateInstances()) // for each template instance
5222 {
5223 ClassDefMutable *tcd=toClassDefMutable(ti.classDef);
5224 if (tcd)
5225 {
5226 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Template instance '{}'",tcd->name());
5227 QCString templSpec = ti.templSpec;
5228 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> templArgs = stringToArgumentList(tcd->getLanguage(),templSpec);
5229 for (const BaseInfo &bi : root->extends)
5230 {
5231 // check if the base class is a template argument
5232 BaseInfo tbi = bi;
5233 const ArgumentList &tl = cd->templateArguments();
5234 if (!tl.empty())
5235 {
5236 TemplateNameMap baseClassNames = tcd->getTemplateBaseClassNames();
5237 TemplateNameMap templateNames = getTemplateArgumentsInName(tl,bi.name.str());
5238 // for each template name that we inherit from we need to
5239 // substitute the formal with the actual arguments
5240 TemplateNameMap actualTemplateNames;
5241 for (const auto &tn_kv : templateNames)
5242 {
5243 size_t templIndex = tn_kv.second;
5244 Argument actArg;
5245 bool hasActArg=FALSE;
5246 if (templIndex<templArgs->size())
5247 {
5248 actArg=templArgs->at(templIndex);
5249 hasActArg=TRUE;
5250 }
5251 if (hasActArg &&
5252 baseClassNames.find(actArg.type.str())!=baseClassNames.end() &&
5253 actualTemplateNames.find(actArg.type.str())==actualTemplateNames.end()
5254 )
5255 {
5256 actualTemplateNames.emplace(actArg.type.str(),static_cast<int>(templIndex));
5257 }
5258 }
5259
5260 tbi.name = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(bi.name,tl,templArgs.get());
5261 // find a documented base class in the correct scope
5262 if (!findClassRelation(root,cd,tcd,&tbi,actualTemplateNames,DocumentedOnly,FALSE))
5263 {
5264 // no documented base class -> try to find an undocumented one
5265 findClassRelation(root,cd,tcd,&tbi,actualTemplateNames,Undocumented,TRUE);
5266 }
5267 }
5268 }
5269 }
5270 }
5271 }
5272 }
5273}
5274
5275//-----------------------------------------------------------------------
5276// compute the references (anchors in HTML) for each function in the file
5277
5278static void computeMemberReferences()
5279{
5280 AUTO_TRACE();
5281 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
5282 {
5283 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
5284 if (cdm)
5285 {
5286 cdm->computeAnchors();
5287 }
5288 }
5289 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
5290 {
5291 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
5292 {
5293 fd->computeAnchors();
5294 }
5295 }
5296 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
5297 {
5298 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
5299 if (ndm)
5300 {
5301 ndm->computeAnchors();
5302 }
5303 }
5304 for (const auto &gd : *Doxygen::groupLinkedMap)
5305 {
5306 gd->computeAnchors();
5307 }
5308}
5309

5311
5312static void addListReferences()
5313{
5314 AUTO_TRACE();
5315 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
5316 {
5317 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
5318 if (cdm)
5319 {
5320 cdm->addListReferences();
5321 }
5322 }
5323
5324 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
5325 {
5326 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
5327 {
5328 fd->addListReferences();
5329 }
5330 }
5331
5332 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
5333 {
5334 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
5335 if (ndm)
5336 {
5337 ndm->addListReferences();
5338 }
5339 }
5340
5341 for (const auto &gd : *Doxygen::groupLinkedMap)
5342 {
5343 gd->addListReferences();
5344 }
5345
5346 for (const auto &pd : *Doxygen::pageLinkedMap)
5347 {
5348 QCString name = pd->getOutputFileBase();
5349 if (pd->getGroupDef())
5350 {
5351 name = pd->getGroupDef()->getOutputFileBase();
5352 }
5353 {
5354 const RefItemVector &xrefItems = pd->xrefListItems();
5355 addRefItem(xrefItems,
5356 name,
5357 theTranslator->trPage(TRUE,TRUE),
5358 name,pd->title(),QCString(),nullptr);
5359 }
5360 }
5361
5362 for (const auto &dd : *Doxygen::dirLinkedMap)
5363 {
5364 QCString name = dd->getOutputFileBase();
5365 //if (dd->getGroupDef())
5366 //{
5367 // name = dd->getGroupDef()->getOutputFileBase();
5368 //}
5369 const RefItemVector &xrefItems = dd->xrefListItems();
5370 addRefItem(xrefItems,
5371 name,
5372 theTranslator->trDir(TRUE,TRUE),
5373 name,dd->displayName(),QCString(),nullptr);
5374 }
5375
5376 ModuleManager::instance().addListReferences();
5377}

5390//----------------------------------------------------------------------
5391// Copy the documentation in entry 'root' to member definition 'md' and
5392// set the function declaration of the member to 'funcDecl'. If the boolean
5393// over_load is set the standard overload text is added.
5394
5395static void addMemberDocs(const Entry *root,
5396 MemberDefMutable *md, const QCString &funcDecl,
5397 const ArgumentList *al,
5398 bool over_load,
5399 TypeSpecifier spec
5400 )
5401{
5402 if (md==nullptr) return;
5403 AUTO_TRACE("scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' funcDecl='{}' mSpec={}",
5404 root->parent()->name,md->name(),md->argsString(),funcDecl,spec);
5405 if (!root->section.isDoc()) // @fn or @var does not need to specify the complete definition, so don't overwrite it
5406 {
5407 QCString fDecl=funcDecl;
5408 // strip extern specifier
5409 fDecl.stripPrefix("extern ");
5410 md->setDefinition(fDecl);
5411 }
5412 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,md);
5413 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
5414 ClassDefMutable *cd=md->getClassDefMutable();
5415 const NamespaceDef *nd=md->getNamespaceDef();
5416 QCString fullName;
5417 if (cd)
5418 fullName = cd->name();
5419 else if (nd)
5420 fullName = nd->name();
5421
5422 if (!fullName.isEmpty()) fullName+="::";
5423 fullName+=md->name();
5424 FileDef *rfd=root->fileDef();
5425
5426 // TODO determine scope based on root not md
5427 Definition *rscope = md->getOuterScope();
5428
5429 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md->argumentList();
5430 if (al)
5431 {
5432 ArgumentList mergedAl = *al;
5433 //printf("merging arguments (1) docs=%d\n",root->doc.isEmpty());
5434 mergeArguments(const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdAl),mergedAl,!root->doc.isEmpty());
5435 }
5436 else
5437 {
5438 if (
5439 matchArguments2( md->getOuterScope(), md->getFileDef(),const_cast<ArgumentList*>(&mdAl),
5440 rscope,rfd,&root->argList,
5441 TRUE, root->lang
5442 )
5443 )
5444 {
5445 //printf("merging arguments (2)\n");
5446 ArgumentList mergedArgList = root->argList;
5447 mergeArguments(const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdAl),mergedArgList,!root->doc.isEmpty());
5448 }
5449 }
5450 if (over_load) // the \overload keyword was used
5451 {
5452 QCString doc=getOverloadDocs();
5453 if (!root->doc.isEmpty())
5454 {
5455 doc+="<p>";
5456 doc+=root->doc;
5457 }
5458 md->setDocumentation(doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
5459 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
5460 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
5461 }
5462 else
5463 {
5464 //printf("overwrite!\n");
5465 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
5466 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
5467
5468 //printf("overwrite!\n");
5469 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
5470
5471 if (
5472 (md->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty() ||
5473 !root->parent()->name.isEmpty()
5474 ) && !root->inbodyDocs.isEmpty()
5475 )
5476 {
5477 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
5478 }
5479 }
5480
5481 //printf("initializer: '%s'(isEmpty=%d) '%s'(isEmpty=%d)\n",
5482 // qPrint(md->initializer()),md->initializer().isEmpty(),
5483 // qPrint(root->initializer),root->initializer.isEmpty()
5484 // );
5485 std::string rootInit = root->initializer.str();
5486 if (md->initializer().isEmpty() && !rootInit.empty())
5487 {
5488 //printf("setInitializer\n");
5489 md->setInitializer(rootInit.c_str());
5490 }
5491 if (md->requiresClause().isEmpty() && !root->req.isEmpty())
5492 {
5493 md->setRequiresClause(root->req);
5494 }
5495
5496 md->setMaxInitLines(root->initLines);
5497
5498 if (rfd)
5499 {
5500 if ((md->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && root->bodyLine!=-1)
5501 )
5502 {
5503 //printf("Setting new body segment [%d,%d]\n",root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
5504 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
5505 md->setBodyDef(rfd);
5506 }
5507
5508 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
5509 }
5510
5511 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,md);
5512 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
5513
5514 md->mergeMemberSpecifiers(spec);
5515 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
5516 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
5517 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md);
5518 if (cd) cd->insertUsedFile(rfd);
5519 //printf("root->mGrpId=%d\n",root->mGrpId);
5520 if (root->mGrpId!=-1)
5521 {
5522 if (md->getMemberGroupId()!=-1)
5523 {
5524 if (md->getMemberGroupId()!=root->mGrpId)
5525 {
5526 warn(
5527 root->fileName,root->startLine,
5528 "member %s belongs to two different groups. The second "
5529 "one found here will be ignored.",
5530 qPrint(md->name())
5531 );
5532 }
5533 }
5534 else // set group id
5535 {
5536 //printf("setMemberGroupId=%d md=%s\n",root->mGrpId,qPrint(md->name()));
5537 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
5538 }
5539 }
5540 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
5541}

5543//----------------------------------------------------------------------
5544// find a class definition given the scope name and (optionally) a
5545// template list specifier
5546
5547static const ClassDef *findClassDefinition(FileDef *fd,NamespaceDef *nd,
5548 const QCString &scopeName)
5549{
5550 SymbolResolver resolver(fd);
5551 const ClassDef *tcd = resolver.resolveClass(nd,scopeName,true,true);
5552 return tcd;
5553}
5554
5555//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5556// Returns TRUE, if the entry belongs to the group of the member definition,
5557// otherwise FALSE.
5558
5559static bool isEntryInGroupOfMember(const Entry *root,const MemberDef *md,bool allowNoGroup=false)
5560{
5561 const GroupDef *gd = md->getGroupDef();
5562 if (!gd)
5563 {
5564 return allowNoGroup;
5565 }
5566
5567 for (const auto &g : root->groups)
5568 {
5569 if (g.groupname == gd->name())
5570 {
5571 return true; // matching group
5572 }
5573 }
5574
5575 return false;
5576}
5577
5578//----------------------------------------------------------------------
5579// Adds the documentation contained in 'root' to a global function
5580// with name 'name' and argument list 'args' (for overloading) and
5581// function declaration 'decl' to the corresponding member definition.
5582
5583static bool findGlobalMember(const Entry *root,
5584 const QCString &namespaceName,
5585 const QCString &type,
5586 const QCString &name,
5587 const QCString &tempArg,
5588 const QCString &,
5589 const QCString &decl,
5590 TypeSpecifier /* spec */)
5591{
5592 AUTO_TRACE("namespace='{}' type='{}' name='{}' tempArg='{}' decl='{}'",namespaceName,type,name,tempArg,decl);
5593 QCString n=name;
5594 if (n.isEmpty()) return FALSE;
5595 if (n.find("::")!=-1) return FALSE; // skip undefined class members
5596 MemberName *mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(n+tempArg); // look in function dictionary
5597 if (mn==nullptr)
5598 {
5599 mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(n); // try without template arguments
5600 }
5601 if (mn) // function name defined
5602 {
5603 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Found symbol name");
5604 //int count=0;
5605 bool found=FALSE;
5606 for (const auto &md : *mn)
5607 {
5608 // If the entry has groups, then restrict the search to members which are
5609 // in one of the groups of the entry. If md is not associated with a group yet,
5610 // allow this documentation entry to add the group info.
5611 if (!root->groups.empty() && !isEntryInGroupOfMember(root, md.get(), true))
5612 {
5613 continue;
5614 }
5615
5616 const NamespaceDef *nd=nullptr;
5617 if (md->isAlias() && md->getOuterScope() &&
5618 md->getOuterScope()->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
5619 {
5620 nd = toNamespaceDef(md->getOuterScope());
5621 }
5622 else
5623 {
5624 nd = md->getNamespaceDef();
5625 }
5626
5627 // special case for strong enums
5628 int enumNamePos=0;
5629 if (nd && md->isEnumValue() && (enumNamePos=namespaceName.findRev("::"))!=-1)
5630 { // md part of a strong enum in a namespace?
5631 QCString enumName = namespaceName.mid(enumNamePos+2);
5632 if (namespaceName.left(enumNamePos)==nd->name())
5633 {
5634 MemberName *enumMn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(enumName);
5635 if (enumMn)
5636 {
5637 for (const auto &emd : *enumMn)
5638 {
5639 found = emd->isStrong() && md->getEnumScope()==emd.get();
5640 if (found)
5641 {
5642 addMemberDocs(root,toMemberDefMutable(md->resolveAlias()),decl,nullptr,FALSE,root->spec);
5643 break;
5644 }
5645 }
5646 }
5647 }
5648 if (found)
5649 {
5650 break;
5651 }
5652 }
5653 else if (nd==nullptr && md->isEnumValue()) // md part of global strong enum?
5654 {
5655 MemberName *enumMn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(namespaceName);
5656 if (enumMn)
5657 {
5658 for (const auto &emd : *enumMn)
5659 {
5660 found = emd->isStrong() && md->getEnumScope()==emd.get();
5661 if (found)
5662 {
5663 addMemberDocs(root,toMemberDefMutable(md->resolveAlias()),decl,nullptr,FALSE,root->spec);
5664 break;
5665 }
5666 }
5667 }
5668 }
5669
5670 const FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
5671 //printf("File %s\n",fd ? qPrint(fd->name()) : "<none>");
5672 LinkedRefMap<NamespaceDef> nl;
5673 if (fd)
5674 {
5675 nl = fd->getUsedNamespaces();
5676 }
5677 //printf("NamespaceList %p\n",nl);
5678
5679 // search in the list of namespaces that are imported via a
5680 // using declaration
5681 bool viaUsingDirective = nd && nl.find(nd->qualifiedName())!=nullptr;
5682
5683 if ((namespaceName.isEmpty() && nd==nullptr) || // not in a namespace
5684 (nd && nd->name()==namespaceName) || // or in the same namespace
5685 viaUsingDirective // member in 'using' namespace
5686 )
5687 {
5688 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Try to add member '{}' to scope '{}'",md->name(),namespaceName);
5689
5690 NamespaceDef *rnd = nullptr;
5691 if (!namespaceName.isEmpty()) rnd = Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(namespaceName);
5692
5693 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md.get()->argumentList();
5694 bool matching=
5695 (mdAl.empty() && root->argList.empty()) ||
5696 md->isVariable() || md->isTypedef() || /* in case of function pointers */
5697 matchArguments2(md->getOuterScope(),md.get()->getFileDef(),&mdAl,
5698 rnd ? rnd : Doxygen::globalScope,fd,&root->argList,
5699 FALSE,root->lang);
5700
5701 // for template members we need to check if the number of
5702 // template arguments is the same, otherwise we are dealing with
5703 // different functions.
5704 if (matching && !root->tArgLists.empty())
5705 {
5706 const ArgumentList &mdTempl = md->templateArguments();
5707 if (root->tArgLists.back().size()!=mdTempl.size())
5708 {
5709 matching=FALSE;
5710 }
5711 }
5712
5713 //printf("%s<->%s\n",
5714 // qPrint(argListToString(md->argumentList())),
5715 // qPrint(argListToString(root->argList)));
5716
5717 // For static members we also check if the comment block was found in
5718 // the same file. This is needed because static members with the same
5719 // name can be in different files. Thus it would be wrong to just
5720 // put the comment block at the first syntactically matching member. If
5721 // the comment block belongs to a group of the static member, then add
5722 // the documentation even if it is in a different file.
5723 if (matching && md->isStatic() &&
5724 md->getDefFileName()!=root->fileName &&
5725 mn->size()>1 &&
5726 !isEntryInGroupOfMember(root,md.get()))
5727 {
5728 matching = FALSE;
5729 }
5730
5731 // for template member we also need to check the return type and requires
5732 if (!md->templateArguments().empty() && !root->tArgLists.empty())
5733 {
5734 //printf("Comparing return types '%s'<->'%s'\n",
5735 // md->typeString(),type);
5736 if (md->templateArguments().size()!=root->tArgLists.back().size() ||
5737 md->typeString()!=type ||
5738 md->requiresClause()!=root->req)
5739 {
5740 //printf(" ---> no matching\n");
5741 matching = FALSE;
5742 }
5743 }
5744
5745 if (matching) // add docs to the member
5746 {
5747 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Match found");
5748 addMemberDocs(root,toMemberDefMutable(md->resolveAlias()),decl,&root->argList,FALSE,root->spec);
5749 found=TRUE;
5750 break;
5751 }
5752 }
5753 }
5754 if (!found && root->relatesType!=RelatesType::Duplicate && root->section.isFunction()) // no match
5755 {
5756 QCString fullFuncDecl=decl;
5757 if (!root->argList.empty()) fullFuncDecl+=argListToString(root->argList,TRUE);
5758 QCString warnMsg =
5759 QCString("no matching file member found for \n")+substitute(fullFuncDecl,"%","%%");
5760 if (mn->size()>0)
5761 {
5762 warnMsg+="\nPossible candidates:";
5763 for (const auto &md : *mn)
5764 {
5765 warnMsg+="\n '";
5766 warnMsg+=substitute(md->declaration(),"%","%%");
5767 warnMsg+="' " + warn_line(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine());
5768 }
5769 }
5770 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine, "%s", qPrint(warnMsg));
5771 }
5772 }
5773 else // got docs for an undefined member!
5774 {
5775 if (root->type!="friend class" &&
5776 root->type!="friend struct" &&
5777 root->type!="friend union" &&
5778 root->type!="friend" &&
5779 (!Config_getBool(TYPEDEF_HIDES_STRUCT) ||
5780 root->type.find("typedef ")==-1)
5781 )
5782 {
5783 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
5784 "documented symbol '%s' was not declared or defined.",qPrint(decl)
5785 );
5786 }
5787 }
5788 return TRUE;
5789}
5790
5791static bool isSpecialization(
5792 const ArgumentLists &srcTempArgLists,
5793 const ArgumentLists &dstTempArgLists
5794 )
5795{
5796 auto srcIt = srcTempArgLists.begin();
5797 auto dstIt = dstTempArgLists.begin();
5798 while (srcIt!=srcTempArgLists.end() && dstIt!=dstTempArgLists.end())
5799 {
5800 if ((*srcIt).size()!=(*dstIt).size()) return TRUE;
5801 ++srcIt;
5802 ++dstIt;
5803 }
5804 return FALSE;
5805}
5806
5807static bool scopeIsTemplate(const Definition *d)
5808{
5809 bool result=FALSE;
5810 if (d && d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
5811 {
5812 result = !(toClassDef(d))->templateArguments().empty() ||
5813 scopeIsTemplate(d->getOuterScope());
5814 }
5815 return result;
5816}
5817
5818static QCString substituteTemplatesInString(
5819 const ArgumentLists &srcTempArgLists,
5820 const ArgumentLists &dstTempArgLists,
5821 const std::string &src
5822 )
5823{
5824 std::string dst;
5825 static const reg::Ex re(R"(\a\w*)");
5826 reg::Iterator it(src,re);
5827 reg::Iterator end;
5828 //printf("type=%s\n",qPrint(sa->type));
5829 size_t p=0;
5830 for (; it!=end ; ++it) // for each word in srcType
5831 {
5832 const auto &match = *it;
5833 size_t i = match.position();
5834 size_t l = match.length();
5835 bool found=FALSE;
5836 dst+=src.substr(p,i-p);
5837 std::string name=match.str();
5838
5839 auto srcIt = srcTempArgLists.begin();
5840 auto dstIt = dstTempArgLists.begin();
5841 while (srcIt!=srcTempArgLists.end() && !found)
5842 {
5843 const ArgumentList *tdAli = nullptr;
5844 std::vector<Argument>::const_iterator tdaIt;
5845 if (dstIt!=dstTempArgLists.end())
5846 {
5847 tdAli = &(*dstIt);
5848 tdaIt = tdAli->begin();
5849 ++dstIt;
5850 }
5851
5852 const ArgumentList &tsaLi = *srcIt;
5853 for (auto tsaIt = tsaLi.begin(); tsaIt!=tsaLi.end() && !found; ++tsaIt)
5854 {
5855 Argument tsa = *tsaIt;
5856 const Argument *tda = nullptr;
5857 if (tdAli && tdaIt!=tdAli->end())
5858 {
5859 tda = &(*tdaIt);
5860 ++tdaIt;
5861 }
5862 //if (tda) printf("tsa=%s|%s tda=%s|%s\n",
5863 // qPrint(tsa.type),qPrint(tsa.name),
5864 // qPrint(tda->type),qPrint(tda->name));
5865 if (name==tsa.name.str())
5866 {
5867 if (tda && tda->name.isEmpty())
5868 {
5869 QCString tdaName = tda->name;
5870 QCString tdaType = tda->type;
5871 int vc=0;
5872 if (tdaType.startsWith("class ")) vc=6;
5873 else if (tdaType.startsWith("typename ")) vc=9;
5874 if (vc>0) // convert type=="class T" to type=="class" name=="T"
5875 {
5876 tdaName = tdaType.mid(vc);
5877 }
5878 if (!tdaName.isEmpty())
5879 {
5880 name=tdaName.str(); // substitute
5881 found=TRUE;
5882 }
5883 }
5884 }
5885 }
5886
5887 //printf(" srcList='%s' dstList='%s faList='%s'\n",
5888 // qPrint(argListToString(srclali.current())),
5889 // qPrint(argListToString(dstlali.current())),
5890 // funcTempArgList ? qPrint(argListToString(funcTempArgList)) : "<none>");
5891 ++srcIt;
5892 }
5893 dst+=name;
5894 p=i+l;
5895 }
5896 dst+=src.substr(p);
5897 //printf(" substituteTemplatesInString(%s)=%s\n",
5898 // qPrint(src),qPrint(dst));
5899 return QCString(dst);
5900}
5901
5902static void substituteTemplatesInArgList(
5903 const ArgumentLists &srcTempArgLists,
5904 const ArgumentLists &dstTempArgLists,
5905 const ArgumentList &src,
5906 ArgumentList &dst
5907 )
5908{
5909 auto dstIt = dst.begin();
5910 for (const Argument &sa : src)
5911 {
5912 QCString dstType = substituteTemplatesInString(srcTempArgLists,dstTempArgLists,sa.type.str());
5913 QCString dstArray = substituteTemplatesInString(srcTempArgLists,dstTempArgLists,sa.array.str());
5914 if (dstIt == dst.end())
5915 {
5916 Argument da = sa;
5917 da.type = dstType;
5918 da.array = dstArray;
5919 dst.push_back(da);
5920 dstIt = dst.end();
5921 }
5922 else
5923 {
5924 Argument da = *dstIt;
5925 da.type = dstType;
5926 da.array = dstArray;
5927 ++dstIt;
5928 }
5929 }
5930 dst.setConstSpecifier(src.constSpecifier());
5931 dst.setVolatileSpecifier(src.volatileSpecifier());
5932 dst.setPureSpecifier(src.pureSpecifier());
5933 dst.setTrailingReturnType(substituteTemplatesInString(
5934 srcTempArgLists,dstTempArgLists,
5935 src.trailingReturnType().str()));
5936 dst.setIsDeleted(src.isDeleted());
5937 dst.setRefQualifier(src.refQualifier());
5938 dst.setNoParameters(src.noParameters());
5939 //printf("substituteTemplatesInArgList: replacing %s with %s\n",
5940 // qPrint(argListToString(src)),qPrint(argListToString(dst))
5941 // );
5942}
5943
5944//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5945
5946static void addLocalObjCMethod(const Entry *root,
5947 const QCString &scopeName,
5948 const QCString &funcType,const QCString &funcName,const QCString &funcArgs,
5949 const QCString &exceptions,const QCString &funcDecl,
5950 TypeSpecifier spec)
5951{
5952 AUTO_TRACE();
5953 //printf("scopeName='%s' className='%s'\n",qPrint(scopeName),qPrint(className));
5954 ClassDefMutable *cd=nullptr;
5955 if (Config_getBool(EXTRACT_LOCAL_METHODS) && (cd=getClassMutable(scopeName)))
5956 {
5957 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Local objective C method '{}' scopeName='{}'",root->name,scopeName);
5958 auto md = createMemberDef(
5959 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
5960 funcType,funcName,funcArgs,exceptions,
5961 root->protection,root->virt,root->isStatic,Relationship::Member,
5962 MemberType::Function,ArgumentList(),root->argList,root->metaData);
5963 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
5964 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
5965 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
5966 mmd->setId(root->id);
5967 mmd->makeImplementationDetail();
5968 mmd->setMemberClass(cd);
5969 mmd->setDefinition(funcDecl);
5970 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
5971 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
5972 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
5973 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
5974 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
5975 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
5976 mmd->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
5977 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
5978 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
5979 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
5980 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
5981 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
5982 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
5983 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
5984 cd->insertMember(md.get());
5985 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
5986 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
5987
5988 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(root->name);
5989 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
5990 }
5991 else
5992 {
5993 // local objective C method found for class without interface
5994 }
5995}
5996
5997//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5998
5999static void addMemberFunction(const Entry *root,
6000 MemberName *mn,
6001 const QCString &scopeName,
6002 const QCString &namespaceName,
6003 const QCString &className,
6004 const QCString &funcTyp,
6005 const QCString &funcName,
6006 const QCString &funcArgs,
6007 const QCString &funcTempList,
6008 const QCString &exceptions,
6009 const QCString &type,
6010 const QCString &args,
6011 bool isFriend,
6012 TypeSpecifier spec,
6013 const QCString &relates,
6014 const QCString &funcDecl,
6015 bool overloaded,
6016 bool isFunc)
6017{
6018 AUTO_TRACE();
6019 QCString funcType = funcTyp;
6020 int count=0;
6021 int noMatchCount=0;
6022 bool memFound=FALSE;
6023 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
6024 {
6025 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
6026 if (md==nullptr) continue;
6027 ClassDefMutable *cd=md->getClassDefMutable();
6028 if (cd==nullptr) continue;
6029 //AUTO_TRACE_ADD("member definition found, scope needed='{}' scope='{}' args='{}' fileName='{}'",
6030 // scopeName, cd->name(), md->argsString(), root->fileName);
6031 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
6032 NamespaceDef *nd=nullptr;
6033 if (!namespaceName.isEmpty()) nd=getResolvedNamespace(namespaceName);
6034
6035 //printf("scopeName %s->%s\n",qPrint(scopeName),
6036 // qPrint(stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(scopeName,FALSE)));
6037
6038 // if the member we are searching for is an enum value that is part of
6039 // a "strong" enum, we need to look into the fields of the enum for a match
6040 int enumNamePos=0;
6041 if (md->isEnumValue() && (enumNamePos=className.findRev("::"))!=-1)
6042 {
6043 QCString enumName = className.mid(enumNamePos+2);
6044 QCString fullScope = className.left(enumNamePos);
6045 if (!namespaceName.isEmpty()) fullScope.prepend(namespaceName+"::");
6046 if (fullScope==cd->name())
6047 {
6048 MemberName *enumMn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(enumName);
6049 //printf("enumMn(%s)=%p\n",qPrint(className),(void*)enumMn);
6050 if (enumMn)
6051 {
6052 for (const auto &emd : *enumMn)
6053 {
6054 memFound = emd->isStrong() && md->getEnumScope()==emd.get();
6055 if (memFound)
6056 {
6057 addMemberDocs(root,md,funcDecl,nullptr,overloaded,spec);
6058 count++;
6059 }
6060 if (memFound) break;
6061 }
6062 }
6063 }
6064 }
6065 if (memFound) break;
6066
6067 const ClassDef *tcd=findClassDefinition(fd,nd,scopeName);
6068 if (tcd==nullptr && cd && stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(cd->name())==scopeName)
6069 {
6070 // don't be fooled by anonymous scopes
6071 tcd=cd;
6072 }
6073 //printf("Looking for %s inside nd=%s result=%p (%s) cd=%p\n",
6074 // qPrint(scopeName),nd?qPrint(nd->name()):"<none>",tcd,tcd?qPrint(tcd->name()):"",cd);
6075
6076 if (cd && tcd==cd) // member's classes match
6077 {
6078 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("class definition '{}' found",cd->name());
6079
6080 // get the template parameter lists found at the member declaration
6081 ArgumentLists declTemplArgs = cd->getTemplateParameterLists();
6082 const ArgumentList &templAl = md->templateArguments();
6083 if (!templAl.empty())
6084 {
6085 declTemplArgs.push_back(templAl);
6086 }
6087
6088 // get the template parameter lists found at the member definition
6089 const ArgumentLists &defTemplArgs = root->tArgLists;
6090 //printf("defTemplArgs=%p\n",defTemplArgs);
6091
6092 // do we replace the decl argument lists with the def argument lists?
6093 bool substDone=FALSE;
6094 ArgumentList argList;
6095
6096 /* substitute the occurrences of class template names in the
6097 * argument list before matching
6098 */
6099 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md->argumentList();
6100 if (declTemplArgs.size()>0 && declTemplArgs.size()==defTemplArgs.size())
6101 {
6102 /* the function definition has template arguments
6103 * and the class definition also has template arguments, so
6104 * we must substitute the template names of the class by that
6105 * of the function definition before matching.
6106 */
6107 substituteTemplatesInArgList(declTemplArgs,defTemplArgs,mdAl,argList);
6108
6109 substDone=TRUE;
6110 }
6111 else /* no template arguments, compare argument lists directly */
6112 {
6113 argList = mdAl;
6114 }
6115
6116 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("matching '{}'<=>'{}' className='{}' namespaceName='{}'",
6117 argListToString(argList,TRUE),argListToString(root->argList,TRUE),className,namespaceName);
6118
6119 bool matching=
6120 md->isVariable() || md->isTypedef() || // needed for function pointers
6121 matchArguments2(
6122 md->getClassDef(),md->getFileDef(),&argList,
6123 cd,fd,&root->argList,
6124 TRUE,root->lang);
6125
6126 if (md->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::ObjC && md->isVariable() && root->section.isFunction())
6127 {
6128 matching = FALSE; // don't match methods and attributes with the same name
6129 }
6130
6131 // for template member we also need to check the return type
6132 if (!md->templateArguments().empty() && !root->tArgLists.empty())
6133 {
6134 QCString memType = md->typeString();
6135 memType.stripPrefix("static "); // see bug700696
6136 funcType=substitute(stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(funcType,TRUE),
6137 className+"::",""); // see bug700693 & bug732594
6138 memType=substitute(stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(memType,TRUE),
6139 className+"::",""); // see bug758900
6140 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Comparing return types '{}'<->'{}' #args {}<->{}",
6141 md->typeString(),funcType,md->templateArguments().size(),root->tArgLists.back().size());
6142 if (md->templateArguments().size()!=root->tArgLists.back().size() || memType!=funcType)
6143 {
6144 //printf(" ---> no matching\n");
6145 matching = FALSE;
6146 }
6147 }
6148 else if (defTemplArgs.size()>declTemplArgs.size())
6149 {
6150 // avoid matching a non-template function in a template class against a
6151 // template function with the same name and parameters, see issue #10184
6152 substDone = false;
6153 matching = false;
6154 }
6155 bool rootIsUserDoc = root->section.isMemberDoc();
6156 bool classIsTemplate = scopeIsTemplate(md->getClassDef());
6157 bool mdIsTemplate = md->templateArguments().hasParameters();
6158 bool classOrMdIsTemplate = mdIsTemplate || classIsTemplate;
6159 bool rootIsTemplate = !root->tArgLists.empty();
6160 //printf("classIsTemplate=%d mdIsTemplate=%d rootIsTemplate=%d\n",classIsTemplate,mdIsTemplate,rootIsTemplate);
6161 if (!rootIsUserDoc && // don't check out-of-line @fn references, see bug722457
6162 (mdIsTemplate || rootIsTemplate) && // either md or root is a template
6163 ((classOrMdIsTemplate && !rootIsTemplate) || (!classOrMdIsTemplate && rootIsTemplate))
6164 )
6165 {
6166 // Method with template return type does not match method without return type
6167 // even if the parameters are the same. See also bug709052
6168 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Comparing return types: template v.s. non-template");
6169 matching = FALSE;
6170 }
6171
6172 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Match results of matchArguments2='{}' substDone='{}'",matching,substDone);
6173
6174 if (substDone) // found a new argument list
6175 {
6176 if (matching) // replace member's argument list
6177 {
6178 md->setDefinitionTemplateParameterLists(root->tArgLists);
6179 md->moveArgumentList(std::make_unique<ArgumentList>(argList));
6180 }
6181 else // no match
6182 {
6183 if (!funcTempList.isEmpty() &&
6184 isSpecialization(declTemplArgs,defTemplArgs))
6185 {
6186 // check if we are dealing with a partial template
6187 // specialization. In this case we add it to the class
6188 // even though the member arguments do not match.
6189
6190 addMethodToClass(root,cd,type,md->name(),args,isFriend,
6191 md->protection(),md->isStatic(),md->virtualness(),spec,relates);
6192 return;
6193 }
6194 }
6195 }
6196 if (matching)
6197 {
6198 addMemberDocs(root,md,funcDecl,nullptr,overloaded,spec);
6199 count++;
6200 memFound=TRUE;
6201 }
6202 }
6203 else if (cd && cd!=tcd) // we did find a class with the same name as cd
6204 // but in a different namespace
6205 {
6206 noMatchCount++;
6207 }
6208
6209 if (memFound) break;
6210 }
6211 if (count==0 && root->parent() && root->parent()->section.isObjcImpl())
6212 {
6213 addLocalObjCMethod(root,scopeName,funcType,funcName,funcArgs,exceptions,funcDecl,spec);
6214 return;
6215 }
6216 if (count==0 && !(isFriend && funcType=="class"))
6217 {
6218 int candidates=0;
6219 const ClassDef *ecd = nullptr, *ucd = nullptr;
6220 MemberDef *emd = nullptr, *umd = nullptr;
6221 //printf("Assume template class\n");
6222 for (const auto &md : *mn)
6223 {
6224 MemberDef *cmd=md.get();
6225 MemberDefMutable *cdmdm = toMemberDefMutable(cmd);
6226 ClassDefMutable *ccd=cdmdm ? cdmdm->getClassDefMutable() : nullptr;
6227 //printf("ccd->name()==%s className=%s\n",qPrint(ccd->name()),qPrint(className));
6228 if (ccd!=nullptr && rightScopeMatch(ccd->name(),className))
6229 {
6230 const ArgumentList &templAl = md->templateArguments();
6231 if (!root->tArgLists.empty() && !templAl.empty() &&
6232 root->tArgLists.back().size()<=templAl.size())
6233 {
6234 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("add template specialization");
6235 addMethodToClass(root,ccd,type,md->name(),args,isFriend,
6236 root->protection,root->isStatic,root->virt,spec,relates);
6237 return;
6238 }
6239 if (argListToString(md->argumentList(),FALSE,FALSE) ==
6240 argListToString(root->argList,FALSE,FALSE))
6241 { // exact argument list match -> remember
6242 ucd = ecd = ccd;
6243 umd = emd = cmd;
6244 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("new candidate className='{}' scope='{}' args='{}': exact match",
6245 className,ccd->name(),md->argsString());
6246 }
6247 else // arguments do not match, but member name and scope do -> remember
6248 {
6249 ucd = ccd;
6250 umd = cmd;
6251 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("new candidate className='{}' scope='{}' args='{}': no match",
6252 className,ccd->name(),md->argsString());
6253 }
6254 candidates++;
6255 }
6256 }
6257 bool strictProtoMatching = Config_getBool(STRICT_PROTO_MATCHING);
6258 if (!strictProtoMatching)
6259 {
6260 if (candidates==1 && ucd && umd)
6261 {
6262 // we didn't find an actual match on argument lists, but there is only 1 member with this
6263 // name in the same scope, so that has to be the one.
6264 addMemberDocs(root,toMemberDefMutable(umd),funcDecl,nullptr,overloaded,spec);
6265 return;
6266 }
6267 else if (candidates>1 && ecd && emd)
6268 {
6269 // we didn't find a unique match using type resolution,
6270 // but one of the matches has the exact same signature so
6271 // we take that one.
6272 addMemberDocs(root,toMemberDefMutable(emd),funcDecl,nullptr,overloaded,spec);
6273 return;
6274 }
6275 }
6276
6277 QCString warnMsg = "no ";
6278 if (noMatchCount>1) warnMsg+="uniquely ";
6279 warnMsg+="matching class member found for \n";
6280
6281 for (const ArgumentList &al : root->tArgLists)
6282 {
6283 warnMsg+=" template ";
6284 warnMsg+=tempArgListToString(al,root->lang);
6285 warnMsg+='\n';
6286 }
6287
6288 QCString fullFuncDecl=funcDecl;
6289 if (isFunc) fullFuncDecl+=argListToString(root->argList,TRUE);
6290
6291 warnMsg+=" ";
6292 warnMsg+=fullFuncDecl;
6293
6294 if (candidates>0 || noMatchCount>=1)
6295 {
6296 warnMsg+="\nPossible candidates:";
6297
6298 NamespaceDef *nd=nullptr;
6299 if (!namespaceName.isEmpty()) nd=getResolvedNamespace(namespaceName);
6300 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
6301
6302 for (const auto &md : *mn)
6303 {
6304 const ClassDef *cd=md->getClassDef();
6305 const ClassDef *tcd=findClassDefinition(fd,nd,scopeName);
6306 if (tcd==nullptr && cd && stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(cd->name())==scopeName)
6307 {
6308 // don't be fooled by anonymous scopes
6309 tcd=cd;
6310 }
6311 if (cd!=nullptr && (rightScopeMatch(cd->name(),className) || (cd!=tcd)))
6312 {
6313 warnMsg+='\n';
6314 const ArgumentList &templAl = md->templateArguments();
6315 warnMsg+=" '";
6316 if (templAl.hasParameters())
6317 {
6318 warnMsg+="template ";
6319 warnMsg+=tempArgListToString(templAl,root->lang);
6320 warnMsg+='\n';
6321 warnMsg+=" ";
6322 }
6323 if (!md->typeString().isEmpty())
6324 {
6325 warnMsg+=md->typeString();
6326 warnMsg+=' ';
6327 }
6328 QCString qScope = cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
6329 if (!qScope.isEmpty())
6330 warnMsg+=qScope+"::"+md->name();
6331 warnMsg+=md->argsString();
6332 warnMsg+="' " + warn_line(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine());
6333 }
6334 }
6335 }
6336 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,"%s",qPrint(warnMsg));
6337 }
6338}
6339
6340//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6341
6342static void addMemberSpecialization(const Entry *root,
6343 MemberName *mn,
6344 ClassDefMutable *cd,
6345 const QCString &funcType,
6346 const QCString &funcName,
6347 const QCString &funcArgs,
6348 const QCString &funcDecl,
6349 const QCString &exceptions,
6350 TypeSpecifier spec
6351 )
6352{
6353 AUTO_TRACE("funcType={} funcName={} funcArgs={} funcDecl={} spec={}",funcType,funcName,funcArgs,funcDecl,spec);
6354 MemberDef *declMd=nullptr;
6355 for (const auto &md : *mn)
6356 {
6357 if (md->getClassDef()==cd)
6358 {
6359 // TODO: we should probably also check for matching arguments
6360 declMd = md.get();
6361 break;
6362 }
6363 }
6364 MemberType mtype=MemberType::Function;
6365 ArgumentList tArgList;
6366 // getTemplateArgumentsFromName(cd->name()+"::"+funcName,root->tArgLists);
6367 auto md = createMemberDef(
6368 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
6369 funcType,funcName,funcArgs,exceptions,
6370 declMd ? declMd->protection() : root->protection,
6371 root->virt,root->isStatic,Relationship::Member,
6372 mtype,tArgList,root->argList,root->metaData);
6373 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
6374 //printf("new specialized member %s args='%s'\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(funcArgs));
6375 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
6376 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
6377 mmd->setId(root->id);
6378 mmd->setMemberClass(cd);
6379 mmd->setTemplateSpecialization(TRUE);
6380 mmd->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
6381 mmd->setDefinition(funcDecl);
6382 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
6383 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
6384 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
6385 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
6386 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
6387 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
6388 mmd->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
6389 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
6390 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
6391 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
6392 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
6393 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
6394 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
6395 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
6396 cd->insertMember(md.get());
6397 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
6398
6399 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
6400}
6401
6402//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6403
6404static void addOverloaded(const Entry *root,MemberName *mn,
6405 const QCString &funcType,const QCString &funcName,const QCString &funcArgs,
6406 const QCString &funcDecl,const QCString &exceptions,TypeSpecifier spec)
6407{
6408 // for unique overloaded member we allow the class to be
6409 // omitted, this is to be Qt compatible. Using this should
6410 // however be avoided, because it is error prone
6411 bool sameClass=false;
6412 if (mn->size()>0)
6413 {
6414 // check if all members with the same name are also in the same class
6415 sameClass = std::equal(mn->begin()+1,mn->end(),mn->begin(),
6416 [](const auto &md1,const auto &md2)
6417 { return md1->getClassDef()->name()==md2->getClassDef()->name(); });
6418 }
6419 if (sameClass)
6420 {
6421 MemberDefMutable *mdm = toMemberDefMutable(mn->front().get());
6422 ClassDefMutable *cd = mdm ? mdm->getClassDefMutable() : nullptr;
6423 if (cd==nullptr) return;
6424
6425 MemberType mtype = MemberType::Function;
6426 if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Signal) mtype=MemberType::Signal;
6427 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Slot) mtype=MemberType::Slot;
6428 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::DCOP) mtype=MemberType::DCOP;
6429
6430 // new overloaded member function
6431 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> tArgList =
6432 getTemplateArgumentsFromName(cd->name()+"::"+funcName,root->tArgLists);
6433 //printf("new related member %s args='%s'\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(funcArgs));
6434 auto md = createMemberDef(
6435 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
6436 funcType,funcName,funcArgs,exceptions,
6437 root->protection,root->virt,root->isStatic,Relationship::Related,
6438 mtype,tArgList ? *tArgList : ArgumentList(),root->argList,root->metaData);
6439 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
6440 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
6441 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
6442 mmd->setId(root->id);
6443 mmd->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
6444 mmd->setMemberClass(cd);
6445 mmd->setDefinition(funcDecl);
6446 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
6447 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
6448 QCString doc=getOverloadDocs();
6449 doc+="<p>";
6450 doc+=root->doc;
6451 mmd->setDocumentation(doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
6452 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
6453 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
6454 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
6455 mmd->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
6456 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
6457 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
6458 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
6459 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
6460 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
6461 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
6462 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
6463 cd->insertMember(md.get());
6464 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
6465 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
6466
6467 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
6468 }
6469}
6470
6471static void insertMemberAlias(Definition *outerScope,const MemberDef *md)
6472{
6473 if (outerScope && outerScope!=Doxygen::globalScope)
6474 {
6475 auto aliasMd = createMemberDefAlias(outerScope,md);
6476 if (outerScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
6477 {
6478 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(outerScope);
6479 if (cdm)
6480 {
6481 cdm->insertMember(aliasMd.get());
6482 }
6483 }
6484 else if (outerScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
6485 {
6486 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(outerScope);
6487 if (ndm)
6488 {
6489 ndm->insertMember(aliasMd.get());
6490 }
6491 }
6492 else if (outerScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile)
6493 {
6494 toFileDef(outerScope)->insertMember(aliasMd.get());
6495 }
6496 if (aliasMd)
6497 {
6498 Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(md->name())->push_back(std::move(aliasMd));
6499 }
6500 }
6501}
6502
6503//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6504
6505/*! This function tries to find a member (in a documented class/file/namespace)
6506 * that corresponds to the function/variable declaration given in \a funcDecl.
6507 *
6508 * The boolean \a overloaded is used to specify whether or not a standard
6509 * overload documentation line should be generated.
6510 *
6511 * The boolean \a isFunc is a hint that indicates that this is a function
6512 * instead of a variable or typedef.
6513 */
6514static void findMember(const Entry *root,
6515 const QCString &relates,
6516 const QCString &type,
6517 const QCString &args,
6518 QCString funcDecl,
6519 bool overloaded,
6520 bool isFunc
6521 )
6522{
6523 AUTO_TRACE("root='{}' funcDecl='{}' related='{}' overload={} isFunc={} mGrpId={} #tArgList={} spec={} lang={}",
6524 root->name, funcDecl, relates, overloaded, isFunc, root->mGrpId, root->tArgLists.size(),
6525 root->spec, root->lang);
6526
6527 QCString scopeName;
6528 QCString className;
6529 QCString namespaceName;
6530 QCString funcType;
6531 QCString funcName;
6532 QCString funcArgs;
6533 QCString funcTempList;
6534 QCString exceptions;
6535 QCString funcSpec;
6536 bool isRelated=false;
6537 bool isMemberOf=false;
6538 bool isFriend=false;
6539 bool done=false;
6540 TypeSpecifier spec = root->spec;
6541 while (!done)
6542 {
6543 done=true;
6544 if (funcDecl.stripPrefix("friend ")) // treat friends as related members
6545 {
6546 isFriend=true;
6547 done=false;
6548 }
6549 if (funcDecl.stripPrefix("inline "))
6550 {
6551 spec.setInline(true);
6552 done=false;
6553 }
6554 if (funcDecl.stripPrefix("explicit "))
6555 {
6556 spec.setExplicit(true);
6557 done=false;
6558 }
6559 if (funcDecl.stripPrefix("mutable "))
6560 {
6561 spec.setMutable(true);
6562 done=false;
6563 }
6564 if (funcDecl.stripPrefix("virtual "))
6565 {
6566 done=false;
6567 }
6568 }
6569
6570 // delete any ; from the function declaration
6571 int sep=0;
6572 while ((sep=funcDecl.find(';'))!=-1)
6573 {
6574 funcDecl=(funcDecl.left(sep)+funcDecl.right(funcDecl.length()-sep-1)).stripWhiteSpace();
6575 }
6576
6577 // make sure the first character is a space to simplify searching.
6578 if (!funcDecl.isEmpty() && funcDecl[0]!=' ') funcDecl.prepend(" ");
6579
6580 // remove some superfluous spaces
6581 funcDecl= substitute(
6582 substitute(
6583 substitute(funcDecl,"~ ","~"),
6584 ":: ","::"
6585 ),
6586 " ::","::"
6587 ).stripWhiteSpace();
6588
6589 //printf("funcDecl='%s'\n",qPrint(funcDecl));
6590 if (isFriend && funcDecl.startsWith("class "))
6591 {
6592 //printf("friend class\n");
6593 funcDecl=funcDecl.right(funcDecl.length()-6);
6594 funcName = funcDecl;
6595 }
6596 else if (isFriend && funcDecl.startsWith("struct "))
6597 {
6598 funcDecl=funcDecl.right(funcDecl.length()-7);
6599 funcName = funcDecl;
6600 }
6601 else
6602 {
6603 // extract information from the declarations
6604 parseFuncDecl(funcDecl,root->lang,scopeName,funcType,funcName,
6605 funcArgs,funcTempList,exceptions
6606 );
6607 }
6608
6609 // the class name can also be a namespace name, we decide this later.
6610 // if a related class name is specified and the class name could
6611 // not be derived from the function declaration, then use the
6612 // related field.
6613 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("scopeName='{}' className='{}' namespaceName='{}' funcType='{}' funcName='{}' funcArgs='{}'",
6614 scopeName,className,namespaceName,funcType,funcName,funcArgs);
6615 if (!relates.isEmpty())
6616 { // related member, prefix user specified scope
6617 isRelated=TRUE;
6618 isMemberOf=(root->relatesType == RelatesType::MemberOf);
6619 if (getClass(relates)==nullptr && !scopeName.isEmpty())
6620 {
6621 scopeName= mergeScopes(scopeName,relates);
6622 }
6623 else
6624 {
6625 scopeName = relates;
6626 }
6627 }
6628
6629 if (relates.isEmpty() && root->parent() &&
6630 (root->parent()->section.isScope() || root->parent()->section.isObjcImpl()) &&
6631 !root->parent()->name.isEmpty()) // see if we can combine scopeName
6632 // with the scope in which it was found
6633 {
6634 QCString joinedName = root->parent()->name+"::"+scopeName;
6635 if (!scopeName.isEmpty() &&
6636 (getClass(joinedName) || Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(joinedName)))
6637 {
6638 scopeName = joinedName;
6639 }
6640 else
6641 {
6642 scopeName = mergeScopes(root->parent()->name,scopeName);
6643 }
6644 }
6645 else // see if we can prefix a namespace or class that is used from the file
6646 {
6647 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
6648 if (fd)
6649 {
6650 for (const auto &fnd : fd->getUsedNamespaces())
6651 {
6652 QCString joinedName = fnd->name()+"::"+scopeName;
6653 if (Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(joinedName))
6654 {
6655 scopeName=joinedName;
6656 break;
6657 }
6658 }
6659 }
6660 }
6661 scopeName=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(
6662 removeRedundantWhiteSpace(scopeName),false,&funcSpec,QCString(),false);
6663
6664 // funcSpec contains the last template specifiers of the given scope.
6665 // If this method does not have any template arguments or they are
6666 // empty while funcSpec is not empty we assume this is a
6667 // specialization of a method. If not, we clear the funcSpec and treat
6668 // this as a normal method of a template class.
6669 if (!(root->tArgLists.size()>0 &&
