6670 root->tArgLists.front().size()==0
6671 )
6672 )
6673 {
6674 funcSpec.clear();
6675 }
6676
6677 // split scope into a namespace and a class part
6678 extractNamespaceName(scopeName,className,namespaceName,TRUE);
6679 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("scopeName='{}' className='{}' namespaceName='{}'",scopeName,className,namespaceName);
6680
6681 //namespaceName=removeAnonymousScopes(namespaceName);
6682 if (namespaceName.find('@')!=-1) return; // skip stuff in anonymous namespace...
6683
6684 //printf("namespaceName='%s' className='%s'\n",qPrint(namespaceName),qPrint(className));
6685 // merge class and namespace scopes again
6686 scopeName.clear();
6687 if (!namespaceName.isEmpty())
6688 {
6689 if (className.isEmpty())
6690 {
6691 scopeName=namespaceName;
6692 }
6693 else if (!relates.isEmpty() || // relates command with explicit scope
6694 !getClass(className)) // class name only exists in a namespace
6695 {
6696 scopeName=namespaceName+"::"+className;
6697 }
6698 else
6699 {
6700 scopeName=className;
6701 }
6702 }
6703 else if (!className.isEmpty())
6704 {
6705 scopeName=className;
6706 }
6707 //printf("new scope='%s'\n",qPrint(scopeName));
6708
6709 QCString tempScopeName=scopeName;
6710 ClassDefMutable *cd=getClassMutable(scopeName);
6711 if (cd)
6712 {
6713 if (funcSpec.isEmpty())
6714 {
6715 uint32_t argListIndex=0;
6716 tempScopeName=cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters(&root->tArgLists,&argListIndex);
6717 }
6718 else
6719 {
6720 tempScopeName=scopeName+funcSpec;
6721 }
6722 }
6723 //printf("scopeName=%s cd=%p root->tArgLists=%p result=%s\n",
6724 // qPrint(scopeName),cd,root->tArgLists,qPrint(tempScopeName));
6725
6726 //printf("scopeName='%s' className='%s'\n",qPrint(scopeName),qPrint(className));
6727 // rebuild the function declaration (needed to get the scope right).
6728 if (!scopeName.isEmpty() && !isRelated && !isFriend && !Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
6729 {
6730 if (!funcType.isEmpty())
6731 {
6732 if (isFunc) // a function -> we use argList for the arguments
6733 {
6734 funcDecl=funcType+" "+tempScopeName+"::"+funcName+funcTempList;
6735 }
6736 else
6737 {
6738 funcDecl=funcType+" "+tempScopeName+"::"+funcName+funcArgs;
6739 }
6740 }
6741 else
6742 {
6743 if (isFunc) // a function => we use argList for the arguments
6744 {
6745 funcDecl=tempScopeName+"::"+funcName+funcTempList;
6746 }
6747 else // variable => add 'argument' list
6748 {
6749 funcDecl=tempScopeName+"::"+funcName+funcArgs;
6750 }
6751 }
6752 }
6753 else // build declaration without scope
6754 {
6755 if (!funcType.isEmpty()) // but with a type
6756 {
6757 if (isFunc) // function => omit argument list
6758 {
6759 funcDecl=funcType+" "+funcName+funcTempList;
6760 }
6761 else // variable => add 'argument' list
6762 {
6763 funcDecl=funcType+" "+funcName+funcArgs;
6764 }
6765 }
6766 else // no type
6767 {
6768 if (isFunc)
6769 {
6770 funcDecl=funcName+funcTempList;
6771 }
6772 else
6773 {
6774 funcDecl=funcName+funcArgs;
6775 }
6776 }
6777 }
6778
6779 if (funcType=="template class" && !funcTempList.isEmpty())
6780 return; // ignore explicit template instantiations
6781
6782 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Parse results: namespaceName='{}' className=`{}` funcType='{}' funcSpec='{}' "
6783 " funcName='{}' funcArgs='{}' funcTempList='{}' funcDecl='{}' relates='{}'"
6784 " exceptions='{}' isRelated={} isMemberOf={} isFriend={} isFunc={}",
6785 namespaceName, className, funcType, funcSpec,
6786 funcName, funcArgs, funcTempList, funcDecl, relates,
6787 exceptions, isRelated, isMemberOf, isFriend, isFunc);
6788
6789 if (!funcName.isEmpty()) // function name is valid
6790 {
6791 // check if 'className' is actually a scoped enum, in which case we need to
6792 // process it as a global, see issue #6471
6793 bool strongEnum = false;
6794 MemberName *mn=nullptr;
6795 if (!className.isEmpty() && (mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(className)))
6796 {
6797 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
6798 {
6799 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
6800 Definition *mdScope = nullptr;
6801 if (md && md->isEnumerate() && md->isStrong() && (mdScope=md->getOuterScope()) &&
6802 // need filter for the correct scope, see issue #9668
6803 ((namespaceName.isEmpty() && mdScope==Doxygen::globalScope) || (mdScope->name()==namespaceName)))
6804 {
6805 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("'{}' is a strong enum! (namespace={} md->getOuterScope()->name()={})",md->name(),namespaceName,md->getOuterScope()->name());
6806 strongEnum = true;
6807 // pass the scope name name as a 'namespace' to the findGlobalMember function
6808 if (!namespaceName.isEmpty())
6809 {
6810 namespaceName+="::"+className;
6811 }
6812 else
6813 {
6814 namespaceName=className;
6815 }
6816 }
6817 }
6818 }
6819
6820 if (funcName.startsWith("operator ")) // strip class scope from cast operator
6821 {
6822 funcName = substitute(funcName,className+"::","");
6823 }
6824 mn = nullptr;
6825 if (!funcTempList.isEmpty()) // try with member specialization
6826 {
6827 mn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(funcName+funcTempList);
6828 }
6829 if (mn==nullptr) // try without specialization
6830 {
6831 mn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(funcName);
6832 }
6833 if (!isRelated && !strongEnum && mn) // function name already found
6834 {
6835 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("member name exists ({} members with this name)",mn->size());
6836 if (!className.isEmpty()) // class name is valid
6837 {
6838 if (funcSpec.isEmpty()) // not a member specialization
6839 {
6840 addMemberFunction(root,mn,scopeName,namespaceName,className,funcType,funcName,
6841 funcArgs,funcTempList,exceptions,
6842 type,args,isFriend,spec,relates,funcDecl,overloaded,isFunc);
6843 }
6844 else if (cd) // member specialization
6845 {
6846 addMemberSpecialization(root,mn,cd,funcType,funcName,funcArgs,funcDecl,exceptions,spec);
6847 }
6848 else
6849 {
6850 //printf("*** Specialized member %s of unknown scope %s%s found!\n",
6851 // qPrint(scopeName),qPrint(funcName),qPrint(funcArgs));
6852 }
6853 }
6854 else if (overloaded) // check if the function belongs to only one class
6855 {
6856 addOverloaded(root,mn,funcType,funcName,funcArgs,funcDecl,exceptions,spec);
6857 }
6858 else // unrelated function with the same name as a member
6859 {
6860 if (!findGlobalMember(root,namespaceName,funcType,funcName,funcTempList,funcArgs,funcDecl,spec))
6861 {
6862 QCString fullFuncDecl=funcDecl;
6863 if (isFunc) fullFuncDecl+=argListToString(root->argList,TRUE);
6864 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
6865 "Cannot determine class for function\n%s",
6866 qPrint(fullFuncDecl)
6867 );
6868 }
6869 }
6870 }
6871 else if (isRelated && !relates.isEmpty())
6872 {
6873 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("related function scopeName='{}' className='{}'",scopeName,className);
6874 if (className.isEmpty()) className=relates;
6875 //printf("scopeName='%s' className='%s'\n",qPrint(scopeName),qPrint(className));
6876 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scopeName)))
6877 {
6878 bool newMember=TRUE; // assume we have a new member
6879 MemberDefMutable *mdDefine=nullptr;
6880 {
6881 mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(funcName);
6882 if (mn)
6883 {
6884 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
6885 {
6886 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
6887 if (md && md->isDefine())
6888 {
6889 mdDefine = md;
6890 break;
6891 }
6892 }
6893 }
6894 }
6895
6896 if (mdDefine) // macro definition is already created by the preprocessor and inserted as a file member
6897 {
6898 //printf("moving #define %s into class %s\n",qPrint(mdDefine->name()),qPrint(cd->name()));
6899
6900 // take mdDefine from the Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap (without deleting the data)
6901 auto mdDefineTaken = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->take(funcName,mdDefine);
6902 // insert it as a class member
6903 if ((mn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(funcName))==nullptr)
6904 {
6905 mn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(funcName);
6906 }
6907
6908 if (mdDefine->getFileDef())
6909 {
6910 mdDefine->getFileDef()->removeMember(mdDefine);
6911 }
6912 mdDefine->makeRelated();
6913 mdDefine->setMemberClass(cd);
6914 mdDefine->moveTo(cd);
6915 cd->insertMember(mdDefine);
6916 // also insert the member as an alias in the parent's scope, so it can be referenced also without cd's scope
6917 insertMemberAlias(cd->getOuterScope(),mdDefine);
6918 mn->push_back(std::move(mdDefineTaken));
6919 }
6920 else // normal member, needs to be created and added to the class
6921 {
6922 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
6923
6924 if ((mn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(funcName))==nullptr)
6925 {
6926 mn=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(funcName);
6927 }
6928 else
6929 {
6930 // see if we got another member with matching arguments
6931 MemberDefMutable *rmd_found = nullptr;
6932 for (const auto &irmd : *mn)
6933 {
6934 MemberDefMutable *rmd = toMemberDefMutable(irmd.get());
6935 if (rmd)
6936 {
6937 const ArgumentList &rmdAl = rmd->argumentList();
6938
6939 newMember=
6940 className!=rmd->getOuterScope()->name() ||
6941 !matchArguments2(rmd->getOuterScope(),rmd->getFileDef(),&rmdAl,
6942 cd,fd,&root->argList,
6943 TRUE,root->lang);
6944 if (!newMember)
6945 {
6946 rmd_found = rmd;
6947 }
6948 }
6949 }
6950 if (rmd_found) // member already exists as rmd -> add docs
6951 {
6952 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("addMemberDocs for related member {}",root->name);
6953 addMemberDocs(root,rmd_found,funcDecl,nullptr,overloaded,spec);
6954 newMember=false;
6955 }
6956 }
6957
6958 if (newMember) // need to create a new member
6959 {
6960 MemberType mtype = MemberType::Function;
6961 switch (root->mtype)
6962 {
6963 case MethodTypes::Method: mtype = MemberType::Function; break;
6964 case MethodTypes::Signal: mtype = MemberType::Signal; break;
6965 case MethodTypes::Slot: mtype = MemberType::Slot; break;
6966 case MethodTypes::DCOP: mtype = MemberType::DCOP; break;
6967 case MethodTypes::Property: mtype = MemberType::Property; break;
6968 case MethodTypes::Event: mtype = MemberType::Event; break;
6969 }
6970
6971 //printf("New related name '%s' '%d'\n",qPrint(funcName),
6972 // root->argList ? (int)root->argList->count() : -1);
6973
6974 // first note that we pass:
6975 // (root->tArgLists ? root->tArgLists->last() : nullptr)
6976 // for the template arguments for the new "member."
6977 // this accurately reflects the template arguments of
6978 // the related function, which don't have to do with
6979 // those of the related class.
6980 auto md = createMemberDef(
6981 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
6982 funcType,funcName,funcArgs,exceptions,
6983 root->protection,root->virt,
6984 root->isStatic,
6985 isMemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign : Relationship::Related,
6986 mtype,
6987 (!root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList()),
6988 funcArgs.isEmpty() ? ArgumentList() : root->argList,
6989 root->metaData);
6990 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
6991
6992 // also insert the member as an alias in the parent's scope, so it can be referenced also without cd's scope
6993 insertMemberAlias(cd->getOuterScope(),md.get());
6994
6995 // we still have the problem that
6996 // MemberDef::writeDocumentation() in memberdef.cpp
6997 // writes the template argument list for the class,
6998 // as if this member is a member of the class.
6999 // fortunately, MemberDef::writeDocumentation() has
7000 // a special mechanism that allows us to totally
7001 // override the set of template argument lists that
7002 // are printed. We use that and set it to the
7003 // template argument lists of the related function.
7004 //
7005 mmd->setDefinitionTemplateParameterLists(root->tArgLists);
7006
7007 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
7008
7009 //printf("Related member name='%s' decl='%s' bodyLine='%d'\n",
7010 // qPrint(funcName),qPrint(funcDecl),root->bodyLine);
7011
7012 // try to find the matching line number of the body from the
7013 // global function list
7014 bool found=FALSE;
7015 if (root->bodyLine==-1)
7016 {
7017 MemberName *rmn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(funcName);
7018 if (rmn)
7019 {
7020 const MemberDefMutable *rmd_found=nullptr;
7021 for (const auto &irmd : *rmn)
7022 {
7023 MemberDefMutable *rmd = toMemberDefMutable(irmd.get());
7024 if (rmd)
7025 {
7026 const ArgumentList &rmdAl = rmd->argumentList();
7027 // check for matching argument lists
7028 if (
7029 matchArguments2(rmd->getOuterScope(),rmd->getFileDef(),&rmdAl,
7030 cd,fd,&root->argList,
7031 TRUE,root->lang)
7032 )
7033 {
7034 found=TRUE;
7035 rmd_found = rmd;
7036 break;
7037 }
7038 }
7039 }
7040 if (rmd_found) // member found -> copy line number info
7041 {
7042 mmd->setBodySegment(rmd_found->getDefLine(),rmd_found->getStartBodyLine(),rmd_found->getEndBodyLine());
7043 mmd->setBodyDef(rmd_found->getBodyDef());
7044 //md->setBodyMember(rmd);
7045 }
7046 }
7047 }
7048 if (!found) // line number could not be found or is available in this
7049 // entry
7050 {
7051 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
7052 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
7053 }
7054
7055 //if (root->mGrpId!=-1)
7056 //{
7057 // md->setMemberGroup(memberGroupDict[root->mGrpId]);
7058 //}
7059 mmd->setMemberClass(cd);
7060 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
7061 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
7062 mmd->setDefinition(funcDecl);
7063 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
7064 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
7065 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
7066 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
7067 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
7068 mmd->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
7069 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
7070 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
7071 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
7072 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
7073 mmd->setId(root->id);
7074 //md->setMemberDefTemplateArguments(root->mtArgList);
7075 cd->insertMember(md.get());
7076 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
7077 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
7078 if (root->relatesType==RelatesType::Duplicate) mmd->setRelatedAlso(cd);
7079 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
7080 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md.get());
7081 //printf("Adding member=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()));
7082 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
7083 }
7084 if (root->relatesType==RelatesType::Duplicate)
7085 {
7086 if (!findGlobalMember(root,namespaceName,funcType,funcName,funcTempList,funcArgs,funcDecl,spec))
7087 {
7088 QCString fullFuncDecl=funcDecl;
7089 if (isFunc) fullFuncDecl+=argListToString(root->argList,TRUE);
7090 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
7091 "Cannot determine file/namespace for relatedalso function\n%s",
7092 qPrint(fullFuncDecl)
7093 );
7094 }
7095 }
7096 }
7097 }
7098 else
7099 {
7100 warn_undoc(root->fileName,root->startLine,
7101 "class '%s' for related function '%s' is not "
7102 "documented.",
7103 qPrint(className),qPrint(funcName)
7104 );
7105 }
7106 }
7107 else if (root->parent() && root->parent()->section.isObjcImpl())
7108 {
7109 addLocalObjCMethod(root,scopeName,funcType,funcName,funcArgs,exceptions,funcDecl,spec);
7110 }
7111 else // unrelated not overloaded member found
7112 {
7113 bool globMem = findGlobalMember(root,namespaceName,funcType,funcName,funcTempList,funcArgs,funcDecl,spec);
7114 if (className.isEmpty() && !globMem)
7115 {
7116 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
7117 "class for member '%s' cannot "
7118 "be found.", qPrint(funcName)
7119 );
7120 }
7121 else if (!className.isEmpty() && !globMem)
7122 {
7123 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
7124 "member '%s' of class '%s' cannot be found",
7125 qPrint(funcName),qPrint(className));
7126 }
7127 }
7128 }
7129 else
7130 {
7131 // this should not be called
7132 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
7133 "member with no name found.");
7134 }
7135 return;
7136}
7137
7138//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7139// find the members corresponding to the different documentation blocks
7140// that are extracted from the sources.
7141
7142static void filterMemberDocumentation(const Entry *root,const QCString &relates)
7143{
7144 AUTO_TRACE("root->type='{}' root->inside='{}' root->name='{}' root->args='{}' section={} root->spec={} root->mGrpId={}",
7145 root->type,root->inside,root->name,root->args,root->section,root->spec,root->mGrpId);
7146 //printf("root->parent()->name=%s\n",qPrint(root->parent()->name));
7147 bool isFunc=TRUE;
7148
7149 QCString type = root->type;
7150 QCString args = root->args;
7151 int i=-1, l=0;
7152 if ( // detect func variable/typedef to func ptr
7153 (i=findFunctionPtr(type.str(),root->lang,&l))!=-1
7154 )
7155 {
7156 //printf("Fixing function pointer!\n");
7157 // fix type and argument
7158 args.prepend(type.right(type.length()-i-l));
7159 type=type.left(i+l);
7160 //printf("Results type=%s,name=%s,args=%s\n",qPrint(type),qPrint(root->name),qPrint(args));
7161 isFunc=FALSE;
7162 }
7163 else if ((type.startsWith("typedef ") && args.find('(')!=-1))
7164 // detect function types marked as functions
7165 {
7166 isFunc=FALSE;
7167 }
7168
7169 //printf("Member %s isFunc=%d\n",qPrint(root->name),isFunc);
7170 if (root->section.isMemberDoc())
7171 {
7172 //printf("Documentation for inline member '%s' found args='%s'\n",
7173 // qPrint(root->name),qPrint(args));
7174 //if (relates.length()) printf(" Relates %s\n",qPrint(relates));
7175 if (type.isEmpty())
7176 {
7177 findMember(root,
7178 relates,
7179 type,
7180 args,
7181 root->name + args + root->exception,
7182 FALSE,
7183 isFunc);
7184 }
7185 else
7186 {
7187 findMember(root,
7188 relates,
7189 type,
7190 args,
7191 type + " " + root->name + args + root->exception,
7192 FALSE,
7193 isFunc);
7194 }
7195 }
7196 else if (root->section.isOverloadDoc())
7197 {
7198 //printf("Overloaded member %s found\n",qPrint(root->name));
7199 findMember(root,
7200 relates,
7201 type,
7202 args,
7203 root->name,
7204 TRUE,
7205 isFunc);
7206 }
7207 else if
7208 ((root->section.isFunction() // function
7209 ||
7210 (root->section.isVariable() && // variable
7211 !type.isEmpty() && // with a type
7212 g_compoundKeywords.find(type.str())==g_compoundKeywords.end() // that is not a keyword
7213 // (to skip forward declaration of class etc.)
7214 )
7215 )
7216 )
7217 {
7218 //printf("Documentation for member '%s' found args='%s' excp='%s'\n",
7219 // qPrint(root->name),qPrint(args),qPrint(root->exception));
7220 //if (relates.length()) printf(" Relates %s\n",qPrint(relates));
7221 //printf("Inside=%s\n Relates=%s\n",qPrint(root->inside),qPrint(relates));
7222 if (type=="friend class" || type=="friend struct" ||
7223 type=="friend union")
7224 {
7225 findMember(root,
7226 relates,
7227 type,
7228 args,
7229 type+" "+root->name,
7230 FALSE,FALSE);
7231
7232 }
7233 else if (!type.isEmpty())
7234 {
7235 findMember(root,
7236 relates,
7237 type,
7238 args,
7239 type+" "+ root->inside + root->name + args + root->exception,
7240 FALSE,isFunc);
7241 }
7242 else
7243 {
7244 findMember(root,
7245 relates,
7246 type,
7247 args,
7248 root->inside + root->name + args + root->exception,
7249 FALSE,isFunc);
7250 }
7251 }
7252 else if (root->section.isDefine() && !relates.isEmpty())
7253 {
7254 findMember(root,
7255 relates,
7256 type,
7257 args,
7258 root->name + args,
7259 FALSE,
7260 !args.isEmpty());
7261 }
7262 else if (root->section.isVariableDoc())
7263 {
7264 //printf("Documentation for variable %s found\n",qPrint(root->name));
7265 //if (!relates.isEmpty()) printf(" Relates %s\n",qPrint(relates));
7266 findMember(root,
7267 relates,
7268 type,
7269 args,
7270 root->name,
7271 FALSE,
7272 FALSE);
7273 }
7274 else if (root->section.isExportedInterface() ||
7275 root->section.isIncludedService())
7276 {
7277 findMember(root,
7278 relates,
7279 type,
7280 args,
7281 type + " " + root->name,
7282 FALSE,
7283 FALSE);
7284 }
7285 else
7286 {
7287 // skip section
7288 //printf("skip section\n");
7289 }
7290}
7291
7292static void findMemberDocumentation(const Entry *root)
7293{
7294 if (root->section.isMemberDoc() ||
7295 root->section.isOverloadDoc() ||
7296 root->section.isFunction() ||
7297 root->section.isVariable() ||
7298 root->section.isVariableDoc() ||
7299 root->section.isDefine() ||
7300 root->section.isIncludedService() ||
7301 root->section.isExportedInterface()
7302 )
7303 {
7304 AUTO_TRACE();
7305 if (root->relatesType==RelatesType::Duplicate && !root->relates.isEmpty())
7306 {
7307 filterMemberDocumentation(root,"");
7308 }
7309 filterMemberDocumentation(root,root->relates);
7310 }
7311 for (const auto &e : root->children())
7312 {
7313 if (!e->section.isEnum())
7314 {
7315 findMemberDocumentation(e.get());
7316 }
7317 }
7318}
7319
7320//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7321
7322static void findObjCMethodDefinitions(const Entry *root)
7323{
7324 AUTO_TRACE();
7325 for (const auto &objCImpl : root->children())
7326 {
7327 if (objCImpl->section.isObjcImpl())
7328 {
7329 for (const auto &objCMethod : objCImpl->children())
7330 {
7331 if (objCMethod->section.isFunction())
7332 {
7333 //Printf(" Found ObjC method definition %s\n",qPrint(objCMethod->name));
7334 findMember(objCMethod.get(),
7335 objCMethod->relates,
7336 objCMethod->type,
7337 objCMethod->args,
7338 objCMethod->type+" "+objCImpl->name+"::"+objCMethod->name+" "+objCMethod->args,
7339 FALSE,TRUE);
7340 objCMethod->section=EntryType::makeEmpty();
7341 }
7342 }
7343 }
7344 }
7345}
7346
7347//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7348// find and add the enumeration to their classes, namespaces or files
7349
7350static void findEnums(const Entry *root)
7351{
7352 if (root->section.isEnum())
7353 {
7354 AUTO_TRACE("name={}",root->name);
7355 ClassDefMutable *cd = nullptr;
7356 FileDef *fd = nullptr;
7357 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = nullptr;
7358 MemberNameLinkedMap *mnsd = nullptr;
7359 bool isGlobal = false;
7360 bool isRelated = false;
7361 bool isMemberOf = false;
7362 //printf("Found enum with name '%s' relates=%s\n",qPrint(root->name),qPrint(root->relates));
7363
7364 QCString name;
7365 QCString scope;
7366
7367 int i = root->name.findRev("::");
7368 if (i!=-1) // scope is specified
7369 {
7370 scope=root->name.left(i); // extract scope
7371 name=root->name.right(root->name.length()-i-2); // extract name
7372 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr)
7373 {
7374 nd=toNamespaceDefMutable(buildScopeFromQualifiedName(root->name.left(i+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo()));
7375 }
7376 }
7377 else // no scope, check the scope in which the docs where found
7378 {
7379 if (root->parent()->section.isScope() && !root->parent()->name.isEmpty()) // found enum docs inside a compound
7380 {
7381 scope=root->parent()->name;
7382 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr) nd=getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scope);
7383 }
7384 name=root->name;
7385 }
7386
7387 if (!root->relates.isEmpty())
7388 { // related member, prefix user specified scope
7389 isRelated=TRUE;
7390 isMemberOf=(root->relatesType==RelatesType::MemberOf);
7391 if (getClass(root->relates)==nullptr && !scope.isEmpty())
7392 scope=mergeScopes(scope,root->relates);
7393 else
7394 scope=root->relates;
7395 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr) nd=getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scope);
7396 }
7397
7398 if (cd && !name.isEmpty()) // found a enum inside a compound
7399 {
7400 //printf("Enum '%s'::'%s'\n",qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(name));
7401 fd=nullptr;
7402 mnsd=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap;
7403 isGlobal=false;
7404 }
7405 else if (nd) // found enum inside namespace
7406 {
7407 mnsd=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap;
7408 isGlobal=true;
7409 }
7410 else // found a global enum
7411 {
7412 fd=root->fileDef();
7413 mnsd=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap;
7414 isGlobal=true;
7415 }
7416
7417 if (!name.isEmpty())
7418 {
7419 // new enum type
7420 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("new enum {} at line {} of {}",name,root->bodyLine,root->fileName);
7421 auto md = createMemberDef(
7422 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
7423 QCString(),name,QCString(),QCString(),
7424 root->protection,Specifier::Normal,FALSE,
7425 isMemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign : isRelated ? Relationship::Related : Relationship::Member,
7426 MemberType::Enumeration,
7427 ArgumentList(),ArgumentList(),root->metaData);
7428 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
7429 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
7430 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
7431 mmd->setId(root->id);
7432 if (!isGlobal) mmd->setMemberClass(cd); else mmd->setFileDef(fd);
7433 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
7434 mmd->setBodyDef(root->fileDef());
7435 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
7436 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
7437 mmd->setEnumBaseType(root->args);
7438 //printf("Enum %s definition at line %d of %s: protection=%d scope=%s\n",
7439 // qPrint(root->name),root->bodyLine,qPrint(root->fileName),root->protection,cd?qPrint(cd->name()):"<none>");
7440 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
7441 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
7442 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
7443 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
7444 //printf("%s::setRefItems(%zu)\n",qPrint(md->name()),root->sli.size());
7445 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
7446 //printf("found enum %s nd=%p\n",qPrint(md->name()),nd);
7447 bool defSet=FALSE;
7448
7449 QCString baseType = root->args;
7450 if (!baseType.isEmpty())
7451 {
7452 baseType.prepend(" : ");
7453 }
7454
7455 if (nd)
7456 {
7457 if (isRelated || Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
7458 {
7459 mmd->setDefinition(name+baseType);
7460 }
7461 else
7462 {
7463 mmd->setDefinition(nd->name()+"::"+name+baseType);
7464 }
7465 //printf("definition=%s\n",md->definition());
7466 defSet=TRUE;
7467 mmd->setNamespace(nd);
7468 nd->insertMember(md.get());
7469 }
7470
7471 // even if we have already added the enum to a namespace, we still
7472 // also want to add it to other appropriate places such as file
7473 // or class.
7474 if (isGlobal && (nd==nullptr || !nd->isAnonymous()))
7475 {
7476 if (!defSet) mmd->setDefinition(name+baseType);
7477 if (fd==nullptr && root->parent())
7478 {
7479 fd=root->parent()->fileDef();
7480 }
7481 if (fd)
7482 {
7483 mmd->setFileDef(fd);
7484 fd->insertMember(md.get());
7485 }
7486 }
7487 else if (cd)
7488 {
7489 if (isRelated || Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
7490 {
7491 mmd->setDefinition(name+baseType);
7492 }
7493 else
7494 {
7495 mmd->setDefinition(cd->name()+"::"+name+baseType);
7496 }
7497 cd->insertMember(md.get());
7498 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
7499 }
7500 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
7501 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
7502 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
7503 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
7504
7505 //printf("Adding member=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()));
7506 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
7507 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md.get());
7508
7509 MemberName *mn = mnsd->add(name);
7510 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
7511 }
7512 }
7513 else
7514 {
7515 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findEnums(e.get());
7516 }
7517}
7518
7519//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7520
7521static void addEnumValuesToEnums(const Entry *root)
7522{
7523 if (root->section.isEnum())
7524 // non anonymous enumeration
7525 {
7526 AUTO_TRACE("name={}",root->name);
7527 ClassDefMutable *cd = nullptr;
7528 FileDef *fd = nullptr;
7529 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = nullptr;
7530 MemberNameLinkedMap *mnsd = nullptr;
7531 bool isGlobal = false;
7532 bool isRelated = false;
7533 //printf("Found enum with name '%s' relates=%s\n",qPrint(root->name),qPrint(root->relates));
7534
7535 QCString name;
7536 QCString scope;
7537
7538 int i = root->name.findRev("::");
7539 if (i!=-1) // scope is specified
7540 {
7541 scope=root->name.left(i); // extract scope
7542 name=root->name.right(root->name.length()-i-2); // extract name
7543 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr)
7544 {
7545 nd=toNamespaceDefMutable(buildScopeFromQualifiedName(root->name.left(i+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo()));
7546 }
7547 }
7548 else // no scope, check the scope in which the docs where found
7549 {
7550 if (root->parent()->section.isScope() && !root->parent()->name.isEmpty()) // found enum docs inside a compound
7551 {
7552 scope=root->parent()->name;
7553 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr) nd=getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scope);
7554 }
7555 name=root->name;
7556 }
7557
7558 if (!root->relates.isEmpty())
7559 { // related member, prefix user specified scope
7560 isRelated=TRUE;
7561 if (getClassMutable(root->relates)==nullptr && !scope.isEmpty())
7562 scope=mergeScopes(scope,root->relates);
7563 else
7564 scope=root->relates;
7565 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr) nd=getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scope);
7566 }
7567
7568 if (cd && !name.isEmpty()) // found a enum inside a compound
7569 {
7570 //printf("Enum in class '%s'::'%s'\n",qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(name));
7571 fd=nullptr;
7572 mnsd=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap;
7573 isGlobal=false;
7574 }
7575 else if (nd && !nd->isAnonymous()) // found enum inside namespace
7576 {
7577 //printf("Enum in namespace '%s'::'%s'\n",qPrint(nd->name()),qPrint(name));
7578 mnsd=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap;
7579 isGlobal=true;
7580 }
7581 else // found a global enum
7582 {
7583 fd=root->fileDef();
7584 //printf("Enum in file '%s': '%s'\n",qPrint(fd->name()),qPrint(name));
7585 mnsd=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap;
7586 isGlobal=true;
7587 }
7588
7589 if (!name.isEmpty())
7590 {
7591 //printf("** name=%s\n",qPrint(name));
7592 MemberName *mn = mnsd->find(name); // for all members with this name
7593 if (mn)
7594 {
7595 struct EnumValueInfo
7596 {
7597 EnumValueInfo(const QCString &n,std::unique_ptr<MemberDef> &&md) :
7598 name(n), member(std::move(md)) {}
7599 QCString name;
7600 std::unique_ptr<MemberDef> member;
7601 };
7602 std::vector< EnumValueInfo > extraMembers;
7603 // for each enum in this list
7604 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
7605 {
7606 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
7607 // use raw pointer in this loop, since we modify mn and can then invalidate mdp.
7608 if (md && md->isEnumerate() && !root->children().empty())
7609 {
7610 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("enum {} with {} children",md->name(),root->children().size());
7611 for (const auto &e : root->children())
7612 {
7613 SrcLangExt sle = root->lang;
7614 bool isJavaLike = sle==SrcLangExt::CSharp || sle==SrcLangExt::Java || sle==SrcLangExt::XML;
7615 if ( isJavaLike || root->spec.isStrong())
7616 {
7617 // Unlike classic C/C++ enums, for C++11, C# & Java enum
7618 // values are only visible inside the enum scope, so we must create
7619 // them here and only add them to the enum
7620 //printf("md->qualifiedName()=%s e->name=%s tagInfo=%p name=%s\n",
7621 // qPrint(md->qualifiedName()),qPrint(e->name),(void*)e->tagInfo(),qPrint(e->name));
7622 QCString qualifiedName = root->name;
7623 if (isJavaLike)
7624 {
7625 qualifiedName=substitute(qualifiedName,"::",".");
7626 }
7627 if (md->qualifiedName()==qualifiedName) // enum value scope matches that of the enum
7628 {
7629 QCString fileName = e->fileName;
7630 if (fileName.isEmpty() && e->tagInfo())
7631 {
7632 fileName = e->tagInfo()->tagName;
7633 }
7634 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("strong enum value {}",e->name);
7635 auto fmd = createMemberDef(
7636 fileName,e->startLine,e->startColumn,
7637 e->type,e->name,e->args,QCString(),
7638 e->protection, Specifier::Normal,e->isStatic,Relationship::Member,
7639 MemberType::EnumValue,ArgumentList(),ArgumentList(),e->metaData);
7640 auto fmmd = toMemberDefMutable(fmd.get());
7641 NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
7642 if (md->getClassDef())
7643 fmmd->setMemberClass(md->getClassDef());
7644 else if (mnd && (mnd->isLinkable() || mnd->isAnonymous()))
7645 fmmd->setNamespace(mnd);
7646 else if (md->getFileDef())
7647 fmmd->setFileDef(md->getFileDef());
7648 fmmd->setOuterScope(md->getOuterScope());
7649 fmmd->setTagInfo(e->tagInfo());
7650 fmmd->setLanguage(e->lang);
7651 fmmd->setBodySegment(e->startLine,e->bodyLine,e->endBodyLine);
7652 fmmd->setBodyDef(e->fileDef());
7653 fmmd->setId(e->id);
7654 fmmd->setDocumentation(e->doc,e->docFile,e->docLine);
7655 fmmd->setBriefDescription(e->brief,e->briefFile,e->briefLine);
7656 fmmd->addSectionsToDefinition(e->anchors);
7657 std::string init = e->initializer.str();
7658 fmmd->setInitializer(init.c_str());
7659 fmmd->setMaxInitLines(e->initLines);
7660 fmmd->setMemberGroupId(e->mGrpId);
7661 fmmd->setExplicitExternal(e->explicitExternal,fileName,e->startLine,e->startColumn);
7662 fmmd->setRefItems(e->sli);
7663 fmmd->setAnchor();
7664 md->insertEnumField(fmd.get());
7665 fmmd->setEnumScope(md,TRUE);
7666 extraMembers.emplace_back(e->name,std::move(fmd));
7667 }
7668 }
7669 else
7670 {
7671 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("enum value {}",e->name);
7672 //printf("e->name=%s isRelated=%d\n",qPrint(e->name),isRelated);
7673 MemberName *fmn=nullptr;
7674 MemberNameLinkedMap *emnsd = isRelated ? Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap : mnsd;
7675 if (!e->name.isEmpty() && (fmn=emnsd->find(e->name)))
7676 // get list of members with the same name as the field
7677 {
7678 for (const auto &ifmd : *fmn)
7679 {
7680 MemberDefMutable *fmd = toMemberDefMutable(ifmd.get());
7681 if (fmd && fmd->isEnumValue() && fmd->getOuterScope()==md->getOuterScope()) // in same scope
7682 {
7683 //printf("found enum value with same name %s in scope %s\n",
7684 // qPrint(fmd->name()),qPrint(fmd->getOuterScope()->name()));
7685 if (nd && !nd->isAnonymous())
7686 {
7687 if (!fmd->isStrongEnumValue()) // only non strong enum values can be globally added
7688 {
7689 const NamespaceDef *fnd=fmd->getNamespaceDef();
7690 if (fnd==nd) // enum value is inside a namespace
7691 {
7692 md->insertEnumField(fmd);
7693 fmd->setEnumScope(md);
7694 }
7695 }
7696 }
7697 else if (isGlobal)
7698 {
7699 if (!fmd->isStrongEnumValue()) // only non strong enum values can be globally added
7700 {
7701 const FileDef *ffd=fmd->getFileDef();
7702 if (ffd==fd && ffd==md->getFileDef()) // enum value has file scope
7703 {
7704 md->insertEnumField(fmd);
7705 fmd->setEnumScope(md);
7706 }
7707 }
7708 }
7709 else if (isRelated && cd) // reparent enum value to
7710 // match the enum's scope
7711 {
7712 md->insertEnumField(fmd); // add field def to list
7713 fmd->setEnumScope(md); // cross ref with enum name
7714 fmd->setEnumClassScope(cd); // cross ref with enum name
7715 fmd->setOuterScope(cd);
7716 fmd->makeRelated();
7717 cd->insertMember(fmd);
7718 }
7719 else
7720 {
7721 if (!fmd->isStrongEnumValue()) // only non strong enum values can be globally added
7722 {
7723 const ClassDef *fcd=fmd->getClassDef();
7724 if (fcd==cd) // enum value is inside a class
7725 {
7726 //printf("Inserting enum field %s in enum scope %s\n",
7727 // qPrint(fmd->name()),qPrint(md->name()));
7728 md->insertEnumField(fmd); // add field def to list
7729 fmd->setEnumScope(md); // cross ref with enum name
7730 }
7731 }
7732 }
7733 }
7734 }
7735 }
7736 }
7737 }
7738 }
7739 }
7740 // move the newly added members into mn
7741 for (auto &e : extraMembers)
7742 {
7743 MemberName *emn=mnsd->add(e.name);
7744 emn->push_back(std::move(e.member));
7745 }
7746 }
7747 }
7748 }
7749 else
7750 {
7751 for (const auto &e : root->children()) addEnumValuesToEnums(e.get());
7752 }
7753}
7754
7755//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7756
7757static void addEnumDocs(const Entry *root,MemberDefMutable *md)
7758{
7759 AUTO_TRACE();
7760 // documentation outside a compound overrides the documentation inside it
7761 {
7762 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
7763 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
7764 }
7765
7766 // brief descriptions inside a compound override the documentation
7767 // outside it
7768 {
7769 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
7770 }
7771
7772 if (md->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty() || !root->parent()->name.isEmpty())
7773 {
7774 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
7775 }
7776
7777 if (root->mGrpId!=-1 && md->getMemberGroupId()==-1)
7778 {
7779 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
7780 }
7781
7782 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
7783 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
7784
7785 const GroupDef *gd=md->getGroupDef();
7786 if (gd==nullptr && !root->groups.empty()) // member not grouped but out-of-line documentation is
7787 {
7788 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
7789 }
7790 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md);
7791}
7792
7793//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7794// Search for the name in the associated groups. If a matching member
7795// definition exists, then add the documentation to it and return TRUE,
7796// otherwise FALSE.
7797
7798static bool tryAddEnumDocsToGroupMember(const Entry *root,const QCString &name)
7799{
7800 for (const auto &g : root->groups)
7801 {
7802 const GroupDef *gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(g.groupname);
7803 if (gd)
7804 {
7805 MemberList *ml = gd->getMemberList(MemberListType::DecEnumMembers());
7806 if (ml)
7807 {
7808 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(ml->find(name));
7809 if (md)
7810 {
7811 addEnumDocs(root,md);
7812 return TRUE;
7813 }
7814 }
7815 }
7816 else if (!gd && g.pri == Grouping::GROUPING_INGROUP)
7817 {
7818 warn(root->fileName, root->startLine,
7819 "Found non-existing group '%s' for the command '%s', ignoring command",
7820 qPrint(g.groupname), Grouping::getGroupPriName( g.pri )
7821 );
7822 }
7823 }
7824
7825 return FALSE;
7826}
7827
7828//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7829// find the documentation blocks for the enumerations
7830
7831static void findEnumDocumentation(const Entry *root)
7832{
7833 if (root->section.isEnumDoc() &&
7834 !root->name.isEmpty() &&
7835 root->name.at(0)!='@' // skip anonymous enums
7836 )
7837 {
7838 QCString name;
7839 QCString scope;
7840 int i = root->name.findRev("::");
7841 if (i!=-1) // scope is specified as part of the name
7842 {
7843 name=root->name.right(root->name.length()-i-2); // extract name
7844 scope=root->name.left(i); // extract scope
7845 //printf("Scope='%s' Name='%s'\n",qPrint(scope),qPrint(name));
7846 }
7847 else // just the name
7848 {
7849 name=root->name;
7850 }
7851 if (root->parent()->section.isScope() && !root->parent()->name.isEmpty()) // found enum docs inside a compound
7852 {
7853 if (!scope.isEmpty()) scope.prepend("::");
7854 scope.prepend(root->parent()->name);
7855 }
7856 const ClassDef *cd = getClass(scope);
7857 const NamespaceDef *nd=Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(scope);
7858 const FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
7859 AUTO_TRACE("Found docs for enum with name '{}' and scope '{}' in context '{}' cd='{}', nd='{}' fd='{}'",
7860 name,scope,root->parent()->name,
7861 cd ? cd->name() : QCString("<none>"),
7862 nd ? nd->name() : QCString("<none>"),
7863 fd ? fd->name() : QCString("<none>"));
7864
7865 if (!name.isEmpty())
7866 {
7867 bool found = tryAddEnumDocsToGroupMember(root, name);
7868 if (!found)
7869 {
7870 MemberName *mn = cd ? Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(name) : Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(name);
7871 if (mn)
7872 {
7873 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
7874 {
7875 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
7876 if (md && md->isEnumerate())
7877 {
7878 const ClassDef *mcd = md->getClassDef();
7879 const NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
7880 const FileDef *mfd = md->getFileDef();
7881 if (cd && mcd==cd)
7882 {
7883 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Match found for class scope");
7884 addEnumDocs(root,md);
7885 found = TRUE;
7886 break;
7887 }
7888 else if (cd==nullptr && mcd==nullptr && nd!=nullptr && mnd==nd)
7889 {
7890 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Match found for namespace scope");
7891 addEnumDocs(root,md);
7892 found = TRUE;
7893 break;
7894 }
7895 else if (cd==nullptr && nd==nullptr && mcd==nullptr && mnd==nullptr && fd==mfd)
7896 {
7897 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Match found for global scope");
7898 addEnumDocs(root,md);
7899 found = TRUE;
7900 break;
7901 }
7902 }
7903 }
7904 }
7905 }
7906 if (!found)
7907 {
7908 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
7909 "Documentation for undefined enum '%s' found.",
7910 qPrint(name)
7911 );
7912 }
7913 }
7914 }
7915 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findEnumDocumentation(e.get());
7916}
7917
7918// search for each enum (member or function) in mnl if it has documented
7919// enum values.
7920static void findDEV(const MemberNameLinkedMap &mnsd)
7921{
7922 // for each member name
7923 for (const auto &mn : mnsd)
7924 {
7925 // for each member definition
7926 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
7927 {
7928 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
7929 if (md && md->isEnumerate()) // member is an enum
7930 {
7931 int documentedEnumValues=0;
7932 // for each enum value
7933 for (const auto &fmd : md->enumFieldList())
7934 {
7935 if (fmd->isLinkableInProject()) documentedEnumValues++;
7936 }
7937 // at least one enum value is documented
7938 if (documentedEnumValues>0) md->setDocumentedEnumValues(TRUE);
7939 }
7940 }
7941 }
7942}
7943
7944// search for each enum (member or function) if it has documented enum
7945// values.
7946static void findDocumentedEnumValues()
7947{
7948 findDEV(*Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap);
7949 findDEV(*Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap);
7950}

7952//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7953
7954static void addMembersToIndex()
7955{
7956 auto &index = Index::instance();
7957 // for each class member name
7958 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
7959 {
7960 // for each member definition
7961 for (const auto &md : *mn)
7962 {
7963 index.addClassMemberNameToIndex(md.get());
7964 if (md->getModuleDef())
7965 {
7966 index.addModuleMemberNameToIndex(md.get());
7967 }
7968 }
7969 }
7970 // for each file/namespace function name
7971 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap)
7972 {
7973 // for each member definition
7974 for (const auto &md : *mn)
7975 {
7976 if (md->getNamespaceDef())
7977 {
7978 index.addNamespaceMemberNameToIndex(md.get());
7979 }
7980 else
7981 {
7982 index.addFileMemberNameToIndex(md.get());
7983 }
7984 if (md->getModuleDef())
7985 {
7986 index.addModuleMemberNameToIndex(md.get());
7987 }
7988 }
7989 }
7990
7991 index.sortMemberIndexLists();
7992}

7994//----------------------------------------------------------------------
7995
7996static void addToIndices()
7997{
7998 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
7999 {
8000 if (cd->isLinkableInProject())
8001 {
8002 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(cd.get(),nullptr);
8003 if (Doxygen::searchIndex.enabled())
8004 {
8005 Doxygen::searchIndex.setCurrentDoc(cd.get(),cd->anchor(),FALSE);
8006 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(cd->localName(),TRUE);
8007 }
8008 }
8009 }
8010
8011 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap)
8012 {
8013 if (cd->isLinkableInProject())
8014 {
8015 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(cd.get(),nullptr);
8016 if (Doxygen::searchIndex.enabled())
8017 {
8018 Doxygen::searchIndex.setCurrentDoc(cd.get(),cd->anchor(),FALSE);
8019 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(cd->localName(),TRUE);
8020 }
8021 }
8022 }
8023
8024 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
8025 {
8026 if (nd->isLinkableInProject())
8027 {
8028 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(nd.get(),nullptr);
8029 if (Doxygen::searchIndex.enabled())
8030 {
8031 Doxygen::searchIndex.setCurrentDoc(nd.get(),nd->anchor(),FALSE);
8032 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(nd->localName(),TRUE);
8033 }
8034 }
8035 }
8036
8037 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8038 {
8039 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8040 {
8041 if (Doxygen::searchIndex.enabled() && fd->isLinkableInProject())
8042 {
8043 Doxygen::searchIndex.setCurrentDoc(fd.get(),fd->anchor(),FALSE);
8044 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(fd->localName(),TRUE);
8045 }
8046 }
8047 }
8048
8049 auto addWordsForTitle = [](const Definition *d,const QCString &anchor,const QCString &title)
8050 {
8051 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(d,nullptr,QCString(),filterTitle(title));
8052 if (Doxygen::searchIndex.enabled())
8053 {
8054 Doxygen::searchIndex.setCurrentDoc(d,anchor,false);
8055 std::string s = title.str();
8056 static const reg::Ex re(R"(\a[\w-]*)");
8057 reg::Iterator it(s,re);
8058 reg::Iterator end;
8059 for (; it!=end ; ++it)
8060 {
8061 const auto &match = *it;
8062 std::string matchStr = match.str();
8063 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(matchStr.c_str(),true);
8064 }
8065 }
8066 };
8067
8068 for (const auto &gd : *Doxygen::groupLinkedMap)
8069 {
8070 if (gd->isLinkableInProject())
8071 {
8072 addWordsForTitle(gd.get(),gd->anchor(),gd->groupTitle());
8073 }
8074 }
8075
8076 for (const auto &pd : *Doxygen::pageLinkedMap)
8077 {
8078 if (pd->isLinkableInProject())
8079 {
8080 addWordsForTitle(pd.get(),pd->anchor(),pd->title());
8081 }
8082 }
8083
8084 if (Doxygen::mainPage)
8085 {
8086 addWordsForTitle(Doxygen::mainPage.get(),Doxygen::mainPage->anchor(),Doxygen::mainPage->title());
8087 }
8088
8089 auto addMemberToSearchIndex = [](const MemberDef *md)
8090 {
8091 if (Doxygen::searchIndex.enabled())
8092 {
8093 Doxygen::searchIndex.setCurrentDoc(md,md->anchor(),FALSE);
8094 QCString ln=md->localName();
8095 QCString qn=md->qualifiedName();
8096 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(ln,TRUE);
8097 if (ln!=qn)
8098 {
8099 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(qn,TRUE);
8100 if (md->getClassDef())
8101 {
8102 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(md->getClassDef()->displayName(),TRUE);
8103 }
8104 if (md->getNamespaceDef())
8105 {
8106 Doxygen::searchIndex.addWord(md->getNamespaceDef()->displayName(),TRUE);
8107 }
8108 }
8109 }
8110 };
8111
8112 auto getScope = [](const MemberDef *md)
8113 {
8114 const Definition *scope = nullptr;
8115 if (md->getGroupDef()) scope = md->getGroupDef();
8116 else if (md->getClassDef()) scope = md->getClassDef();
8117 else if (md->getNamespaceDef()) scope = md->getNamespaceDef();
8118 else if (md->getFileDef()) scope = md->getFileDef();
8119 return scope;
8120 };
8121
8122 auto addMemberToIndices = [addMemberToSearchIndex,getScope](const MemberDef *md)
8123 {
8124 if (md->isLinkableInProject())
8125 {
8126 if (!(md->isEnumerate() && md->isAnonymous()))
8127 {
8128 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(getScope(md),md);
8129 addMemberToSearchIndex(md);
8130 }
8131 if (md->isEnumerate())
8132 {
8133 for (const auto &fmd : md->enumFieldList())
8134 {
8135 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(getScope(fmd),fmd);
8136 addMemberToSearchIndex(fmd);
8137 }
8138 }
8139 }
8140 };
8141
8142 // for each class member name
8143 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
8144 {
8145 // for each member definition
8146 for (const auto &md : *mn)
8147 {
8148 addMemberToIndices(md.get());
8149 }
8150 }
8151 // for each file/namespace function name
8152 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap)
8153 {
8154 // for each member definition
8155 for (const auto &md : *mn)
8156 {
8157 addMemberToIndices(md.get());
8158 }
8159 }
8160}

8193
8194// recursive helper function looking for reimplements/implemented
8195// by relations between class cd and direct or indirect base class bcd
8196static void computeMemberRelationsForBaseClass(const ClassDef *cd,const BaseClassDef *bcd)
8197{
8198 for (const auto &mn : cd->memberNameInfoLinkedMap()) // for each member in class cd with a unique name
8199 {
8200 for (const auto &imd : *mn) // for each member with a given name
8201 {
8202 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd->memberDef());
8203 if (md && (md->isFunction() || md->isCSharpProperty())) // filter on reimplementable members
8204 {
8205 ClassDef *mbcd = bcd->classDef;
8206 if (mbcd && mbcd->isLinkable()) // filter on linkable classes
8207 {
8208 const auto &bmn = mbcd->memberNameInfoLinkedMap();
8209 const auto &bmni = bmn.find(mn->memberName());
8210 if (bmni) // there are base class members with the same name
8211 {
8212 for (const auto &ibmd : *bmni) // for base class member with that name
8213 {
8214 MemberDefMutable *bmd = toMemberDefMutable(ibmd->memberDef());
8215 if (bmd) // not part of an inline namespace
8216 {
8217 if (bmd->virtualness()!=Specifier::Normal ||
8218 bmd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Python ||
8219 bmd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Java ||
8220 bmd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::PHP ||
8221 mbcd->compoundType()==ClassDef::Interface ||
8222 mbcd->compoundType()==ClassDef::Protocol)
8223 {
8224 const ArgumentList &bmdAl = bmd->argumentList();
8225 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md->argumentList();
8226 //printf(" Base argList='%s'\n Super argList='%s'\n",
8227 // qPrint(argListToString(bmdAl)),
8228 // qPrint(argListToString(mdAl))
8229 // );
8230 if (
8231 bmd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Python ||
8232 matchArguments2(bmd->getOuterScope(),bmd->getFileDef(),&bmdAl,
8233 md->getOuterScope(), md->getFileDef(), &mdAl,
8234 TRUE,bmd->getLanguage()
8235 )
8236 )
8237 {
8238 //printf("match!\n");
8239 const MemberDef *rmd = md->reimplements();
8240 if (rmd==nullptr) // not already assigned
8241 {
8242 //printf("%s: setting (new) reimplements member %s\n",qPrint(md->qualifiedName()),qPrint(bmd->qualifiedName()));
8243 md->setReimplements(bmd);
8244 }
8245 //printf("%s: add reimplementedBy member %s\n",qPrint(bmd->qualifiedName()),qPrint(md->qualifiedName()));
8246 bmd->insertReimplementedBy(md);
8247 }
8248 else
8249 {
8250 //printf("no match!\n");
8251 }
8252 }
8253 }
8254 }
8255 }
8256 }
8257 }
8258 }
8259 }
8260
8261 // do also for indirect base classes
8262 for (const auto &bbcd : bcd->classDef->baseClasses())
8263 {
8264 computeMemberRelationsForBaseClass(cd,&bbcd);
8265 }
8266}
8267
8268//----------------------------------------------------------------------
8269// computes the relation between all members. For each member 'm'
8270// the members that override the implementation of 'm' are searched and
8271// the member that 'm' overrides is searched.
8272
8273static void computeMemberRelations()
8274{
8275 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8276 {
8277 if (cd->isLinkable())
8278 {
8279 for (const auto &bcd : cd->baseClasses())
8280 {
8281 computeMemberRelationsForBaseClass(cd.get(),&bcd);
8282 }
8283 }
8284 }
8285}

8288
8289static void createTemplateInstanceMembers()
8290{
8291 // for each class
8292 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8293 {
8294 // that is a template
8295 for (const auto &ti : cd->getTemplateInstances())
8296 {
8297 ClassDefMutable *tcdm = toClassDefMutable(ti.classDef);
8298 if (tcdm)
8299 {
8300 tcdm->addMembersToTemplateInstance(cd.get(),cd->templateArguments(),ti.templSpec);
8301 }
8302 }
8303 }
8304}

8306//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8307
8308static void mergeCategories()
8309{
8310 AUTO_TRACE();
8311 // merge members of categories into the class they extend
8312 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8313 {
8314 int i=cd->name().find('(');
8315 if (i!=-1) // it is an Objective-C category
8316 {
8317 QCString baseName=cd->name().left(i);
8318 ClassDefMutable *baseClass=toClassDefMutable(Doxygen::classLinkedMap->find(baseName));
8319 if (baseClass)
8320 {
8321 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("merging members of category {} into {}",cd->name(),baseClass->name());
8322 baseClass->mergeCategory(cd.get());
8323 }
8324 }
8325 }
8326}
8327
8328// builds the list of all members for each class
8329
8330static void buildCompleteMemberLists()
8331{
8332 // merge the member list of base classes into the inherited classes.
8333 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8334 {
8335 if (// !cd->isReference() && // not an external class
8336 cd->subClasses().empty() && // is a root of the hierarchy
8337 !cd->baseClasses().empty()) // and has at least one base class
8338 {
8339 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
8340 if (cdm)
8341 {
8342 //printf("*** merging members for %s\n",qPrint(cd->name()));
8343 cdm->mergeMembers();
8344 }
8345 }
8346 }
8347 // now sort the member list of all members for all classes.
8348 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8349 {
8350 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
8351 if (cdm)
8352 {
8353 cdm->sortAllMembersList();
8354 }
8355 }
8356}
8357
8358//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8359
8360static void generateFileSources()
8361{
8362 auto processSourceFile = [](FileDef *fd,OutputList &ol,ClangTUParser *parser)
8363 {
8364 bool showSources = fd->generateSourceFile() && !Htags::useHtags; // sources need to be shown in the output
8365 bool parseSources = !fd->isReference() && Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded; // we needed to parse the sources even if we do not show them
8366 if (showSources)
8367 {
8368 msg("Generating code for file %s...\n",qPrint(fd->docName()));
8369 fd->writeSourceHeader(ol);
8370 fd->writeSourceBody(ol,parser);
8371 fd->writeSourceFooter(ol);
8372 }
8373 else if (parseSources)
8374 {
8375 msg("Parsing code for file %s...\n",qPrint(fd->docName()));
8376 fd->parseSource(parser);
8377 }
8378 };
8379 if (!Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap->empty())
8380 {
8381#if USE_LIBCLANG
8382 if (Doxygen::clangAssistedParsing)
8383 {
8384 StringUnorderedSet processedFiles;
8385
8386 // create a dictionary with files to process
8387 StringUnorderedSet filesToProcess;
8388
8389 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8390 {
8391 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8392 {
8393 filesToProcess.insert(fd->absFilePath().str());
8394 }
8395 }
8396 // process source files (and their include dependencies)
8397 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8398 {
8399 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8400 {
8401 if (fd->isSource() && !fd->isReference() && fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Cpp &&
8402 (fd->generateSourceFile() ||
8403 (!fd->isReference() && Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded)
8404 )
8405 )
8406 {
8407 auto clangParser = ClangParser::instance()->createTUParser(fd.get());
8408 clangParser->parse();
8409 processSourceFile(fd.get(),*g_outputList,clangParser.get());
8410
8411 for (auto incFile : clangParser->filesInSameTU())
8412 {
8413 if (filesToProcess.find(incFile)!=filesToProcess.end() && // part of input
8414 fd->absFilePath()!=QCString(incFile) && // not same file
8415 processedFiles.find(incFile)==processedFiles.end()) // not yet marked as processed
8416 {
8417 StringVector moreFiles;
8418 bool ambig = false;
8419 FileDef *ifd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,incFile.c_str(),ambig);
8420 if (ifd && !ifd->isReference())
8421 {
8422 processSourceFile(ifd,*g_outputList,clangParser.get());
8423 processedFiles.insert(incFile);
8424 }
8425 }
8426 }
8427 processedFiles.insert(fd->absFilePath().str());
8428 }
8429 }
8430 }
8431 // process remaining files
8432 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8433 {
8434 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8435 {
8436 if (processedFiles.find(fd->absFilePath().str())==processedFiles.end()) // not yet processed
8437 {
8438 if (fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Cpp) // C/C++ file, use clang parser
8439 {
8440 auto clangParser = ClangParser::instance()->createTUParser(fd.get());
8441 clangParser->parse();
8442 processSourceFile(fd.get(),*g_outputList,clangParser.get());
8443 }
8444 else // non C/C++ file, use built-in parser
8445 {
8446 processSourceFile(fd.get(),*g_outputList,nullptr);
8447 }
8448 }
8449 }
8450 }
8451 }
8452 else
8453#endif
8454 {
8455 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
8456 if (numThreads>1)
8457 {
8458 msg("Generating code files using %zu threads.\n",numThreads);
8459 struct SourceContext
8460 {
8461 SourceContext(FileDef *fd_,bool gen_,const OutputList &ol_)
8462 : fd(fd_), generateSourceFile(gen_), ol(ol_) {}
8463 FileDef *fd;
8464 bool generateSourceFile;
8465 OutputList ol;
8466 };
8467 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
8468 std::vector< std::future< std::shared_ptr<SourceContext> > > results;
8469 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8470 {
8471 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8472 {
8473 bool generateSourceFile = fd->generateSourceFile() && !Htags::useHtags;
8474 auto ctx = std::make_shared<SourceContext>(fd.get(),generateSourceFile,*g_outputList);
8475 auto processFile = [ctx]()
8476 {
8477 if (ctx->generateSourceFile)
8478 {
8479 msg("Generating code for file %s...\n",qPrint(ctx->fd->docName()));
8480 }
8481 else
8482 {
8483 msg("Parsing code for file %s...\n",qPrint(ctx->fd->docName()));
8484 }
8485 StringVector filesInSameTu;
8486 ctx->fd->getAllIncludeFilesRecursively(filesInSameTu);
8487 if (ctx->generateSourceFile) // sources need to be shown in the output
8488 {
8489 ctx->fd->writeSourceHeader(ctx->ol);
8490 ctx->fd->writeSourceBody(ctx->ol,nullptr);
8491 ctx->fd->writeSourceFooter(ctx->ol);
8492 }
8493 else if (!ctx->fd->isReference() && Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded)
8494 // we needed to parse the sources even if we do not show them
8495 {
8496 ctx->fd->parseSource(nullptr);
8497 }
8498 return ctx;
8499 };
8500 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
8501 }
8502 }
8503 for (auto &f : results)
8504 {
8505 auto ctx = f.get();
8506 }
8507 }
8508 else // single threaded version
8509 {
8510 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8511 {
8512 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8513 {
8514 StringVector filesInSameTu;
8515 fd->getAllIncludeFilesRecursively(filesInSameTu);
8516 processSourceFile(fd.get(),*g_outputList,nullptr);
8517 }
8518 }
8519 }
8520 }
8521 }
8522}
8523
8524//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8525
8526static void generateFileDocs()
8527{
8528 if (Index::instance().numDocumentedFiles()==0) return;
8529
8530 if (!Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap->empty())
8531 {
8532 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
8533 if (numThreads>1) // multi threaded processing
8534 {
8535 struct DocContext
8536 {
8537 DocContext(FileDef *fd_,const OutputList &ol_)
8538 : fd(fd_), ol(ol_) {}
8539 FileDef *fd;
8540 OutputList ol;
8541 };
8542 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
8543 std::vector< std::future< std::shared_ptr<DocContext> > > results;
8544 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8545 {
8546 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8547 {
8548 bool doc = fd->isLinkableInProject();
8549 if (doc)
8550 {
8551 auto ctx = std::make_shared<DocContext>(fd.get(),*g_outputList);
8552 auto processFile = [ctx]() {
8553 msg("Generating docs for file %s...\n",qPrint(ctx->fd->docName()));
8554 ctx->fd->writeDocumentation(ctx->ol);
8555 return ctx;
8556 };
8557 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
8558 }
8559 }
8560 }
8561 for (auto &f : results)
8562 {
8563 auto ctx = f.get();
8564 }
8565 }
8566 else // single threaded processing
8567 {
8568 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8569 {
8570 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8571 {
8572 bool doc = fd->isLinkableInProject();
8573 if (doc)
8574 {
8575 msg("Generating docs for file %s...\n",qPrint(fd->docName()));
8576 fd->writeDocumentation(*g_outputList);
8577 }
8578 }
8579 }
8580 }
8581 }
8582}
8583
8584//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8585
8586static void addSourceReferences()
8587{
8588 // add source references for class definitions
8589 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8590 {
8591 const FileDef *fd=cd->getBodyDef();
8592 if (fd && cd->isLinkableInProject() && cd->getStartDefLine()!=-1)
8593 {
8594 const_cast<FileDef*>(fd)->addSourceRef(cd->getStartDefLine(),cd.get(),nullptr);
8595 }
8596 }
8597 // add source references for concept definitions
8598 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap)
8599 {
8600 const FileDef *fd=cd->getBodyDef();
8601 if (fd && cd->isLinkableInProject() && cd->getStartDefLine()!=-1)
8602 {
8603 const_cast<FileDef*>(fd)->addSourceRef(cd->getStartDefLine(),cd.get(),nullptr);
8604 }
8605 }
8606 // add source references for namespace definitions
8607 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
8608 {
8609 const FileDef *fd=nd->getBodyDef();
8610 if (fd && nd->isLinkableInProject() && nd->getStartDefLine()!=-1)
8611 {
8612 const_cast<FileDef*>(fd)->addSourceRef(nd->getStartDefLine(),nd.get(),nullptr);
8613 }
8614 }
8615
8616 // add source references for member names
8617 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
8618 {
8619 for (const auto &md : *mn)
8620 {
8621 //printf("class member %s: def=%s body=%d link?=%d\n",
8622 // qPrint(md->name()),
8623 // md->getBodyDef()?qPrint(md->getBodyDef()->name()):"<none>",
8624 // md->getStartBodyLine(),md->isLinkableInProject());
8625 const FileDef *fd=md->getBodyDef();
8626 if (fd &&
8627 md->getStartDefLine()!=-1 &&
8628 md->isLinkableInProject() &&
8629 (fd->generateSourceFile() || Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded)
8630 )
8631 {
8632 //printf("Found member '%s' in file '%s' at line '%d' def=%s\n",
8633 // qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(fd->name()),md->getStartBodyLine(),qPrint(md->getOuterScope()->name()));
8634 const_cast<FileDef*>(fd)->addSourceRef(md->getStartDefLine(),md->getOuterScope(),md.get());
8635 }
8636 }
8637 }
8638 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap)
8639 {
8640 for (const auto &md : *mn)
8641 {
8642 const FileDef *fd=md->getBodyDef();
8643 //printf("member %s body=[%d,%d] fd=%p link=%d parseSources=%d\n",
8644 // qPrint(md->name()),
8645 // md->getStartBodyLine(),md->getEndBodyLine(),fd,
8646 // md->isLinkableInProject(),
8647 // Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded);
8648 if (fd &&
8649 md->getStartDefLine()!=-1 &&
8650 md->isLinkableInProject() &&
8651 (fd->generateSourceFile() || Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded)
8652 )
8653 {
8654 //printf("Found member '%s' in file '%s' at line '%d' def=%s\n",
8655 // qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(fd->name()),md->getStartBodyLine(),qPrint(md->getOuterScope()->name()));
8656 const_cast<FileDef*>(fd)->addSourceRef(md->getStartDefLine(),md->getOuterScope(),md.get());
8657 }
8658 }
8659 }
8660}
8661
8662//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8663
8664// add the macro definitions found during preprocessing as file members
8665static void buildDefineList()
8666{
8667 AUTO_TRACE();
8668 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
8669 {
8670 auto it = Doxygen::macroDefinitions.find(s);
8671 if (it!=Doxygen::macroDefinitions.end())
8672 {
8673 for (const auto &def : it->second)
8674 {
8675 auto md = createMemberDef(
8676 def.fileName,def.lineNr,def.columnNr,
8677 "#define",def.name,def.args,QCString(),
8678 Protection::Public,Specifier::Normal,FALSE,Relationship::Member,MemberType::Define,
8679 ArgumentList(),ArgumentList(),"");
8680 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
8681
8682 if (!def.args.isEmpty())
8683 {
8684 mmd->moveArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(SrcLangExt::Cpp, def.args));
8685 }
8686 mmd->setInitializer(def.definition);
8687 mmd->setFileDef(def.fileDef);
8688 mmd->setDefinition("#define "+def.name);
8689
8690 MemberName *mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(def.name);
8691 if (def.fileDef)
8692 {
8693 def.fileDef->insertMember(md.get());
8694 }
8695 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("adding macro {} with definition {}",def.name,def.definition);
8696 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
8697 }
8698 }
8699 }
8700}

8702//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8703
8704static void sortMemberLists()
8705{
8706 // sort class member lists
8707 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8708 {
8709 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
8710 if (cdm)
8711 {
8712 cdm->sortMemberLists();
8713 }
8714 }
8715
8716 // sort namespace member lists
8717 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
8718 {
8719 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
8720 if (ndm)
8721 {
8722 ndm->sortMemberLists();
8723 }
8724 }
8725
8726 // sort file member lists
8727 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8728 {
8729 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8730 {
8731 fd->sortMemberLists();
8732 }
8733 }
8734
8735 // sort group member lists
8736 for (const auto &gd : *Doxygen::groupLinkedMap)
8737 {
8738 gd->sortMemberLists();
8739 }
8740
8741 ModuleManager::instance().sortMemberLists();
8742}

8744//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8745
8746static bool isSymbolHidden(const Definition *d)
8747{
8748 bool hidden = d->isHidden();
8749 const Definition *parent = d->getOuterScope();
8750 return parent ? hidden || isSymbolHidden(parent) : hidden;
8751}
8752
8753static void computeTooltipTexts()
8754{
8755 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
8756 if (numThreads>1)
8757 {
8758 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
8759 std::vector < std::future< void > > results;
8760 // queue the work
8761 for (const auto &[name,symList] : *Doxygen::symbolMap)
8762 {
8763 for (const auto &def : symList)
8764 {
8765 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(def);
8766 if (dm && !isSymbolHidden(def) && !def->isArtificial() && def->isLinkableInProject())
8767 {
8768 auto processTooltip = [dm]() {
8769 dm->computeTooltip();
8770 };
8771 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processTooltip));
8772 }
8773 }
8774 }
8775 // wait for the results
8776 for (auto &f : results)
8777 {
8778 f.get();
8779 }
8780 }
8781 else
8782 {
8783 for (const auto &[name,symList] : *Doxygen::symbolMap)
8784 {
8785 for (const auto &def : symList)
8786 {
8787 DefinitionMutable *dm = toDefinitionMutable(def);
8788 if (dm && !isSymbolHidden(def) && !def->isArtificial() && def->isLinkableInProject())
8789 {
8790 dm->computeTooltip();
8791 }
8792 }
8793 }
8794 }
8795}

8814{
8815 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8816 {
8817 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
8818 if (cdm)
8819 {
8820 cdm->countMembers();
8821 }
8822 }
8823
8824 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
8825 {
8826 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
8827 if (ndm)
8828 {
8829 ndm->countMembers();
8830 }
8831 }

8833 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
8834 {
8835 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
8836 {
8837 fd->countMembers();
8838 }
8839 }
8840
8841 for (const auto &gd : *Doxygen::groupLinkedMap)
8842 {
8843 gd->countMembers();
8844 }
8845
8846 auto &mm = ModuleManager::instance();
8847 mm.countMembers();
8848}

8850
8851//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8852// generate the documentation for all classes
8853
8854static void generateDocsForClassList(const std::vector<ClassDefMutable*> &classList)
8855{
8856 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
8857 if (numThreads>1) // multi threaded processing
8858 {
8859 struct DocContext
8860 {
8861 DocContext(ClassDefMutable *cd_,const OutputList &ol_)
8862 : cd(cd_), ol(ol_) {}
8863 ClassDefMutable *cd;
8864 OutputList ol;
8865 };
8866 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
8867 std::vector< std::future< std::shared_ptr<DocContext> > > results;
8868 for (const auto &cd : classList)
8869 {
8870 //printf("cd=%s getOuterScope=%p global=%p\n",qPrint(cd->name()),cd->getOuterScope(),Doxygen::globalScope);
8871 if (cd->getOuterScope()==nullptr || // <-- should not happen, but can if we read an old tag file
8872 cd->getOuterScope()==Doxygen::globalScope // only look at global classes
8873 )
8874 {
8875 auto ctx = std::make_shared<DocContext>(cd,*g_outputList);
8876 auto processFile = [ctx]()
8877 {
8878 msg("Generating docs for compound %s...\n",qPrint(ctx->cd->displayName()));
8879
8880 // skip external references, anonymous compounds and
8881 // template instances
8882 if (!ctx->cd->isHidden() && !ctx->cd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope() &&
8883 ctx->cd->isLinkableInProject() && ctx->cd->templateMaster()==nullptr)
8884 {
8885 ctx->cd->writeDocumentation(ctx->ol);
8886 ctx->cd->writeMemberList(ctx->ol);
8887 }
8888
8889 // even for undocumented classes, the inner classes can be documented.
8890 ctx->cd->writeDocumentationForInnerClasses(ctx->ol);
8891 return ctx;
8892 };
8893 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
8894 }
8895 }
8896 for (auto &f : results)
8897 {
8898 auto ctx = f.get();
8899 }
8900 }
8901 else // single threaded processing
8902 {
8903 for (const auto &cd : classList)
8904 {
8905 //printf("cd=%s getOuterScope=%p global=%p hidden=%d embeddedInOuterScope=%d\n",
8906 // qPrint(cd->name()),cd->getOuterScope(),Doxygen::globalScope,cd->isHidden(),cd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope());
8907 if (cd->getOuterScope()==nullptr || // <-- should not happen, but can if we read an old tag file
8908 cd->getOuterScope()==Doxygen::globalScope // only look at global classes
8909 )
8910 {
8911 // skip external references, anonymous compounds and
8912 // template instances
8913 if ( !cd->isHidden() && !cd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope() &&
8914 cd->isLinkableInProject() && cd->templateMaster()==nullptr)
8915 {
8916 msg("Generating docs for compound %s...\n",qPrint(cd->displayName()));
8917
8918 cd->writeDocumentation(*g_outputList);
8919 cd->writeMemberList(*g_outputList);
8920 }
8921 // even for undocumented classes, the inner classes can be documented.
8922 cd->writeDocumentationForInnerClasses(*g_outputList);
8923 }
8924 }
8925 }
8926}
8927
8928static void addClassAndNestedClasses(std::vector<ClassDefMutable*> &list,ClassDefMutable *cd)
8929{
8930 list.push_back(cd);
8931 for (const auto &innerCdi : cd->getClasses())
8932 {
8933 ClassDefMutable *innerCd = toClassDefMutable(innerCdi);
8934 if (innerCd && innerCd->isLinkableInProject() && innerCd->templateMaster()==nullptr &&
8935 protectionLevelVisible(innerCd->protection()) &&
8936 !innerCd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope()
8937 )
8938 {
8939 list.push_back(innerCd);
8940 addClassAndNestedClasses(list,innerCd);
8941 }
8942 }
8943}
8944
8945static void generateClassDocs()
8946{
8947 std::vector<ClassDefMutable*> classList;
8948 for (const auto &cdi : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
8949 {
8950 ClassDefMutable *cd = toClassDefMutable(cdi.get());
8951 if (cd && (cd->getOuterScope()==nullptr ||
8952 cd->getOuterScope()->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeClass))
8953 {
8954 addClassAndNestedClasses(classList,cd);
8955 }
8956 }
8957 for (const auto &cdi : *Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap)
8958 {
8959 ClassDefMutable *cd = toClassDefMutable(cdi.get());
8960 if (cd && (cd->getOuterScope()==nullptr ||
8961 cd->getOuterScope()->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeClass))
8962 {
8963 addClassAndNestedClasses(classList,cd);
8964 }
8965 }
8966 generateDocsForClassList(classList);
8967}
8968
8969//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8970
8971static void generateConceptDocs()
8972{
8973 for (const auto &cdi : *Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap)
8974 {
8975 ConceptDefMutable *cd=toConceptDefMutable(cdi.get());
8976
8977 //printf("cd=%s getOuterScope=%p global=%p\n",qPrint(cd->name()),cd->getOuterScope(),Doxygen::globalScope);
8978 if (cd &&
8979 (cd->getOuterScope()==nullptr || // <-- should not happen, but can if we read an old tag file
8980 cd->getOuterScope()==Doxygen::globalScope // only look at global concepts
8981 ) && !cd->isHidden() && cd->isLinkableInProject()
8982 )
8983 {
8984 msg("Generating docs for concept %s...\n",qPrint(cd->displayName()));
8985 cd->writeDocumentation(*g_outputList);
8986 }
8987 }
8988}

8990//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8991
8992static void inheritDocumentation()
8993{
8994 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
8995 {
8996 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
8997 {
8998 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
8999 //static int count=0;
9000 //printf("%04d Member '%s'\n",count++,qPrint(md->qualifiedName()));
9001 if (md && md->documentation().isEmpty() && md->briefDescription().isEmpty())
9002 { // no documentation yet
9003 const MemberDef *bmd = md->reimplements();
9004 while (bmd && bmd->documentation().isEmpty() &&
9005 bmd->briefDescription().isEmpty()
9006 )
9007 { // search up the inheritance tree for a documentation member
9008 //printf("bmd=%s class=%s\n",qPrint(bmd->name()),qPrint(bmd->getClassDef()->name()));
9009 bmd = bmd->reimplements();
9010 }
9011 if (bmd) // copy the documentation from the reimplemented member
9012 {
9013 md->setInheritsDocsFrom(bmd);
9014 md->setDocumentation(bmd->documentation(),bmd->docFile(),bmd->docLine());
9015 md->setDocsForDefinition(bmd->isDocsForDefinition());
9016 md->setBriefDescription(bmd->briefDescription(),bmd->briefFile(),bmd->briefLine());
9017 md->copyArgumentNames(bmd);
9018 md->setInbodyDocumentation(bmd->inbodyDocumentation(),bmd->inbodyFile(),bmd->inbodyLine());
9019 }
9020 }
9021 }
9022 }
9023}

9027static void combineUsingRelations()
9028{
9029 // for each file
9030 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
9031 {
9032 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
9033 {
9034 fd->combineUsingRelations();
9035 }
9036 }
9037
9038 // for each namespace
9039 NamespaceDefSet visitedNamespaces;
9040 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
9041 {
9042 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
9043 if (ndm)
9044 {
9045 ndm->combineUsingRelations(visitedNamespaces);
9046 }
9047 }
9048}

9128static void findSectionsInDocumentation()
9129{
9130 // for each class
9131 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::classLinkedMap)
9132 {
9133 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd.get());
9134 if (cdm)
9135 {
9136 cdm->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9137 }
9138 }
9139 // for each concept
9140 for (const auto &cd : *Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap)
9141 {
9142 ConceptDefMutable *cdm = toConceptDefMutable(cd.get());
9143 if (cdm)
9144 {
9145 cdm->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9146 }
9147 }
9148 // for each file
9149 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
9150 {
9151 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
9152 {
9153 fd->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9154 }
9155 }
9156 // for each namespace
9157 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
9158 {
9159 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
9160 if (ndm)
9161 {
9162 ndm->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9163 }
9164 }
9165 // for each group
9166 for (const auto &gd : *Doxygen::groupLinkedMap)
9167 {
9168 gd->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9169 }
9170 // for each page
9171 for (const auto &pd : *Doxygen::pageLinkedMap)
9172 {
9173 pd->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9174 }
9175 ModuleManager::instance().findSectionsInDocumentation();
9176 if (Doxygen::mainPage) Doxygen::mainPage->findSectionsInDocumentation();
9177}
