9179//----------------------------------------------------------------------
9180
9181
9182static void flushCachedTemplateRelations()
9183{
9184 // remove all references to classes from the cache
9185 // as there can be new template instances in the inheritance path
9186 // to this class. Optimization: only remove those classes that
9187 // have inheritance instances as direct or indirect sub classes.
9188 StringVector elementsToRemove;
9189 for (const auto &ci : *Doxygen::typeLookupCache)
9190 {
9191 const LookupInfo &li = ci.second;
9192 if (li.definition)
9193 {
9194 elementsToRemove.push_back(ci.first);
9195 }
9196 }
9197 for (const auto &k : elementsToRemove)
9198 {
9199 Doxygen::typeLookupCache->remove(k);
9200 }
9201
9202 // remove all cached typedef resolutions whose target is a
9203 // template class as this may now be a template instance
9204 // for each global function name
9205 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap)
9206 {
9207 // for each function with that name
9208 for (const auto &ifmd : *fn)
9209 {
9210 MemberDefMutable *fmd = toMemberDefMutable(ifmd.get());
9211 if (fmd && fmd->isTypedefValCached())
9212 {
9213 const ClassDef *cd = fmd->getCachedTypedefVal();
9214 if (cd->isTemplate()) fmd->invalidateTypedefValCache();
9215 }
9216 }
9217 }
9218 // for each class method name
9219 for (const auto &nm : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
9220 {
9221 // for each function with that name
9222 for (const auto &imd : *nm)
9223 {
9224 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
9225 if (md && md->isTypedefValCached())
9226 {
9227 const ClassDef *cd = md->getCachedTypedefVal();
9228 if (cd->isTemplate()) md->invalidateTypedefValCache();
9229 }
9230 }
9231 }
9232}
9233
9234//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9235
9236static void flushUnresolvedRelations()
9237{
9238 // Remove all unresolved references to classes from the cache.
9239 // This is needed before resolving the inheritance relations, since
9240 // it would otherwise not find the inheritance relation
9241 // for C in the example below, as B::I was already found to be unresolvable
9242 // (which is correct if you ignore the inheritance relation between A and B).
9243 //
9244 // class A { class I {} };
9245 // class B : public A {};
9246 // class C : public B::I {};
9247
9248 StringVector elementsToRemove;
9249 for (const auto &ci : *Doxygen::typeLookupCache)
9250 {
9251 const LookupInfo &li = ci.second;
9252 if (li.definition==nullptr && li.typeDef==nullptr)
9253 {
9254 elementsToRemove.push_back(ci.first);
9255 }
9256 }
9257 for (const auto &k : elementsToRemove)
9258 {
9259 Doxygen::typeLookupCache->remove(k);
9260 }
9261
9262 // for each global function name
9263 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap)
9264 {
9265 // for each function with that name
9266 for (const auto &ifmd : *fn)
9267 {
9268 MemberDefMutable *fmd = toMemberDefMutable(ifmd.get());
9269 if (fmd)
9270 {
9271 fmd->invalidateCachedArgumentTypes();
9272 }
9273 }
9274 }
9275 // for each class method name
9276 for (const auto &nm : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
9277 {
9278 // for each function with that name
9279 for (const auto &imd : *nm)
9280 {
9281 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
9282 if (md)
9283 {
9284 md->invalidateCachedArgumentTypes();
9285 }
9286 }
9287 }
9288
9289}
9290
9291//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9292// Returns TRUE if the entry and member definition have equal file names,
9293// otherwise FALSE.
9294
9295static bool haveEqualFileNames(const Entry *root,const MemberDef *md)
9296{
9297 const FileDef *fd = md->getFileDef();
9298 if (!fd)
9299 {
9300 return FALSE;
9301 }
9302
9303 return fd->absFilePath() == root->fileName;
9304}
9305
9306//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9307
9308static void addDefineDoc(const Entry *root, MemberDefMutable *md)
9309{
9310 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
9311 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
9312 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
9313 if (md->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
9314 {
9315 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
9316 }
9317 if (md->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && root->bodyLine!=-1)
9318 {
9319 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
9320 md->setBodyDef(root->fileDef());
9321 }
9322 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
9323 md->setMaxInitLines(root->initLines);
9324 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,md);
9325 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
9326 if (root->mGrpId!=-1) md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
9327 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
9328 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md);
9329}
9330
9331//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9332
9333static void findDefineDocumentation(Entry *root)
9334{
9335 if ((root->section.isDefineDoc() || root->section.isDefine()) && !root->name.isEmpty())
9336 {
9337 //printf("found define '%s' '%s' brief='%s' doc='%s'\n",
9338 // qPrint(root->name),qPrint(root->args),qPrint(root->brief),qPrint(root->doc));
9339
9340 if (root->tagInfo() && !root->name.isEmpty()) // define read from a tag file
9341 {
9342 auto md = createMemberDef(root->tagInfo()->tagName,1,1,
9343 "#define",root->name,root->args,QCString(),
9344 Protection::Public,Specifier::Normal,FALSE,Relationship::Member,MemberType::Define,
9345 ArgumentList(),ArgumentList(),"");
9346 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
9347 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
9348 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
9349 //printf("Searching for '%s' fd=%p\n",qPrint(filePathName),fd);
9350 mmd->setFileDef(root->parent()->fileDef());
9351 //printf("Adding member=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()));
9352 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(root->name);
9353 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
9354 }
9355 MemberName *mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(root->name);
9356 if (mn)
9357 {
9358 int count=0;
9359 for (const auto &md : *mn)
9360 {
9361 if (md->memberType()==MemberType::Define) count++;
9362 }
9363 if (count==1)
9364 {
9365 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
9366 {
9367 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
9368 if (md && md->memberType()==MemberType::Define)
9369 {
9370 addDefineDoc(root,md);
9371 }
9372 }
9373 }
9374 else if (count>1 &&
9375 (!root->doc.isEmpty() ||
9376 !root->brief.isEmpty() ||
9377 root->bodyLine!=-1
9378 )
9379 )
9380 // multiple defines don't know where to add docs
9381 // but maybe they are in different files together with their documentation
9382 {
9383 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
9384 {
9385 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
9386 if (md && md->memberType()==MemberType::Define)
9387 {
9388 if (haveEqualFileNames(root, md) || isEntryInGroupOfMember(root, md))
9389 // doc and define in the same file or group assume they belong together.
9390 {
9391 addDefineDoc(root,md);
9392 }
9393 }
9394 }
9395 //warn("define %s found in the following files:\n",qPrint(root->name));
9396 //warn("Cannot determine where to add the documentation found "
9397 // "at line %d of file %s. \n",
9398 // root->startLine,qPrint(root->fileName));
9399 }
9400 }
9401 else if (!root->doc.isEmpty() || !root->brief.isEmpty()) // define not found
9402 {
9403 bool preEnabled = Config_getBool(ENABLE_PREPROCESSING);
9404 if (preEnabled)
9405 {
9406 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
9407 "documentation for unknown define %s found.",
9408 qPrint(root->name)
9409 );
9410 }
9411 else
9412 {
9413 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
9414 "found documented #define %s but ignoring it because "
9415 "ENABLE_PREPROCESSING is NO.",
9416 qPrint(root->name)
9417 );
9418 }
9419 }
9420 }
9421 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findDefineDocumentation(e.get());
9422}
9423
9424//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9425
9426static void findDirDocumentation(const Entry *root)
9427{
9428 if (root->section.isDirDoc())
9429 {
9430 QCString normalizedName = root->name;
9431 normalizedName = substitute(normalizedName,"\\","/");
9432 //printf("root->docFile=%s normalizedName=%s\n",
9433 // qPrint(root->docFile),qPrint(normalizedName));
9434 if (root->docFile==normalizedName) // current dir?
9435 {
9436 int lastSlashPos=normalizedName.findRev('/');
9437 if (lastSlashPos!=-1) // strip file name
9438 {
9439 normalizedName=normalizedName.left(lastSlashPos);
9440 }
9441 }
9442 if (normalizedName.at(normalizedName.length()-1)!='/')
9443 {
9444 normalizedName+='/';
9445 }
9446 DirDef *matchingDir=nullptr;
9447 for (const auto &dir : *Doxygen::dirLinkedMap)
9448 {
9449 //printf("Dir: %s<->%s\n",qPrint(dir->name()),qPrint(normalizedName));
9450 if (dir->name().right(normalizedName.length())==normalizedName)
9451 {
9452 if (matchingDir)
9453 {
9454 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
9455 "\\dir command matches multiple directories.\n"
9456 " Applying the command for directory %s\n"
9457 " Ignoring the command for directory %s",
9458 qPrint(matchingDir->name()),qPrint(dir->name())
9459 );
9460 }
9461 else
9462 {
9463 matchingDir=dir.get();
9464 }
9465 }
9466 }
9467 if (matchingDir)
9468 {
9469 //printf("Match for with dir %s\n",qPrint(matchingDir->name()));
9470 matchingDir->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
9471 matchingDir->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
9472 matchingDir->setRefItems(root->sli);
9473 root->commandOverrides.apply_directoryGraph([&](bool b) { matchingDir->overrideDirectoryGraph(b); });
9474 addDirToGroups(root,matchingDir);
9475 }
9476 else
9477 {
9478 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,"No matching "
9479 "directory found for command \\dir %s",qPrint(normalizedName));
9480 }
9481 }
9482 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findDirDocumentation(e.get());
9483}

9486//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9487// create a (sorted) list of separate documentation pages
9488
9489static void buildPageList(Entry *root)
9490{
9491 if (root->section.isPageDoc())
9492 {
9493 if (!root->name.isEmpty())
9494 {
9495 addRelatedPage(root);
9496 }
9497 }
9498 else if (root->section.isMainpageDoc())
9499 {
9500 QCString title=root->args.stripWhiteSpace();
9501 if (title.isEmpty()) title=theTranslator->trMainPage();
9502 //QCString name = Config_getBool(GENERATE_TREEVIEW)?"main":"index";
9503 QCString name = "index";
9504 addRefItem(root->sli,
9505 name,
9506 "page",
9507 name,
9508 title,
9509 QCString(),nullptr
9510 );
9511 }
9512 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildPageList(e.get());
9513}
9514
9515// search for the main page defined in this project
9516static void findMainPage(Entry *root)
9517{
9518 if (root->section.isMainpageDoc())
9519 {
9520 if (Doxygen::mainPage==nullptr && root->tagInfo()==nullptr)
9521 {
9522 //printf("mainpage: docLine=%d startLine=%d\n",root->docLine,root->startLine);
9523 //printf("Found main page! \n======\n%s\n=======\n",qPrint(root->doc));
9524 QCString title=root->args.stripWhiteSpace();
9525 if (title.isEmpty()) title = Config_getString(PROJECT_NAME);
9526 //QCString indexName=Config_getBool(GENERATE_TREEVIEW)?"main":"index";
9527 QCString indexName="index";
9528 Doxygen::mainPage = createPageDef(root->docFile,root->docLine,
9529 indexName, root->brief+root->doc+root->inbodyDocs,title);
9530 //setFileNameForSections(root->anchors,"index",Doxygen::mainPage);
9531 Doxygen::mainPage->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
9532 Doxygen::mainPage->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->startLine,-1);
9533 Doxygen::mainPage->setFileName(indexName);
9534 Doxygen::mainPage->setLocalToc(root->localToc);
9535 addPageToContext(Doxygen::mainPage.get(),root);
9536
9537 const SectionInfo *si = SectionManager::instance().find(Doxygen::mainPage->name());
9538 if (si)
9539 {
9540 if (!si->ref().isEmpty()) // we are from a tag file
9541 {
9542 // a page name is a label as well! but should no be double either
9543 SectionManager::instance().replace(
9544 Doxygen::mainPage->name(),
9545 indexName,
9546 root->startLine,
9547 Doxygen::mainPage->title(),
9548 SectionType::Page,
9549 0); // level 0
9550 }
9551 else if (si->lineNr() != -1)
9552 {
9553 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,"multiple use of section label '%s' for main page, (first occurrence: %s, line %d)",
9554 qPrint(Doxygen::mainPage->name()),qPrint(si->fileName()),si->lineNr());
9555 }
9556 else
9557 {
9558 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,"multiple use of section label '%s' for main page, (first occurrence: %s)",
9559 qPrint(Doxygen::mainPage->name()),qPrint(si->fileName()));
9560 }
9561 }
9562 else
9563 {
9564 // a page name is a label as well! but should no be double either
9565 SectionManager::instance().add(
9566 Doxygen::mainPage->name(),
9567 indexName,
9568 root->startLine,
9569 Doxygen::mainPage->title(),
9570 SectionType::Page,
9571 0); // level 0
9572 }
9573 Doxygen::mainPage->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
9574 }
9575 else if (root->tagInfo()==nullptr)
9576 {
9577 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
9578 "found more than one \\mainpage comment block! (first occurrence: %s, line %d), Skipping current block!",
9579 qPrint(Doxygen::mainPage->docFile()),Doxygen::mainPage->getStartBodyLine());
9580 }
9581 }
9582 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findMainPage(e.get());
9583}
9584
9585// search for the main page imported via tag files and add only the section labels
9586static void findMainPageTagFiles(Entry *root)
9587{
9588 if (root->section.isMainpageDoc())
9589 {
9590 if (Doxygen::mainPage && root->tagInfo())
9591 {
9592 Doxygen::mainPage->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
9593 }
9594 }
9595 for (const auto &e : root->children()) findMainPageTagFiles(e.get());
9596}
9597
9598static void computePageRelations(Entry *root)
9599{
9600 if ((root->section.isPageDoc() || root->section.isMainpageDoc()) && !root->name.isEmpty())
9601 {
9602 PageDef *pd = root->section.isPageDoc() ?
9603 Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(root->name) :
9604 Doxygen::mainPage.get();
9605 if (pd)
9606 {
9607 for (const BaseInfo &bi : root->extends)
9608 {
9609 PageDef *subPd = Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(bi.name);
9610 if (pd==subPd)
9611 {
9612 term("page defined %s with label %s is a direct "
9613 "subpage of itself! Please remove this cyclic dependency.\n",
9614 qPrint(warn_line(pd->docFile(),pd->docLine())),qPrint(pd->name()));
9615 }
9616 else if (subPd)
9617 {
9618 pd->addInnerCompound(subPd);
9619 //printf("*** Added subpage relation: %s->%s\n",
9620 // qPrint(pd->name()),qPrint(subPd->name()));
9621 }
9622 }
9623 }
9624 }
9625 for (const auto &e : root->children()) computePageRelations(e.get());
9626}
9627
9628static void checkPageRelations()
9629{
9630 for (const auto &pd : *Doxygen::pageLinkedMap)
9631 {
9632 Definition *ppd = pd->getOuterScope();
9633 while (ppd)
9634 {
9635 if (ppd==pd.get())
9636 {
9637 term("page defined %s with label %s is a subpage "
9638 "of itself! Please remove this cyclic dependency.\n",
9639 qPrint(warn_line(pd->docFile(),pd->docLine())),qPrint(pd->name()));
9640 }
9641 ppd=ppd->getOuterScope();
9642 }
9643 }
9644}
9645
9646//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9647
9648static void resolveUserReferences()
9649{
9650 for (const auto &si : SectionManager::instance())
9651 {
9652 //printf("si->label='%s' si->definition=%s si->fileName='%s'\n",
9653 // qPrint(si->label),si->definition?qPrint(si->definition->name()):"<none>",
9654 // qPrint(si->fileName));
9655 PageDef *pd=nullptr;
9656
9657 // hack: the items of a todo/test/bug/deprecated list are all fragments from
9658 // different files, so the resulting section's all have the wrong file
9659 // name (not from the todo/test/bug/deprecated list, but from the file in
9660 // which they are defined). We correct this here by looking at the
9661 // generated section labels!
9662 for (const RefListManager::Ptr &rl : RefListManager::instance())
9663 {
9664 QCString label="_"+rl->listName(); // "_todo", "_test", ...
9665 if (si->label().left(label.length())==label)
9666 {
9667 si->setFileName(rl->listName());
9668 si->setGenerated(TRUE);
9669 break;
9670 }
9671 }
9672
9673 //printf("start: si->label=%s si->fileName=%s\n",qPrint(si->label),qPrint(si->fileName));
9674 if (!si->generated())
9675 {
9676 // if this section is in a page and the page is in a group, then we
9677 // have to adjust the link file name to point to the group.
9678 if (!si->fileName().isEmpty() &&
9679 (pd=Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(si->fileName())) &&
9680 pd->getGroupDef())
9681 {
9682 si->setFileName(pd->getGroupDef()->getOutputFileBase());
9683 }
9684
9685 if (si->definition())
9686 {
9687 // TODO: there should be one function in Definition that returns
9688 // the file to link to, so we can avoid the following tests.
9689 const GroupDef *gd=nullptr;
9690 if (si->definition()->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
9691 {
9692 gd = (toMemberDef(si->definition()))->getGroupDef();
9693 }
9694
9695 if (gd)
9696 {
9697 si->setFileName(gd->getOutputFileBase());
9698 }
9699 else
9700 {
9701 //si->fileName=si->definition->getOutputFileBase();
9702 //printf("Setting si->fileName to %s\n",qPrint(si->fileName));
9703 }
9704 }
9705 }
9706 //printf("end: si->label=%s si->fileName=%s\n",qPrint(si->label),qPrint(si->fileName));
9707 }
9708}

9730//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9731// create a (sorted) list & dictionary of example pages
9732
9733static void buildExampleList(Entry *root)
9734{
9735 if ((root->section.isExample() || root->section.isExampleLineno()) && !root->name.isEmpty())
9736 {
9737 if (Doxygen::exampleLinkedMap->find(root->name))
9738 {
9739 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
9740 "Example %s was already documented. Ignoring "
9741 "documentation found here.",
9742 qPrint(root->name)
9743 );
9744 }
9745 else
9746 {
9747 PageDef *pd = Doxygen::exampleLinkedMap->add(root->name,
9748 createPageDef(root->fileName,root->startLine,
9749 root->name,root->brief+root->doc+root->inbodyDocs,root->args));
9750 pd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
9751 pd->setFileName(convertNameToFile(pd->name()+"-example",FALSE,TRUE));
9752 pd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
9753 pd->setLanguage(root->lang);
9754 pd->setShowLineNo(root->section.isExampleLineno());
9755
9756 //we don't add example to groups
9757 //addExampleToGroups(root,pd);
9758 }
9759 }
9760 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildExampleList(e.get());
9761}

9803
9804void printLayout()
9805{
9806 bool extraIndent = false;
9807 Debug::print(Debug::Layout,0,"Part: Navigation index\n");
9808 for (const auto &e : LayoutDocManager::instance().rootNavEntry()->children())
9809 {
9810 printNavLayout(e.get(),2);
9811 }
9812
9813 for (int i = 0; i < LayoutDocManager::NrParts; i++)
9814 {
9815 Debug::print(Debug::Layout,0,"\nPart: %s\n", qPrint(LayoutDocManager::partToString(i)));
9816 for (const auto &lde : LayoutDocManager::instance().docEntries(static_cast<LayoutDocManager::LayoutPart>(i)))
9817 {
9818 if (const LayoutDocEntrySimple *ldes = dynamic_cast<const LayoutDocEntrySimple*>(lde.get()))
9819 {
9820 if (lde->kind() == LayoutDocEntry::MemberDeclEnd || lde->kind() == LayoutDocEntry::MemberDefEnd) extraIndent = false;
9821 Debug::print(Debug::Layout,0," %skind: %s, visible=%d\n",
9822 extraIndent? " " : "",qPrint(lde->entryToString()), ldes->visible());
9823 if (lde->kind() == LayoutDocEntry::MemberDeclStart || lde->kind() == LayoutDocEntry::MemberDefStart) extraIndent = true;
9824 }
9825 else if (const LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl *lmdecl = dynamic_cast<const LayoutDocEntryMemberDecl*>(lde.get()))
9826 {
9827 Debug::print(Debug::Layout,0," %scomplex kind: %s, type: %s\n",
9828 extraIndent? " " : "",qPrint(lde->entryToString()),qPrint(lmdecl->type.to_string()));
9829 }
9830 else if (const LayoutDocEntryMemberDef *lmdef = dynamic_cast<const LayoutDocEntryMemberDef*>(lde.get()))
9831 {
9832 Debug::print(Debug::Layout,0," %scomplex kind: %s, type: %s\n",
9833 extraIndent? " " : "",qPrint(lde->entryToString()),qPrint(lmdef->type.to_string()));
9834 }
9835 else
9836 {
9837 // should not happen
9838 Debug::print(Debug::Layout,0," %snot handled kind: %s\n",extraIndent? " " : "",qPrint(lde->entryToString()));
9839 }
9840 }
9841 }
9842}

9861//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9862// generate the example documentation
9863
9864static void generateExampleDocs()
9865{
9866 g_outputList->disable(OutputType::Man);
9867 for (const auto &pd : *Doxygen::exampleLinkedMap)
9868 {
9869 msg("Generating docs for example %s...\n",qPrint(pd->name()));
9870 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguageFromFileName(pd->name(), SrcLangExt::Unknown);
9871 if (lang != SrcLangExt::Unknown)
9872 {
9873 QCString ext = getFileNameExtension(pd->name());
9874 auto intf = Doxygen::parserManager->getCodeParser(ext);
9875 intf->resetCodeParserState();
9876 }
9877 QCString n=pd->getOutputFileBase();
9878 startFile(*g_outputList,n,n,pd->name());
9879 startTitle(*g_outputList,n);
9880 g_outputList->docify(pd->name());
9881 endTitle(*g_outputList,n,QCString());
9882 g_outputList->startContents();
9883 QCString lineNoOptStr;
9884 if (pd->showLineNo())
9885 {
9886 lineNoOptStr="{lineno}";
9887 }
9888 g_outputList->generateDoc(pd->docFile(), // file
9889 pd->docLine(), // startLine
9890 pd.get(), // context
9891 nullptr, // memberDef
9892 (pd->briefDescription().isEmpty()?"":pd->briefDescription()+"\n\n")+
9893 pd->documentation()+"\n\n\\include"+lineNoOptStr+" "+pd->name(), // docs
9894 TRUE, // index words
9895 TRUE, // is example
9896 pd->name(),
9897 FALSE,
9898 FALSE,
9899 Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT)
9900 );
9901 endFile(*g_outputList); // contains g_outputList->endContents()
9902 }
9903 g_outputList->enable(OutputType::Man);
9904}

9919
9920//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9921// generate module pages
9922
9923static void generateNamespaceClassDocs(const ClassLinkedRefMap &classList)
9924{
9925 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
9926 if (numThreads>1) // multi threaded processing
9927 {
9928 struct DocContext
9929 {
9930 DocContext(ClassDefMutable *cdm_,const OutputList &ol_)
9931 : cdm(cdm_), ol(ol_) {}
9932 ClassDefMutable *cdm;
9933 OutputList ol;
9934 };
9935 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
9936 std::vector< std::future< std::shared_ptr<DocContext> > > results;
9937 // for each class in the namespace...
9938 for (const auto &cd : classList)
9939 {
9940 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd);
9941 if (cdm)
9942 {
9943 auto ctx = std::make_shared<DocContext>(cdm,*g_outputList);
9944 auto processFile = [ctx]()
9945 {
9946 if ( ( ctx->cdm->isLinkableInProject() &&
9947 ctx->cdm->templateMaster()==nullptr
9948 ) // skip external references, anonymous compounds and
9949 // template instances and nested classes
9950 && !ctx->cdm->isHidden() && !ctx->cdm->isEmbeddedInOuterScope()
9951 )
9952 {
9953 msg("Generating docs for compound %s...\n",qPrint(ctx->cdm->displayName()));
9954 ctx->cdm->writeDocumentation(ctx->ol);
9955 ctx->cdm->writeMemberList(ctx->ol);
9956 }
9957 ctx->cdm->writeDocumentationForInnerClasses(ctx->ol);
9958 return ctx;
9959 };
9960 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
9961 }
9962 }
9963 // wait for the results
9964 for (auto &f : results)
9965 {
9966 auto ctx = f.get();
9967 }
9968 }
9969 else // single threaded processing
9970 {
9971 // for each class in the namespace...
9972 for (const auto &cd : classList)
9973 {
9974 ClassDefMutable *cdm = toClassDefMutable(cd);
9975 if (cdm)
9976 {
9977 if ( ( cd->isLinkableInProject() &&
9978 cd->templateMaster()==nullptr
9979 ) // skip external references, anonymous compounds and
9980 // template instances and nested classes
9981 && !cd->isHidden() && !cd->isEmbeddedInOuterScope()
9982 )
9983 {
9984 msg("Generating docs for compound %s...\n",qPrint(cd->displayName()));
9985
9986 cdm->writeDocumentation(*g_outputList);
9987 cdm->writeMemberList(*g_outputList);
9988 }
9989 cdm->writeDocumentationForInnerClasses(*g_outputList);
9990 }
9991 }
9992 }
9993}
9994
9995static void generateNamespaceConceptDocs(const ConceptLinkedRefMap &conceptList)
9996{
9997 // for each concept in the namespace...
9998 for (const auto &cd : conceptList)
9999 {
10000 ConceptDefMutable *cdm = toConceptDefMutable(cd);
10001 if ( cdm && cd->isLinkableInProject() && !cd->isHidden())
10002 {
10003 msg("Generating docs for concept %s...\n",qPrint(cd->name()));
10004 cdm->writeDocumentation(*g_outputList);
10005 }
10006 }
10007}
10008
10009static void generateNamespaceDocs()
10010{
10011 bool sliceOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_SLICE);
10012
10013 //writeNamespaceIndex(*g_outputList);
10014
10015 // for each namespace...
10016 for (const auto &nd : *Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap)
10017 {
10018 if (nd->isLinkableInProject())
10019 {
10020 NamespaceDefMutable *ndm = toNamespaceDefMutable(nd.get());
10021 if (ndm)
10022 {
10023 msg("Generating docs for namespace %s\n",qPrint(nd->displayName()));
10024 ndm->writeDocumentation(*g_outputList);
10025 }
10026 }
10027
10028 generateNamespaceClassDocs(nd->getClasses());
10029 if (sliceOpt)
10030 {
10031 generateNamespaceClassDocs(nd->getInterfaces());
10032 generateNamespaceClassDocs(nd->getStructs());
10033 generateNamespaceClassDocs(nd->getExceptions());
10034 }
10035 generateNamespaceConceptDocs(nd->getConcepts());
10036 }
10037}
10038
10039static void runHtmlHelpCompiler()
10040{
10041 std::string oldDir = Dir::currentDirPath();
10042 Dir::setCurrent(Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT).str());
10043 Portable::setShortDir();
10044 if (Portable::system(Config_getString(HHC_LOCATION).data(), qPrint(HtmlHelp::hhpFileName), Debug::isFlagSet(Debug::ExtCmd))!=1)
10045 {
10046 err("failed to run html help compiler on %s\n", qPrint(HtmlHelp::hhpFileName));
10047 }
10048 Dir::setCurrent(oldDir);
10049}
10050
10051static void runQHelpGenerator()
10052{
10053 QCString args = Qhp::qhpFileName + " -o \"" + Qhp::getQchFileName() + "\"";
10054 std::string oldDir = Dir::currentDirPath();
10055 Dir::setCurrent(Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT).str());
10056
10057 QCString qhgLocation=Config_getString(QHG_LOCATION);
10058 if (Debug::isFlagSet(Debug::Qhp)) // produce info for debugging
10059 {
10060 // run qhelpgenerator -v and extract the Qt version used
10061 QCString cmd=qhgLocation+ " -v 2>&1";
10062 Debug::print(Debug::ExtCmd,0,"Executing popen(`%s`)\n",qPrint(cmd));
10063 FILE *f=Portable::popen(cmd,"r");
10064 if (!f)
10065 {
10066 err("could not execute %s\n",qPrint(qhgLocation));
10067 }
10068 else
10069 {
10070 const size_t bufSize = 1024;
10071 char inBuf[bufSize+1];
10072 size_t numRead=fread(inBuf,1,bufSize,f);
10073 inBuf[numRead] = '\0';
10074 Debug::print(Debug::Qhp,0,inBuf);
10075 Portable::pclose(f);
10076
10077 int qtVersion=0;
10078 static const reg::Ex versionReg(R"(Qt (\d+)\.(\d+)\.(\d+))");
10079 reg::Match match;
10080 std::string s = inBuf;
10081 if (reg::search(inBuf,match,versionReg))
10082 {
10083 qtVersion = 10000*QCString(match[1].str()).toInt() +
10084 100*QCString(match[2].str()).toInt() +
10085 QCString(match[3].str()).toInt();
10086 }
10087 if (qtVersion>0 && (qtVersion<60000 || qtVersion >= 60205))
10088 {
10089 // dump the output of qhelpgenerator -c file.qhp
10090 // Qt<6 or Qt>=6.2.5 or higher, see https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-101070
10091 cmd=qhgLocation+ " -c " + Qhp::qhpFileName + " 2>&1";
10092 Debug::print(Debug::ExtCmd,0,"Executing popen(`%s`)\n",qPrint(cmd));
10093 f=Portable::popen(cmd,"r");
10094 if (!f)
10095 {
10096 err("could not execute %s\n",qPrint(qhgLocation));
10097 }
10098 else
10099 {
10100 std::string output;
10101 while ((numRead=fread(inBuf,1,bufSize,f))>0)
10102 {
10103 inBuf[numRead] = '\0';
10104 output += inBuf;
10105 }
10106 Portable::pclose(f);
10107 Debug::print(Debug::Qhp,0,output.c_str());
10108 }
10109 }
10110 }
10111 }
10112
10113 if (Portable::system(qhgLocation, args, FALSE))
10114 {
10115 err("failed to run qhelpgenerator on %s\n",qPrint(Qhp::qhpFileName));
10116 }
10117 Dir::setCurrent(oldDir);
10118}

10120//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10121
10122static void computeVerifiedDotPath()
10123{
10124 // check dot path
10125 QCString dotPath = Config_getString(DOT_PATH);
10126 if (!dotPath.isEmpty())
10127 {
10128 FileInfo fi(dotPath.str());
10129 if (!(fi.exists() && fi.isFile()) )// not an existing user specified path + exec
10130 {
10131 dotPath = dotPath+"/dot"+Portable::commandExtension();
10132 FileInfo dp(dotPath.str());
10133 if (!dp.exists() || !dp.isFile())
10134 {
10135 warn_uncond("the dot tool could not be found as '%s'\n",qPrint(dotPath));
10136 dotPath = "dot";
10137 dotPath += Portable::commandExtension();
10138 }
10139 }
10140#if defined(_WIN32) // convert slashes
10141 size_t l=dotPath.length();
10142 for (size_t i=0;i<l;i++) if (dotPath.at(i)=='/') dotPath.at(i)='\\';
10143#endif
10144 }
10145 else
10146 {
10147 dotPath = "dot";
10148 dotPath += Portable::commandExtension();
10149 }
10150 Doxygen::verifiedDotPath = dotPath;
10151 TRACE("{}",Doxygen::verifiedDotPath);
10152}

10156/*! Generate a template version of the configuration file.
10157 * If the \a shortList parameter is TRUE a configuration file without
10158 * comments will be generated.
10159 */
10160static void generateConfigFile(const QCString &configFile,bool shortList,
10161 bool updateOnly=FALSE)
10162{
10163 std::ofstream f;
10164 bool fileOpened=openOutputFile(configFile,f);
10165 bool writeToStdout=configFile=="-";
10166 if (fileOpened)
10167 {
10168 TextStream t(&f);
10169 Config::writeTemplate(t,shortList,updateOnly);
10170 if (!writeToStdout)
10171 {
10172 if (!updateOnly)
10173 {
10174 msg("\n\nConfiguration file '%s' created.\n\n",qPrint(configFile));
10175 msg("Now edit the configuration file and enter\n\n");
10176 if (configFile!="Doxyfile" && configFile!="doxyfile")
10177 msg(" doxygen %s\n\n",qPrint(configFile));
10178 else
10179 msg(" doxygen\n\n");
10180 msg("to generate the documentation for your project\n\n");
10181 }
10182 else
10183 {
10184 msg("\n\nConfiguration file '%s' updated.\n\n",qPrint(configFile));
10185 }
10186 }
10187 }
10188 else
10189 {
10190 term("Cannot open file %s for writing\n",qPrint(configFile));
10191 }
10192}
10193

10195{
10196 std::ofstream f;
10197 bool fileOpened=openOutputFile("-",f);
10198 if (fileOpened)
10199 {
10200 TextStream t(&f);
10201 Config::compareDoxyfile(t,diffList);
10202 }
10203 else
10204 {
10205 term("Cannot open stdout for writing\n");
10206 }
10207}

10209//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10210// read and parse a tag file
10211
10212static void readTagFile(const std::shared_ptr<Entry> &root,const QCString &tagLine)
10213{
10214 QCString fileName;
10215 QCString destName;
10216 int eqPos = tagLine.find('=');
10217 if (eqPos!=-1) // tag command contains a destination
10218 {
10219 fileName = tagLine.left(eqPos).stripWhiteSpace();
10220 destName = tagLine.right(tagLine.length()-eqPos-1).stripWhiteSpace();
10221 if (fileName.isEmpty() || destName.isEmpty()) return;
10222 //printf("insert tagDestination %s->%s\n",qPrint(fi.fileName()),qPrint(destName));
10223 }
10224 else
10225 {
10226 fileName = tagLine;
10227 }
10228
10229 FileInfo fi(fileName.str());
10230 if (!fi.exists() || !fi.isFile())
10231 {
10232 err("Tag file '%s' does not exist or is not a file. Skipping it...\n",
10233 qPrint(fileName));
10234 return;
10235 }
10236
10237 if (Doxygen::tagFileSet.find(fi.absFilePath().c_str()) != Doxygen::tagFileSet.end()) return;
10238
10239 Doxygen::tagFileSet.emplace(fi.absFilePath());
10240
10241 if (!destName.isEmpty())
10242 {
10243 Doxygen::tagDestinationMap.emplace(fi.absFilePath(), destName.str());
10244 msg("Reading tag file '%s', location '%s'...\n",qPrint(fileName),qPrint(destName));
10245 }
10246 else
10247 msg("Reading tag file '%s'...\n",qPrint(fileName));
10248
10249 parseTagFile(root,fi.absFilePath().c_str());
10250}

10253static void copyLatexStyleSheet()
10254{
10255 const StringVector &latexExtraStyleSheet = Config_getList(LATEX_EXTRA_STYLESHEET);
10256 for (const auto &sheet : latexExtraStyleSheet)
10257 {
10258 std::string fileName = sheet;
10259 if (!fileName.empty())
10260 {
10261 FileInfo fi(fileName);
10262 if (!fi.exists())
10263 {
10264 err("Style sheet '%s' specified by LATEX_EXTRA_STYLESHEET does not exist!\n",qPrint(fileName));
10265 }
10266 else if (fi.isDir())
10267 {
10268 err("Style sheet '%s' specified by LATEX_EXTRA_STYLESHEET is a directory, it has to be a file!\n", qPrint(fileName));
10269 }
10270 else
10271 {
10272 QCString destFileName = Config_getString(LATEX_OUTPUT)+"/"+fi.fileName();
10273 if (!checkExtension(fi.fileName().c_str(), LATEX_STYLE_EXTENSION))
10274 {
10275 destFileName += LATEX_STYLE_EXTENSION;
10276 }
10277 copyFile(QCString(fileName), destFileName);
10278 }
10279 }
10280 }

10283//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10284static void copyStyleSheet()
10285{
10286 QCString htmlStyleSheet = Config_getString(HTML_STYLESHEET);
10287 if (!htmlStyleSheet.isEmpty())
10288 {
10289 if (!htmlStyleSheet.startsWith("http:") && !htmlStyleSheet.startsWith("https:"))
10290 {
10291 FileInfo fi(htmlStyleSheet.str());
10292 if (!fi.exists())
10293 {
10294 err("Style sheet '%s' specified by HTML_STYLESHEET does not exist!\n",qPrint(htmlStyleSheet));
10295 htmlStyleSheet = Config_updateString(HTML_STYLESHEET,""); // revert to the default
10296 }
10297 else if (fi.isDir())
10298 {
10299 err("Style sheet '%s' specified by HTML_STYLESHEET is a directory, it has to be a file!\n",qPrint(htmlStyleSheet));
10300 htmlStyleSheet = Config_updateString(HTML_STYLESHEET,""); // revert to the default
10301 }
10302 else
10303 {
10304 QCString destFileName = Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT)+"/"+fi.fileName();
10305 copyFile(htmlStyleSheet,destFileName);
10306 }
10307 }
10308 }
10309 const StringVector &htmlExtraStyleSheet = Config_getList(HTML_EXTRA_STYLESHEET);
10310 for (const auto &sheet : htmlExtraStyleSheet)
10311 {
10312 QCString fileName(sheet);
10313 if (!fileName.isEmpty() && !fileName.startsWith("http:") && !fileName.startsWith("https:"))
10314 {
10315 FileInfo fi(fileName.str());
10316 if (!fi.exists())
10317 {
10318 err("Style sheet '%s' specified by HTML_EXTRA_STYLESHEET does not exist!\n",qPrint(fileName));
10319 }
10320 else if (fi.fileName()=="doxygen.css" || fi.fileName()=="tabs.css" || fi.fileName()=="navtree.css")
10321 {
10322 err("Style sheet %s specified by HTML_EXTRA_STYLESHEET is already a built-in stylesheet. Please use a different name\n",qPrint(fi.fileName()));
10323 }
10324 else if (fi.isDir())
10325 {
10326 err("Style sheet '%s' specified by HTML_EXTRA_STYLESHEET is a directory, it has to be a file!\n",qPrint(fileName));
10327 }
10328 else
10329 {
10330 QCString destFileName = Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT)+"/"+fi.fileName();
10331 copyFile(QCString(fileName), destFileName);
10332 }
10333 }
10334 }

10412//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10413
10414static void generateDiskNames()
10415{
10416 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap)
10417 {
10418 struct FileEntry
10419 {
10420 FileEntry(const QCString &p,FileDef *fd) : path(p), fileDef(fd) {}
10421 QCString path;
10422 FileDef *fileDef;
10423 };
10424
10425 // collect the entry for which to compute the longest common prefix (LCP) of the path
10426 std::vector<FileEntry> fileEntries;
10427 for (const auto &fd : *fn)
10428 {
10429 if (!fd->isReference()) // skip external references
10430 {
10431 fileEntries.emplace_back(fd->getPath(),fd.get());
10432 }
10433 }
10434
10435 size_t size = fileEntries.size();
10436
10437 if (size==1) // name if unique, so diskname is simply the name
10438 {
10439 FileDef *fd = fileEntries[0].fileDef;
10440 fd->setDiskName(fn->fileName());
10441 }
10442 else if (size>1) // multiple occurrences of the same file name
10443 {
10444 // sort the array
10445 std::stable_sort(fileEntries.begin(),
10446 fileEntries.end(),
10447 [](const FileEntry &fe1,const FileEntry &fe2)
10448 { return qstricmp_sort(fe1.path,fe2.path)<0; }
10449 );
10450
10451 // since the entries are sorted, the common prefix of the whole array is same
10452 // as the common prefix between the first and last entry
10453 const FileEntry &first = fileEntries[0];
10454 const FileEntry &last = fileEntries[size-1];
10455 int first_path_size = static_cast<int>(first.path.size())-1; // -1 to skip trailing slash
10456 int last_path_size = static_cast<int>(last.path.size())-1; // -1 to skip trailing slash
10457 int j=0;
10458 int i=0;
10459 for (i=0;i<first_path_size && i<last_path_size;i++)
10460 {
10461 if (first.path[i]=='/') j=i;
10462 if (first.path[i]!=last.path[i]) break;
10463 }
10464 if (i==first_path_size && i<last_path_size && last.path[i]=='/')
10465 {
10466 // case first='some/path' and last='some/path/more' => match is 'some/path'
10467 j=first_path_size;
10468 }
10469 else if (i==last_path_size && i<first_path_size && first.path[i]=='/')
10470 {
10471 // case first='some/path/more' and last='some/path' => match is 'some/path'
10472 j=last_path_size;
10473 }
10474
10475 // add non-common part of the path to the name
10476 for (auto &fileEntry : fileEntries)
10477 {
10478 QCString prefix = fileEntry.path.right(fileEntry.path.length()-j-1);
10479 fileEntry.fileDef->setName(prefix+fn->fileName());
10480 //printf("!!!!!!!! non unique disk name=%s:%s\n",qPrint(prefix),fn->fileName());
10481 fileEntry.fileDef->setDiskName(prefix+fn->fileName());
10482 }
10483 }
10484 }
10485}

10488
10489//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10490
10491static std::unique_ptr<OutlineParserInterface> getParserForFile(const QCString &fn)
10492{
10493 QCString fileName=fn;
10494 QCString extension;
10495 int sep = fileName.findRev('/');
10496 int ei = fileName.findRev('.');
10497 if (ei!=-1 && (sep==-1 || ei>sep)) // matches dir/file.ext but not dir.1/file
10498 {
10499 extension=fileName.right(fileName.length()-ei);
10500 }
10501 else
10502 {
10503 extension = ".no_extension";
10504 }
10505
10506 return Doxygen::parserManager->getOutlineParser(extension);
10507}
10508
10509static std::shared_ptr<Entry> parseFile(OutlineParserInterface &parser,
10510 FileDef *fd,const QCString &fn,
10511 ClangTUParser *clangParser,bool newTU)
10512{
10513 QCString fileName=fn;
10514 AUTO_TRACE("fileName={}",fileName);
10515 QCString extension;
10516 int ei = fileName.findRev('.');
10517 if (ei!=-1)
10518 {
10519 extension=fileName.right(fileName.length()-ei);
10520 }
10521 else
10522 {
10523 extension = ".no_extension";
10524 }
10525
10526 FileInfo fi(fileName.str());
10527 std::string preBuf;
10528
10529 if (Config_getBool(ENABLE_PREPROCESSING) &&
10530 parser.needsPreprocessing(extension))
10531 {
10532 Preprocessor preprocessor;
10533 const StringVector &includePath = Config_getList(INCLUDE_PATH);
10534 for (const auto &s : includePath)
10535 {
10536 std::string absPath = FileInfo(s).absFilePath();
10537 preprocessor.addSearchDir(absPath.c_str());
10538 }
10539 std::string inBuf;
10540 msg("Preprocessing %s...\n",qPrint(fn));
10541 readInputFile(fileName,inBuf);
10542 addTerminalCharIfMissing(inBuf,'\n');
10543 preprocessor.processFile(fileName,inBuf,preBuf);
10544 }
10545 else // no preprocessing
10546 {
10547 msg("Reading %s...\n",qPrint(fn));
10548 readInputFile(fileName,preBuf);
10549 addTerminalCharIfMissing(preBuf,'\n');
10550 }
10551
10552 std::string convBuf;
10553 convBuf.reserve(preBuf.size()+1024);
10554
10555 // convert multi-line C++ comments to C style comments
10556 convertCppComments(preBuf,convBuf,fileName.str());
10557
10558 std::shared_ptr<Entry> fileRoot = std::make_shared<Entry>();
10559 // use language parse to parse the file
10560 if (clangParser)
10561 {
10562 if (newTU) clangParser->parse();
10563 clangParser->switchToFile(fd);
10564 }
10565 parser.parseInput(fileName,convBuf.data(),fileRoot,clangParser);
10566 fileRoot->setFileDef(fd);
10567 return fileRoot;
10568}
10569
10570//! parse the list of input files
10571static void parseFilesMultiThreading(const std::shared_ptr<Entry> &root)
10572{
10573 AUTO_TRACE();
10574#if USE_LIBCLANG
10575 if (Doxygen::clangAssistedParsing)
10576 {
10577 StringUnorderedSet processedFiles;
10578
10579 // create a dictionary with files to process
10580 StringUnorderedSet filesToProcess;
10581 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10582 {
10583 filesToProcess.insert(s);
10584 }
10585
10586 std::mutex processedFilesLock;
10587 // process source files (and their include dependencies)
10588 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
10589 msg("Processing input using %zu threads.\n",numThreads);
10590 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
10591 using FutureType = std::vector< std::shared_ptr<Entry> >;
10592 std::vector< std::future< FutureType > > results;
10593 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10594 {
10595 bool ambig = false;
10596 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig);
10597 ASSERT(fd!=nullptr);
10598 if (fd->isSource() && !fd->isReference() && fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Cpp) // this is a source file
10599 {
10600 // lambda representing the work to executed by a thread
10601 auto processFile = [s,&filesToProcess,&processedFilesLock,&processedFiles]() {
10602 bool ambig_l = false;
10603 std::vector< std::shared_ptr<Entry> > roots;
10604 FileDef *fd_l = findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig_l);
10605 auto clangParser = ClangParser::instance()->createTUParser(fd_l);
10606 auto parser = getParserForFile(s.c_str());
10607 auto fileRoot { parseFile(*parser.get(),fd_l,s.c_str(),clangParser.get(),true) };
10608 roots.push_back(fileRoot);
10609
10610 // Now process any include files in the same translation unit
10611 // first. When libclang is used this is much more efficient.
10612 for (auto incFile : clangParser->filesInSameTU())
10613 {
10614 if (filesToProcess.find(incFile)!=filesToProcess.end())
10615 {
10616 bool needsToBeProcessed = false;
10617 {
10618 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(processedFilesLock);
10619 needsToBeProcessed = processedFiles.find(incFile)==processedFiles.end();
10620 if (needsToBeProcessed) processedFiles.insert(incFile);
10621 }
10622 if (incFile!=s && needsToBeProcessed)
10623 {
10624 FileDef *ifd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,incFile.c_str(),ambig_l);
10625 if (ifd && !ifd->isReference())
10626 {
10627 //printf(" Processing %s in same translation unit as %s\n",incFile,s->c_str());
10628 fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),ifd,incFile.c_str(),clangParser.get(),false);
10629 roots.push_back(fileRoot);
10630 }
10631 }
10632 }
10633 }
10634 return roots;
10635 };
10636 // dispatch the work and collect the future results
10637 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
10638 }
10639 }
10640 // synchronize with the Entry result lists produced and add them to the root
10641 for (auto &f : results)
10642 {
10643 auto l = f.get();
10644 for (auto &e : l)
10645 {
10646 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(e);
10647 }
10648 }
10649 // process remaining files
10650 results.clear();
10651 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10652 {
10653 if (processedFiles.find(s)==processedFiles.end()) // not yet processed
10654 {
10655 // lambda representing the work to executed by a thread
10656 auto processFile = [s]() {
10657 bool ambig = false;
10658 std::vector< std::shared_ptr<Entry> > roots;
10659 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig);
10660 auto parser { getParserForFile(s.c_str()) };
10661 bool useClang = getLanguageFromFileName(s.c_str())==SrcLangExt::Cpp;
10662 if (useClang)
10663 {
10664 auto clangParser = ClangParser::instance()->createTUParser(fd);
10665 auto fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),clangParser.get(),true);
10666 roots.push_back(fileRoot);
10667 }
10668 else
10669 {
10670 auto fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),nullptr,true);
10671 roots.push_back(fileRoot);
10672 }
10673 return roots;
10674 };
10675 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
10676 }
10677 }
10678 // synchronize with the Entry result lists produced and add them to the root
10679 for (auto &f : results)
10680 {
10681 auto l = f.get();
10682 for (auto &e : l)
10683 {
10684 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(e);
10685 }
10686 }
10687 }
10688 else // normal processing
10689#endif
10690 {
10691 std::size_t numThreads = static_cast<std::size_t>(Config_getInt(NUM_PROC_THREADS));
10692 msg("Processing input using %zu threads.\n",numThreads);
10693 ThreadPool threadPool(numThreads);
10694 using FutureType = std::shared_ptr<Entry>;
10695 std::vector< std::future< FutureType > > results;
10696 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10697 {
10698 // lambda representing the work to executed by a thread
10699 auto processFile = [s]() {
10700 bool ambig = false;
10701 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig);
10702 auto parser = getParserForFile(s.c_str());
10703 auto fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),nullptr,true);
10704 return fileRoot;
10705 };
10706 // dispatch the work and collect the future results
10707 results.emplace_back(threadPool.queue(processFile));
10708 }
10709 // synchronize with the Entry results produced and add them to the root
10710 for (auto &f : results)
10711 {
10712 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(f.get());
10713 }
10714 }
10715}
10716
10717//! parse the list of input files
10718static void parseFilesSingleThreading(const std::shared_ptr<Entry> &root)
10719{
10720 AUTO_TRACE();
10721#if USE_LIBCLANG
10722 if (Doxygen::clangAssistedParsing)
10723 {
10724 StringUnorderedSet processedFiles;
10725
10726 // create a dictionary with files to process
10727 StringUnorderedSet filesToProcess;
10728 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10729 {
10730 filesToProcess.insert(s);
10731 }
10732
10733 // process source files (and their include dependencies)
10734 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10735 {
10736 bool ambig = false;
10737 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig);
10738 ASSERT(fd!=nullptr);
10739 if (fd->isSource() && !fd->isReference() && getLanguageFromFileName(s.c_str())==SrcLangExt::Cpp) // this is a source file
10740 {
10741 auto clangParser = ClangParser::instance()->createTUParser(fd);
10742 auto parser { getParserForFile(s.c_str()) };
10743 auto fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),clangParser.get(),true);
10744 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(fileRoot);
10745 processedFiles.insert(s);
10746
10747 // Now process any include files in the same translation unit
10748 // first. When libclang is used this is much more efficient.
10749 for (auto incFile : clangParser->filesInSameTU())
10750 {
10751 //printf(" file %s\n",incFile.c_str());
10752 if (filesToProcess.find(incFile)!=filesToProcess.end() && // file need to be processed
10753 processedFiles.find(incFile)==processedFiles.end()) // and is not processed already
10754 {
10755 FileDef *ifd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,incFile.c_str(),ambig);
10756 if (ifd && !ifd->isReference())
10757 {
10758 //printf(" Processing %s in same translation unit as %s\n",incFile.c_str(),s.c_str());
10759 fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),ifd,incFile.c_str(),clangParser.get(),false);
10760 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(fileRoot);
10761 processedFiles.insert(incFile);
10762 }
10763 }
10764 }
10765 }
10766 }
10767 // process remaining files
10768 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10769 {
10770 if (processedFiles.find(s)==processedFiles.end()) // not yet processed
10771 {
10772 bool ambig = false;
10773 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig);
10774 if (getLanguageFromFileName(s.c_str())==SrcLangExt::Cpp) // not yet processed
10775 {
10776 auto clangParser = ClangParser::instance()->createTUParser(fd);
10777 auto parser { getParserForFile(s.c_str()) };
10778 auto fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),clangParser.get(),true);
10779 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(fileRoot);
10780 }
10781 else
10782 {
10783 std::unique_ptr<OutlineParserInterface> parser { getParserForFile(s.c_str()) };
10784 std::shared_ptr<Entry> fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),nullptr,true);
10785 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(fileRoot);
10786 }
10787 processedFiles.insert(s);
10788 }
10789 }
10790 }
10791 else // normal processing
10792#endif
10793 {
10794 for (const auto &s : g_inputFiles)
10795 {
10796 bool ambig = false;
10797 FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameLinkedMap,s.c_str(),ambig);
10798 ASSERT(fd!=nullptr);
10799 std::unique_ptr<OutlineParserInterface> parser { getParserForFile(s.c_str()) };
10800 std::shared_ptr<Entry> fileRoot = parseFile(*parser.get(),fd,s.c_str(),nullptr,true);
10801 root->moveToSubEntryAndKeep(std::move(fileRoot));
10802 }
10803 }
10804}
10805
10806// resolves a path that may include symlinks, if a recursive symlink is
10807// found an empty string is returned.
10808static std::string resolveSymlink(const std::string &path)
10809{
10810 int sepPos=0;
10811 int oldPos=0;
10812 StringUnorderedSet nonSymlinks;
10813 StringUnorderedSet known;
10814 QCString result(path);
10815 QCString oldPrefix = "/";
10816 do
10817 {
10818#if defined(_WIN32)
10819 // UNC path, skip server and share name
10820 if (sepPos==0 && (result.startsWith("//") || result.startsWith("\\\\")))
10821 sepPos = result.find('/',2);
10822 if (sepPos!=-1)
10823 sepPos = result.find('/',sepPos+1);
10824#else
10825 sepPos = result.find('/',sepPos+1);
10826#endif
10827 QCString prefix = sepPos==-1 ? result : result.left(sepPos);
10828 if (nonSymlinks.find(prefix.str())==nonSymlinks.end())
10829 {
10830 FileInfo fi(prefix.str());
10831 if (fi.isSymLink())
10832 {
10833 QCString target = fi.readLink();
10834 bool isRelative = FileInfo(target.str()).isRelative();
10835 if (isRelative)
10836 {
10837 target = Dir::cleanDirPath(oldPrefix.str()+"/"+target.str());
10838 }
10839 if (sepPos!=-1)
10840 {
10841 if (fi.isDir() && target.length()>0 && target.at(target.length()-1)!='/')
10842 {
10843 target+='/';
10844 }
10845 target+=result.mid(sepPos);
10846 }
10847 result = Dir::cleanDirPath(target.str());
10848 if (known.find(result.str())!=known.end()) return std::string(); // recursive symlink!
10849 known.insert(result.str());
10850 if (isRelative)
10851 {
10852 sepPos = oldPos;
10853 }
10854 else // link to absolute path
10855 {
10856 sepPos = 0;
10857 oldPrefix = "/";
10858 }
10859 }
10860 else
10861 {
10862 nonSymlinks.insert(prefix.str());
10863 oldPrefix = prefix;
10864 }
10865 oldPos = sepPos;
10866 }
10867 }
10868 while (sepPos!=-1);
10869 return Dir::cleanDirPath(result.str());
10870}
10871
10872static StringUnorderedSet g_pathsVisited(1009);
10873
10874//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10875// Read all files matching at least one pattern in 'patList' in the
10876// directory represented by 'fi'.
10877// The directory is read iff the recursiveFlag is set.
10878// The contents of all files is append to the input string
10879
10880static void readDir(FileInfo *fi,
10881 FileNameLinkedMap *fnMap,
10882 StringUnorderedSet *exclSet,
10883 const StringVector *patList,
10884 const StringVector *exclPatList,
10885 StringVector *resultList,
10886 StringUnorderedSet *resultSet,
10887 bool errorIfNotExist,
10888 bool recursive,
10889 StringUnorderedSet *killSet,
10890 StringUnorderedSet *paths
10891 )
10892{
10893 std::string dirName = fi->absFilePath();
10894 if (paths && !dirName.empty())
10895 {
10896 paths->insert(dirName);
10897 }
10898 //printf("%s isSymLink()=%d\n",qPrint(dirName),fi->isSymLink());
10899 if (fi->isSymLink())
10900 {
10901 dirName = resolveSymlink(dirName);
10902 if (dirName.empty())
10903 {
10904 //printf("RECURSIVE SYMLINK: %s\n",qPrint(dirName));
10905 return; // recursive symlink
10906 }
10907 }
10908
10909 if (g_pathsVisited.find(dirName)!=g_pathsVisited.end())
10910 {
10911 //printf("PATH ALREADY VISITED: %s\n",qPrint(dirName));
10912 return; // already visited path
10913 }
10914 g_pathsVisited.insert(dirName);
10915
10916 Dir dir(dirName);
10917 msg("Searching for files in directory %s\n", qPrint(fi->absFilePath()));
10918 //printf("killSet=%p count=%d\n",killSet,killSet ? (int)killSet->count() : -1);
10919
10920 StringVector dirResultList;
10921
10922 for (const auto &dirEntry : dir.iterator())
10923 {
10924 FileInfo cfi(dirEntry.path());
10925 if (exclSet==nullptr || exclSet->find(cfi.absFilePath())==exclSet->end())
10926 { // file should not be excluded
10927 //printf("killSet->find(%s)\n",qPrint(cfi->absFilePath()));
10928 if (Config_getBool(EXCLUDE_SYMLINKS) && cfi.isSymLink())
10929 {
10930 }
10931 else if (!cfi.exists() || !cfi.isReadable())
10932 {
10933 if (errorIfNotExist)
10934 {
10935 warn_uncond("source '%s' is not a readable file or directory... skipping.\n",cfi.absFilePath().c_str());
10936 }
10937 }
10938 else if (cfi.isFile() &&
10939 (patList==nullptr || patternMatch(cfi,*patList)) &&
10940 (exclPatList==nullptr || !patternMatch(cfi,*exclPatList)) &&
10941 (killSet==nullptr || killSet->find(cfi.absFilePath())==killSet->end())
10942 )
10943 {
10944 std::string name=cfi.fileName();
10945 std::string path=cfi.dirPath()+"/";
10946 std::string fullName=path+name;
10947 if (fnMap)
10948 {
10949 auto fd = createFileDef(QCString(path),QCString(name));
10950 FileName *fn=nullptr;
10951 if (!name.empty())
10952 {
10953 fn = fnMap->add(QCString(name),QCString(fullName));
10954 fn->push_back(std::move(fd));
10955 }
10956 }
10957 dirResultList.push_back(fullName);
10958 if (resultSet) resultSet->insert(fullName);
10959 if (killSet) killSet->insert(fullName);
10960 }
10961 else if (recursive &&
10962 cfi.isDir() &&
10963 (exclPatList==nullptr || !patternMatch(cfi,*exclPatList)) &&
10964 cfi.fileName().at(0)!='.') // skip "." ".." and ".dir"
10965 {
10966 FileInfo acfi(cfi.absFilePath());
10967 readDir(&acfi,fnMap,exclSet,
10968 patList,exclPatList,&dirResultList,resultSet,errorIfNotExist,
10969 recursive,killSet,paths);
10970 }
10971 }
10972 }
10973 if (resultList && !dirResultList.empty())
10974 {
10975 // sort the resulting list to make the order platform independent.
10976 std::stable_sort(dirResultList.begin(),
10977 dirResultList.end(),
10978 [](const auto &f1,const auto &f2) { return qstricmp_sort(f1.c_str(),f2.c_str())<0; });
10979
10980 // append the sorted results to resultList
10981 resultList->insert(resultList->end(), dirResultList.begin(), dirResultList.end());
10982 }
10983}
10984
10985
10986//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10987// read a file or all files in a directory and append their contents to the
10988// input string. The names of the files are appended to the 'fiList' list.
10989
10990void readFileOrDirectory(const QCString &s,
10991 FileNameLinkedMap *fnMap,
10992 StringUnorderedSet *exclSet,
10993 const StringVector *patList,
10994 const StringVector *exclPatList,
10995 StringVector *resultList,
10996 StringUnorderedSet *resultSet,
10997 bool recursive,
10998 bool errorIfNotExist,
10999 StringUnorderedSet *killSet,
11000 StringUnorderedSet *paths
11001 )
11002{
11003 //printf("killSet count=%d\n",killSet ? (int)killSet->size() : -1);
11004 // strip trailing slashes
11005 if (s.isEmpty()) return;
11006
11007 g_pathsVisited.clear();
11008
11009 FileInfo fi(s.str());
11010 //printf("readFileOrDirectory(%s)\n",s);
11011 {
11012 if (exclSet==nullptr || exclSet->find(fi.absFilePath())==exclSet->end())
11013 {
11014 if (Config_getBool(EXCLUDE_SYMLINKS) && fi.isSymLink())
11015 {
11016 }
11017 else if (!fi.exists() || !fi.isReadable())
11018 {
11019 if (errorIfNotExist)
11020 {
11021 warn_uncond("source '%s' is not a readable file or directory... skipping.\n",qPrint(s));
11022 }
11023 }
11024 else if (fi.isFile())
11025 {
11026 std::string dirPath = fi.dirPath(true);
11027 std::string filePath = fi.absFilePath();
11028 if (paths && !dirPath.empty())
11029 {
11030 paths->insert(dirPath);
11031 }
11032 //printf("killSet.find(%s)=%d\n",qPrint(fi.absFilePath()),killSet.find(fi.absFilePath())!=killSet.end());
11033 if (killSet==nullptr || killSet->find(filePath)==killSet->end())
11034 {
11035 std::string name=fi.fileName();
11036 if (fnMap)
11037 {
11038 auto fd = createFileDef(QCString(dirPath+"/"),QCString(name));
11039 if (!name.empty())
11040 {
11041 FileName *fn = fnMap->add(QCString(name),QCString(filePath));
11042 fn->push_back(std::move(fd));
11043 }
11044 }
11045 if (resultList || resultSet)
11046 {
11047 if (resultList) resultList->push_back(filePath);
11048 if (resultSet) resultSet->insert(filePath);
11049 }
11050
11051 if (killSet) killSet->insert(fi.absFilePath());
11052 }
11053 }
11054 else if (fi.isDir()) // readable dir
11055 {
11056 readDir(&fi,fnMap,exclSet,patList,
11057 exclPatList,resultList,resultSet,errorIfNotExist,
11058 recursive,killSet,paths);
11059 }
11060 }
11061 }
11062}
11063
11064//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
11065
11066static void dumpSymbol(TextStream &t,Definition *d)
11067{
11068 QCString anchor;
11069 if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
11070 {
11071 MemberDef *md = toMemberDef(d);
11072 anchor=":"+md->anchor();
11073 }
11074 QCString scope;
11075 QCString fn = d->getOutputFileBase();
11076 addHtmlExtensionIfMissing(fn);
11077 if (d->getOuterScope() && d->getOuterScope()!=Doxygen::globalScope)
11078 {
11079 scope = fn;
11080 }
11081 t << "REPLACE INTO symbols (symbol_id,scope_id,name,file,line) VALUES('"
11082 << fn+anchor << "','"
11083 << scope << "','"
11084 << d->name() << "','"
11085 << d->getDefFileName() << "','"
11086 << d->getDefLine()
11087 << "');\n";
11088}
11089
11090static void dumpSymbolMap()
11091{
11092 std::ofstream f = Portable::openOutputStream("symbols.sql");
11093 if (f.is_open())
11094 {
11095 TextStream t(&f);
11096 for (const auto &[name,symList] : *Doxygen::symbolMap)
11097 {
11098 for (const auto &def : symList)
11099 {
11100 dumpSymbol(t,def);
11101 }
11102 }
11103 }
11104}

11106// print developer options of Doxygen
11107static void devUsage()
11108{
11109 Debug::clearFlag(Debug::Time);
11110 msg("Developer parameters:\n");
11111 msg(" -m dump symbol map\n");
11112 msg(" -b making messages output unbuffered\n");
11113#if ENABLE_TRACING
11114 msg(" -t [<file|stdout|stderr>] trace debug info to file, stdout, or stderr (default file stdout)\n");
11115 msg(" -t_time [<file|stdout|stderr>] trace debug info to file, stdout, or stderr (default file stdout),\n"
11116 " and include time and thread information\n");
11117#endif
11118 msg(" -d <level> enable a debug level, such as (multiple invocations of -d are possible):\n");
11119 Debug::printFlags();
11120}

11123//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
11124// print the version of Doxygen
11125
11126static void version(const bool extended)
11127{
11128 Debug::clearFlag(Debug::Time);
11129 QCString versionString = getFullVersion();
11130 msg("%s\n",qPrint(versionString));
11131 if (extended)
11132 {
11133 QCString extVers;
11134 if (!extVers.isEmpty()) extVers+= ", ";
11135 extVers += "sqlite3 ";
11136 extVers += sqlite3_libversion();
11137#if USE_LIBCLANG
11138 if (!extVers.isEmpty()) extVers+= ", ";
11139 extVers += "clang support ";
11140 extVers += CLANG_VERSION_STRING;
11141#endif
11142 if (!extVers.isEmpty())
11143 {
11144 int lastComma = extVers.findRev(',');
11145 if (lastComma != -1) extVers = extVers.replace(lastComma,1," and");
11146 msg(" with %s.\n",qPrint(extVers));
11147 }
11148 }
11149}
